title: peanut patty
directions: Place peanuts, milk, sugar and syrup in heavy pan.
Bring to boil.
Lower heat and simmer.
Cook until soft ball stage (approximately 1 hour).
Remove from heat.
Add vanilla, butter and coloring.
Cool 15 minutes.

title: rotel cheese dip
directions: Melt cheese in
microwave.
Add Ro-Tel.
Heat well and stir. Serve with tortillas.

title: coney island hot dog sauce
directions: Brown hamburg and drain.
Add remaining ingredients and simmer for 20 to 30 minutes.
Makes enough for 45 hot dogs.

title: baked pork chops
directions: Brown pork chops which have been sprinkled with salt and pepper.
Place in baking dish and put 1 tablespoon rice on each chop.
Pour the cooked tomatoes over the chops.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
When ready to serve, lift chops carefully with rice and baked tomatoes intact.
Yield:
4 servings.

title: long island iced tea
directions: Pour all ingredients except cola into highball glass filled with ice. Stir. Top up with chilled cola. Garnish with a wedge of lime.

title: applesauce bran muffins
directions: Mix bran, applesauce, egg, margarine and brown sugar; let stand 5 minutes.
In large bowl, blend flour, baking powder and cinnamon; stir in bran mixture just until blended.
(Batter will be lumpy.)
Stir in raisins.
Makes 12 muffins.
Bake at 400° for 15 to 18 minutes or until done.
Cool slightly and drizzle with applesauce glaze; serve warm.

title: easy sour cream chocolate chip cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. In a large mixing bowl, beat together butter, sugar and eggs with an electric mixer on medium speed until light and fluffy, 3 to 4 minutes. Beat in sour cream and vanilla until well blended. Add flour, baking powder, baking soda and salt; beat well mixed. Stir in nuts and chocolate chips. Turn into a WELL-GREASED AND FLOURED 12-cup Bundt pan. Will be a thick batter.

title: apple spinach salad
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients. Combine sugar and next 4 ingredients in a jar; cover tightly and shake well.
Pour over spinach mixture, tossing gently. Yield: 6 servings.

title: pepsi chicken
directions: Place chicken pieces and melted margarine in a shallow baking dish.
Pour pepsi and ketchup over and bake at 325° for 1 hour, until chicken is tender and browned.

title: cheddar bread
directions: Combine flour, baking powder, sugar, onion salt, oregano, dry mustard and cheese; set aside.

title: layered lettuce salad
directions: Tear lettuce into bite-size pieces and put into 9 x 12-inch glass dish.
Layer rest of ingredients in order given.
Add sugar with mayonnaise and spread over top like icing.
Add grated cheese on top.
Cover with foil or plastic wrap.
Let set overnight or for 8 hours.

title: nutmeg butterballs
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add almonds and vanilla.
Work flour in with fingers.
Shape in the size of a quarter.
Chill until cold.
Bake on greased cookie sheets 15 to 20 minutes at 300°. Mix confectioners sugar and nutmeg.
Roll cookies in mixture while still hot.
Makes 6 dozen.

title: italian cream cake
directions: Combine soda and buttermilk and let stand a few minutes. Cream sugar, oleo, crisco and add egg yolks one at a time. Beat well after each addition. Add buttermilk alternately with flour to cream mixture. Stir in vanilla. Beat egg whites stiff but not dry. Fold into batter gently.
Mix in pecans and coconut. Pour in 3 nine inch cake pans or one 13 X 9 glass dish. Bake at 325 degrees until firm.

title: tater tot hot dish
directions: Layer in casserole in order given.
Peas, corn or mixed vegetables can be used.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: pistachio-chocolate cake
directions: Combine all ingredients except syrup; beat 3 to 5 minutes on high mixer speed.
Pour half into a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan or tube pan.

title: shish kabobs
directions: Place meat cubes, dry onion, garlic, oil, lemon juice, thyme, salt and pepper in bowl.
Coat meat with marinade.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Arrange tomato, meat cubes, green peppers and whole onions on a skewer.
Place skewers on red hot charcoal. Broil for 5 minutes on one side, turn and broil over coals for 5 minutes.
Skewers should be 3 inches from coals.

title: "make ahead" mashed potatoes
directions: Mash potatoes; add cream cheese in small pieces and then butter.
Beat well and mix in sour cream.
Add eggs and onion to milk and then add to potatoes with seasonings.
Place in greased or "Pammed" 9-inch casserole and refrigerate if not using immediately. Bake in preheated 350° oven for 45 minutes until lightly browned. Serves 8 to 12.

title: minie loaf
directions: Chop
onions
and
green peppers in mixing bowl with the chopped meat and wheat bread, add eggs, saraga or beef sausage, mix in
Old
Bay
seasoning
to finish the minie loaf.
Bake at 350°.
Serves 6 to 10.

title: pumpkin nut bread
directions: Sift together first 6 ingredients.
Combine pumpkin, sugar, milk and eggs in mixing bowl.
Add dry ingredients and butter; mix until well blended.
Stir in nuts.

title: broccoli rice casserole
directions: In saucepan, melt butter and cook chopped onion.
Mix broccoli, rice, soup and onion.
Pour into greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Pour melted cheese over top.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: breakfast pizza
directions: Separate crescent dough into eight triangles and press into ungreased 12-inch pizza pan with points to the center, sides and bottom to form crust.
Seal all holes.
Spoon browned sausage over crust.
Sprinkle with potatoes and top with Cheddar cheese.
Pour egg mixture over all and sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Bake in 375° oven for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: heart healthy carrot cake
directions: Mix sugar, egg substitute, oil, buttermilk and vanilla.
Sift together flour, soda, cinnamon and salt, if desired.
Mix well with liquids.
Add pineapple, carrots, nuts and raisins.
Pour into greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan and bake at 325° for 55 minutes.

title: instant coffee
directions: Put water in pan and boil hard.

title: christmas breakfast dish
directions: In a large baking dish, combine ham, bread, cheese, flour, mustard and butter.
Mix together the eggs, milk and 2 sauces. Pour over bread mixture.
Chill in refrigerator overnight and bake Christmas morning at 350° for 75 minutes.

title: finger jello
directions: Pour boiling water and juice over jello and gelatin.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch pan and chill until firm.
Cut into squares. This can be eaten with fingers.

title: frozen fruit salad
directions: Drain juice from fruit and bring to a boil.
Dissolve jello in juice.
Mix fruit, milk and mayonnaise, add to jello mix. Refrigerate overnight.

title: potato casserole
directions: Even a day ahead, cook potatoes in salted water with a bay leaf added.
Store in refrigerator.
Skin and shred on a grater.
Put in greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Make sauce with the soup, sour cream, butter, onion, salt and pepper and cheese.
This will be thick, so spread it over the potatoes.
You can do this in the morning or the day before.
Cover with foil and refrigerate.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Sprinkle with crumbs and brown 5 to 10 minutes more.

title: bernice hagata's cowboy stew
directions: Saute onion, green pepper and garlic in small amount of cooking oil until tender.
Add ground beef; cook until well browned, breaking up with fork as it cooks.
Add tomatoes, salt, pepper and chili powder; cover and simmer 30 minutes.
Add kidney beans, potatoes and corn; simmer 15 more minutes.
Makes 8 servings.

title: crock-pot steak
directions: Cut the steak into thin strips.
Dredge in flour, salt and pepper, then combine steak and the rest of the ingredients in the crock-pot.
Cook on high for 1 hour, then cook on low for 8 hours. Serve over cooked rice.

title: christmas fudge
directions: In a very large pot or pan, combine butter, milk, vanilla, sugar and marshmallows.
Heat until boiling, then 2 minutes more. Marshmallows must be melted.
Remove from heat.
Add Baker's chocolate; stir until melted.
Add semi-sweet chocolate; stir until melted.
Add milk chocolate; stir until melted.
Immediately pour into two 13 x 9-inch pans, lined with wax paper, and place in refrigerator to cool.
Cut into small squares the same day.
Store in cool place or refrigerator.

title: rotel chicken casserole
directions: Melt margarine in large skillet.
Add chopped onion and bell pepper.
Cook until tender.
Add cheese (cut up) and stir until melted.
Add Ro-Tel, chicken and cooked spaghetti.
Stir really well.
Gently fold in English peas so that you don't smash them. Bake in oven at 350° for 30 minutes or until starts turning brown on top.

title: hamburger-squash casserole
directions: Cut squash into cubes, cook until tender; drain.
Brown ground beef in oil, drain.
Combine with squash and remaining ingredients, except cheese.
Spoon into a greased 2-quart casserole dish.
Sprinkle cheese on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: chicken gumbo
directions: Heat chicken, water, salt, garlic and bay leaf to boiling in Dutch oven; reduce heat.
Cover and simmer until chicken is done, about 45 minutes.
Remove chicken from broth; strain broth. Refrigerate chicken and broth.
When cool, remove chicken from bones.
Cut chicken into bite-size pieces.
Place broth and chicken in Dutch oven.
Stir in celery, onion, tomatoes, okra, corn, rice and Tabasco.
Break up tomatoes with fork.
Heat to boiling; reduce heat.
Cover and simmer until okra and rice are tender.
Garnish with parsley.

title: marinade for london broil
directions: Mix all ingredients except onion.
Layer half of the onion on bottom of shallow baking dish.
Place London broil cut, or flank steak on top.
Layer remaining onion slices on top of meat.
Pour marinade over all.
(It should cover half the thickness of meat.) Marinate 3 to 24 hours; turn meat halfway through time.
Grill meat and broil to taste.
Refrigerate leftover marinade to use again.

title: salmon cakes
directions: Empty salmon into large bowl.
Skin and remove bones from salmon.
In separate bowl, whip egg.
Pour into salmon and mix well.
Add enough corn meal mix to make consistent.
Cover spooned salmon lightly with corn meal mix.
Place into large skillet with hot vegetable oil.
Fry on medium to medium-high heat until brown on both sides.
Watch closely as it will burn easily. Be sure to keep plenty of oil in skillet at all times.

title: quicky-sticky buns
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
In small bowl, combine margarine, brown sugar and corn syrup.
Blend well.
Spread evenly in bottom of ungreased 8 or 9-inch round pan.
Sprinkle with walnuts.
Remove dough from can.
Separate into 8 coils.
Do not unroll breadsticks.

title: chicken crescent rolls
directions: Mix cream cheese and milk. Add chicken. Separate crescent rolls into 4 rectangles and seal perforations. Put 1/2 cup chicken mixture in center of each rectangle. Bring 4 corners of dough to center and seal. Bake on ungreased cookie sheet 20 to 25 minutes, until brown.

title: ritz biscuits
directions: Mix all together. Roll out like biscuits and cut.
Dip in melted butter and fold in half.
Brush butter on top.
Let rise 45 minutes.
Bake at 400° until brown.

title: bourbon roll
directions: Mix bourbon into milk; stir in all other ingredients.
Form into 4 rolls; roll in powdered sugar to coat.
Refrigerate; slice and serve.

title: aunt alice's shoo-fly cake
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients until crumbly.
Reserve 1 cup crumbs. Combine molasses, boiling water and baking soda.
Add to crumbs; pour batter in greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
Top with 1 cup reserved crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: anise toast(italian cookies)
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Grease and flour a loaf pan, 9 x 5 x 3-inch.
Beat eggs and sugar thoroughly.
Add anise seed. Gradually mix in flour.
Spread this stiff batter in prepared pan. Bake about 20 minutes or until toothpick stuck in center of loaf comes out clean.
Pan will be only 1/4 full.
Remove from pan and cut loaf into 16 (1/2-inch thick) slices.
Place slices on buttered baking sheet; bake 5 minutes or until bottoms of slices are browned.
Turn and bake 5 minutes more or until other sides are browned.
Cool and serve with ice cream, fruit or cheese. Makes 16 to 18 slices.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix the sausage and cheese together with hands. Add Bisquick and mix.

title: jello cake
directions: Mix and bake in tube pan for 1 hour at 350°, then take out of oven and pour 1 cup sugar and 1/2 cup of orange juice after the sugar and orange juice have boiled.
Let the cake set for about 1 hour, so this will soak through the cake.

title: mim's mess
directions: Place in a 2-quart casserole dish in order:
1 layer of potatoes, 1 layer of onions. Cover with green pepper.
Brown ground beef and drain.
Layer over other layers.
Layer grated cheese. Sprinkle with uncooked rice. Cover with tomato soup and can of water. Bake at 325° for 2 hours.

title: pound cake
directions: Cream sugar and Crisco.
Add 1 cup of flour at a time, alternately with 3 eggs at a time.
Blend well after each addition.
Add lemon and vanilla flavoring last.
Pour in tube pan.
Put in a cold oven at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: syllabub(an old english recipe)
directions: Whip the cream and confectioners sugar. Incorporate the remaining ingredients.
Serve in a frosted glass.

title: winifred's rosemary chicken
directions: Roll chicken legs in pan with oil.
Arrange legs and pour wine and Kitchen Bouquet mixture over legs.
Sprinkle with rosemary. Bake at 350°
for 1 hour, turning once during cooking time.

title: easy apple strudel
directions: In a large mixing bowl, cut margarine into flour as for pie dough.
Make a well in center and add egg yolks, water and vinegar; mix well.
Cover and refrigerate overnight or at least 6 hours.
Pare and slice apples.
Divide chilled dough into 3 equal parts.
On a lightly floured board, roll each out to a rectangle the thickness of pie crust.
Spread apple slices over 2/3 of each rectangle.
Sprinkle with sugar, cinnamon and graham cracker crumbs.
Roll up like a jelly roll with no apple slices inside the last turn.
Place on a lightly greased cookie sheet.
Brush tops with milk and sprinkle with additional sugar.

title: spinach lasagne
directions: Brown hamburger and drain.
Cook lasagne noodles according to package directions.
Cook spinach according to package instructions.
Pour small amount of sauce in an 8 x 12-inch baking dish/pan.

title: cherry nut dessert
directions: Bake crust 10 minutes at 350°.

title: cheesy potatoes
directions: Mix the first five ingredients together and pour into a rectangular casserole.
Top with the corn flakes.
Bake in a 350° oven for 45 minutes.

title: chocolate dream drops
directions: In a large bowl, mix oatmeal, peanut butter, coconut and nuts. In a saucepan, mix sugar, milk, cocoa and butter.
Bring to a boil and boil 1 minute.
Pour over dry mixture and mix well.
Drop by spoonful on wax paper.

title: cabbage rolls
directions: Cut out core of cabbage; run under cold water to separate each leaf.

title: instant brunswick stew
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix well.
Heat in crock-pot for 1 to 2 hours.

title: gourmet chicken chili
directions: Brown chicken chunks in oil in a large skillet.
Remove and set aside.
Saute onion and chopped red pepper.
Replace chicken. Add tomatoes, olives, jalapeno peppers, spices and beer.
Simmer about 30 minutes.

title: hot fudge sauce
directions: Combine sugar and cocoa with evaporated milk in saucepan over low heat.
Cook 15 to 20 minutes.
Stir occasionally.
Remove from heat.
Add vanilla.
Beat quickly until smooth.

title: fried pie crust
directions: Mix in order given by hand or mixer.
Put on floured board and knead until not sticky.
Pinch off in pieces the size of plums. Roll and cut by a saucer.
Place cold filling on half of circle and fold over.
Press edges together with fork.
Drop in hot oil and brown.
Makes 15 pies.
This recipe will serve 15 people.

title: beef rouladen
directions: Pound sirloin between 2 pieces of wax paper until thin.
Mix onion, pickles and bacon together in a small bowl.
Spread this mixture over each slice of sirloin to almost cover.
Leave about 1/2 to 1 inch on edges of each steak.
Roll each steak up into a long roll.
Tie a couple of pieces of thread around each roll to keep secure.
Brown steaks in a small amount of oil in frying pan. Remove steaks.
Add flour to oil and brown, making a light brown paste.
Add garlic salt, salt and pepper to taste to paste.
Add can of beef broth to paste.
Bring to a rolling boil; turn heat down to simmer.
Add steak rolls back to gravy; simmer about 12 to 15 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: orange biscuits
directions: Heat oven to 450°.
Stir ingredients until soft dough forms. Turn dough onto surface dusted with baking mix.
Knead 10 times. Roll 1/2 inch thick.
Cut with 2 inch cutter.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes or until golden brown.
Makes 7 biscuits.

title: fudge brownies
directions: Mix all ingredients in large bowl.
Beat 50 strokes by hand. Don't undermix.
Spread in greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 33 to 35 minutes.
Don't overbake.
Cool completely.
Store covered.

title: french onion soup
directions: Peel and slice onions thinly.
Heat butter in a large saucepan with a little sugar; add the onion rings and cook them very gently over a low flame, stirring constantly with a wooden spoon until the rings are an even golden brown.
Add the beef stock gradually, stirring constantly until the soup begins to boil.
Then lower the heat, cover the pan and simmer gently for about one hour.

Just before serving, add cognac, salt and pepper and serve in a heated soup tureen or in individual serving bowls, each one containing toasted buttered rounds of French bread heaped with grated Gruyere cheese.

title: baked beans
directions: Brown hamburg and onion; drain.
Add remaining ingredients. Bake at 350° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours in covered casserole.

title: gooey butter cake
directions: Mix cake mix, 2 eggs and margarine.
Spread in greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix cream cheese, 2 eggs and powdered sugar; spread on top of cake mixture.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: banana split cake
directions: Mix ingredients and press into 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Set aside.

title: spicy stir-fried shrimp
directions: In small bowl, mix chili sauce, soy sauce and sherry.
Cut green onions into 3-inch pieces.

title: sand tarts
directions: Roll thin, cut in diamonds so you do not have much to re-roll. Spread egg over top, then sugar and press nut into center of cookie.
Bake at 350°.
Start on bottom, then put up on top of oven; watch carefully.

title: corn meal griddle cakes
directions: Combine egg, milk and shortening; add flour mixed with salt and baking powder.
Then mix with corn meal.
Beat smooth and bake on ungreased griddle.
Makes 6 cakes.

title: zippy sweet-sour sauce
directions: Combine sugar and flour; gradually add pineapple juice. Heat. Moisten mustard with the water; add to mixture with vinegar and soy sauce. Bring to a boil. A delicious sauce to use with sausage balls or shrimp.

title: drop sugar cookies
directions: Mix in order listed.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto cookie sheet sprayed with Pam.
Bake at 400° until brown.
Makes 48.

title: fruit dip
directions: Combine softened cream cheese and marshmallow cream.
Mix until well blended.
Serve with fresh fruit and cookies as dippers.

title: chicken divan
directions: Boil chicken with onion, celery tops and salt.
Strip from bones.
Cook broccoli and drain.
Mix rest of ingredients to form sauce.
Grease a 2-quart casserole.
Put broccoli on bottom and bite-size meat on top.
Pour on sauce.
Sprinkle with 3/4 cup grated Cheddar cheese on top.
Sprinkle crumbs of Ritz crackers or bread crumbs.
Dot with butter.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.
Serves 6.

title: streetfield's strawberry pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together in a bowl.
Pour into baked pie crusts and refrigerate.
Garnish top with remaining strawberries.

title: never fail dinner rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in water, add sugar, salt and 3 cups flour, beat until smooth.
Add shortening and eggs and beat well again. Then stir in the rest of the flour or enough to make easily handled dough.
Knead well and place in greased bowl.
Cover and set in warm place.
Let rise until dough is doubled in size (2 hours or longer).
Shape into rolls and place in a well greased pan.
Cover and let rise until light (20 - 30 minutes).
Bake at 375 degrees for 25 minutes in a 9 x 13 inch pan.
Makes 2 1/2 to 3 dozen.

title: chicken salad
directions: Mix all ingredients and moisten with mayonnaise.

title: baked beans
directions: Drain beans.
Fry
bacon;
only use half of the grease. Put ketchup and
sugar	in bacon and stir good, then pour over beans and simmer	for
hours slow, or until ketchup is thick.

title: earthquake cake
directions: Mix cake according to package directions.
Spread nuts and coconut in bottom of greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Pour in cake mixture.
In bowl, mix cream cheese, sugar and margarine.
Dab on cake.
Do not spread!
Bake at 325° for 50 minutes.
Serve upside down.

title: devonshire splits
directions: Cut margarine into warm flour (leave out at room temperature overnight).
Add yeast creamed in a little milk and salt.
Mix to a soft dough with the flour mixture.
Knead well and return to bowl to rise in a warm place.
After rising, turn it over, knead again and roll out to 3/4 inch thickness.
Cut of pieces and roll into rounds.
Place onto lightly greased tin.
Leave to rise until the splits have doubled.
Bake in hot oven, 450°, for 10 to 15 minutes.
Serve with strawberry jam and cream.

title: oatsies
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Grease baking pan, 9 x 9 x 2-inch.

title: party mix
directions: Melt butter in large roaster pan.
Add garlic salt and Worcestershire sauce.
Add all cereal and nuts.
Mix well until all are coated with butter.
Bake 1 1/2 hours at 250°.
Stir every 15 minutes.

title: miniature cream cheese tart shells
directions: Soften cream cheese and butter.
Add the flour; mix well. (Dough should resemble slightly firm biscuit dough.) Refrigerate for 1 hour.

title: pecan logs
directions: Melt marshmallows and butter. Add graham crackers, milk and pecans. Roll into logs and refrigerate. Slice.

title: aunt mary's pound cake
directions: Combine dry ingredients and set aside.
In a large bowl cream shortening, butter and sugar.
Add flavoring and eggs; beat well. Add milk and dry ingredients.
Beat well.
Pour batter into a large greased and floured tube pan.
Place pan in cold oven (do not preheat).
Bake for 1 1/2 hours at 325°.
Let cool in pan for 30 minutes.

title: mashed potatoes
directions: Cook potatoes and onions until tender and drain.
Add butter, cream cheese, sour cream, egg, salt and pepper.
Beat well.
Place in greased casserole dish.
Dot with butter.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: tomato sauce
directions: Combine all ingredients in blender.
Blend to mix well.
Use this sauce to pour over pinto enchiladas.
Also good for other dishes.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients and bring to a boil. Let cool. Pour strawberries into crust. Pour filling over strawberries. Refrigerate.

title: orange julius
directions: Put all ingredients into blender.
Blend until ice cubes are crushed.
Serve in cold glasses.
May garnish with sprig of mint.

title: luscious and dreamy, frozen and creamy strawberry tart
directions: Combine yogurt and sugar.
Fold in whipped topping and sliced strawberries.
Fill tart shells with mixture and freeze at least 4 hours or overnight.
Remove from freezer 30 minutes prior to serving and garnish with sliced strawberries and a sprig of mint.

title: alex and garry's sopa de limon
directions: In a large nonreactive soup kettle, bring the stock, mint, allspice, peppercorns, cinnamon, cloves, cumin, garlic and onions to a boil.
Reduce the heat; simmer for 20 minutes.
Add the chicken breasts, cilantro, whole chili pepper and cut lemons; continue to simmer until the chicken is cooked, approximately 15 minutes.

title: tortilla roll-ups
directions: Combine sour cream, cream cheese, green chilies, lemon juice and cumin.
Spread mixture over each tortilla and refrigerate several hours or overnight.
Slice into 3/4-inch pieces and serve with picante sauce.

title: cheesy potato casserole
directions: Cook potatoes until tender, drain and put in a shallow baking dish.
Mix cream cheese, sour cream, Cheez Whiz, cream of mushroom soup and pepper together in a saucepan and heat until smooth, stirring constantly.
Pour hot mixture over potatoes and sprinkle bread crumbs on top.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: banana split cake
directions: First Layer:
Mix cracker crumbs and 1 stick oleo.
Press into bottom of 9 x 13-inch cake pan.

title: the best beans
directions: Saute onion in bacon grease. Drain beans and save juice.
Add to bean pot all ingredients except bean juice.
(Save and add as beans cook and need liquid.)
Add some of the bacon grease to bean pot for exceptional flavor.
Better if prepared a day or two ahead of time.

title: turtle cake
directions: Place cake mix, margarine and 1/2 cup milk into bowl and mix. Separate and place half into a greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
Set half aside.
Bake this at 350° for 7 minutes and set aside.
Place caramels and 1/2 cup milk into a pan and melt caramels.
Pour over baked cake mix.
Pour chocolate chips (do not melt) over caramels.
Pour nuts over chips.
Pour other half of cake mix over nuts.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Let set 12 hours at room temperature.

title: mexican wedding cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together. Bake in oblong pan 45 minutes at 350.

title: kidney bean salad
directions: Boil egg.
Drain kidney beans.
Mix kidney beans, mayonnaise and dill relish.
Cut up egg in mixture.
Mix again.
Serve cold.

title: strawberry mousse
directions: Pour boiling water into blender; add Jell-O and blend at low speed until dissolved.
Add ice cubes and stir until partially dissolved.
Add berries and Cool Whip.
Blend at high speed 30 seconds or until smooth.
Pour into mold or individual dishes. Should set in 30 minutes.

title: cheese grits casserole
directions: Bring water to boil; add salt and grits.
Cook until thick. Add Worcestershire sauce, margarine, Smokelle and bacon cheese to hot grits.
Stir to melt cheese.
Break eggs into cup; beat lightly.
Fill cup with milk.
Add to grits.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.
Five minutes before removing from oven, sprinkle 1/2 cup sharp Cheddar on top.
Return to oven until cheese melts.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix together first 7 ingredients and place into casserole dish. Cover with crushed cornflakes or crackers.
Dot with 2 tablespoons margarine.
Bake covered 45 minutes at 325°.

title: best barbecue sauce
directions: Mix together; use right away.
No cooking necessary.

title: swiss tea
directions: Remove boiling water from heat.
Add the rest of the ingredients.
Let set overnight.
Strain.
Keep in refrigerator.

title: dirt cake dessert
directions: Make pudding with milk; add Cool Whip.
Mix well and set aside. In another bowl, blend together well cream cheese, butter and confectioners sugar.
Blend the 2 mixtures together.
Layer crushed Oreos and pudding mixture in a child's plastic pail.
Leave about 1 cup of Oreos for the top.
Decorate top with gummy worms and plastic or silk flowers.
Refrigerate 8 hours or overnight.
Kids love it!
Enjoy.

title: swedish cabbage rolls
directions: Combine egg, salt, pepper, Worcestershire sauce, onion and milk in a bowl.
Mix well. Add beef, pork and rice.
Mix together.

title: cherry frozen salad
directions: *Can substitute strawberry pie filling for strawberry salad.

title: artichoke dip with mozzarella cheese
directions: Combine all ingredients in a large bowl.
Place into pie or quiche dish.
Sprinkle with Paprika and bake at 350 degrees for about 25 minutes or until brown & bubbly.

title: irish stew
directions: Cut meat into small pieces; coat with flour and brown in butter in fryer.
Add the rest of the ingredients.
Cover; put on medium heat for 3 minutes.
Then turn the heat to low and cook for 3 hours.

title: potato soup
directions: Cook first 8 ingredients for 15 minutes or until tender.
Add milk to flour until smooth.
Add to vegetables and heat until thick.
Add cheese.
(Omit flour if you prefer not so thick.)

title: fruit cobbler
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Put a 10-inch skillet in oven with butter to melt.
Mix flour, sugar, powdered milk, baking powder, salt and juice from fruit.
Pour into melted butter in a skillet. Pour fruit into center of skillet.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until golden brown around outside edge.
A great recipe for a Dutch oven.
Do not double this recipe!

title: easy party carrots and onions
directions: Cook beans and, while still hot, season with French dressing and finely chopped raw onion and mix well.

title: seafood cocktail
directions: Mix together the cream cheese, crabmeat, garlic powder and Worcestershire sauce.
Pack into lightly oiled small ring mold or rounded bowl.
Refrigerate until serving time.
Surround with crackers or lettuce.
Serve Cocktail Sauce.

title: carrot cake
directions: Mix together all ingredients except carrots and blend.
Add grated carrots to batter.
Bake for 45 minutes at 350°.
Use rectangular pan or two layer pans.

title: creamy corn pudding
directions: Blend all ingredients.
Pour into buttered 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes or until set.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: veal loaf with pistachios(serves 6)
directions: Preheat the oven to 375°.
Heat the olive oil in
a saucepan and add the scallions, onions and garlic.
Saute, stirring, for 5 minutes.
Place the veal and the onion mixture in a bowl.
Chop the liver very finely and add it to the mixture along with the bread crumbs, parsley and pepper.
Blend well.
Spoon the mixture into a 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan.
Cover the pan with foil and place it in the oven.
Bake for 1 hour.
Remove the foil and bake 15 minutes longer.

title: bean soup
directions: Put beans in a bowl and cover with water.
Let soak overnight. Dice ham hock.
Add ham, tomatoes, chili powder, lemon juice, sliced celery and sliced onion to water and bring to a boil.
Turn to simmer.
Add beans and pepper to taste.
Let simmer all afternoon.

title: banana brownie split pizza
directions: Prepare brownies according to box instructions and bake on parchment paper for 18 minutes. Then spread pineapple, sugar and cream cheese on cooled brownie. Top with everything else.

title: hong kong chicken
directions: Mix together;
put
in
bowl with chicken.
Marinate in refrigerator overnight (24 hours).
Bake at 350° for one hour, covered, then
minutes
or
so, uncovered.
Watch and turn often.
For 6 or 8 breasts I double recipe.

title: angel cookies
directions: Mix dry ingredients with creamed shortening, margarine, egg and vanilla.
Refrigerate until cool, 2 hours or so.
Can be rolled out for cut outs or pressed with a glass bottom sprinkled with sugar.
Bake at 375° until done.

title: cheese krispies
directions: Cream margarine and cheese together.
Add flour, mix well; add krispy rice cereal.
Knead together well.
Pinch off piece, make into small balls.
Place on cookie sheet, flatten with tines of fork.
Bake at 350° for 12 minutes.

title: applesauce fruitcake
directions: Line four 1-pound coffee cans with waxed paper.
(May use any pans which will hold 11 cups when filled 3/4 full.
Grease well if not lining with paper.)
Boil applesauce, shortening and sugar together for 5 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Let stand until cool.
Sift together the flour, soda and spices over the fruit and nuts, mixing until each piece is coated.
Stir in cooled applesauce mixture, then turn into cans.
Bake in preheated oven.
When browned, cover with brown paper; continue baking until wooden pick comes clean from center.
Remove from cans; cool on rack.
Store in moisture-proof wrapping in cool place or freeze in covered cans. Allow to mellow 2 weeks before cutting.
When ready to serve, bring to a boil 1/2 cup light corn syrup and 1/4 cup water.
Cool to lukewarm and pour over cold cake for shiny glaze.
Bake at 250° for 2 hours.

title: chocolate fudge
directions: Mix cocoa and sugar (small amount at a time). Add milk. When mixed well, place on low heat until dissolved, stirring lightly. Increase heat and cook until it forms soft ball in cold water. (It will begin to have a glazed look.) Stir a little to prevent sticking. Remove from heat and add butter. Beat until mixture thickens. Add pecans. Pour onto buttered pan. Cool completely and cut.

title: hawaiian beef with vegetables
directions: Pound meat and cut into thin strips, 2 to 3-inches long. Brown meat in oil.
Add onion, celery and pepper; cook for 3 minutes.
Add tomatoes, shoyu, sugar, garlic salt and flour and cook for 5 minutes.
Serve over cooked rice or cooked thin egg noodles.
Add enough soy sauce to rice or noodles to color them. Green onion slices or shallots may also be added, to taste.

title: marinated chicken
directions: Poke chicken with fork.
Put in shallow pan and pour Italian salad dressing over top.
Refrigerate overnight.
Best if cooked on the grill.
Just before taking off grill, brush with honey. Cut into strips and mix with steamed vegetables.

title: egg drop soup
directions: Mix cornstarch in well flavored cold stock in saucepan.
Bring to full boil.
Reduce heat and simmer until clear, stirring occasionally.
Gradually stir in eggs by holding cup high over pot, allowing egg to run off the tines of a fork in a watery stream.
Pour into bowls and serve with a generous squeeze of lemon.

title: fudge pudding
directions: Kids love to make this!

title: pound cake
directions: Mix together all ingredients.
Bake in tube pan at 350° for 45 to 55 minutes.

title: pineapple betty
directions: Cut thin slices of bread and butter, without the crust.
Lay some slices in the bottom of a dish, then put a layer of well-cleaned cherries or any preserved fruit, then more bread and butter and so on until the dish is nearly filled.
Mix a quart of milk, 4 well-beaten eggs
and 3 tablespoons rose water (sweetened with brown sugar to taste).
Pour over the bread and butter; let it soak for 2 or 3 hours before being baked.

title: jello paradise pudding
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water.
When cold and slightly thickened, beat with rotary egg beater until consistency of whipped cream.
Mix and add cherries, nuts, marshmallows, macaroons, sugar and salt.
Fold in whipped cream.
Turn into mold and chill until firm.
Serve in slices.

title: praline butter pecan pie
directions: Combine brown sugar, butter and pecans in saucepan.
Heat until butter melts.
Pour into pie shell.
Bake at 450° for 5 minutes.
Cool.
Blend milk and ice cream in mixer bowl.
Add pudding mix.
Beat at low speed for 1 minute or until blended. Pour into pie shell.
Chill for 3 hours or until set.

title: jalapeno soup
directions: In large saucepan, combine broth, celery, onion, garlic salt and white pepper.
Cook on high heat for 10 minutes until mixture reduces and thickens slightly.
In blender or food processor, place broth mixture, cheese and jalapenos.
Puree until mixture is smooth.
Return processed mixture to saucepan and simmer 5 minutes.
When ready to serve, place some sour cream in each bowl and add soup.

title: lasagne
directions: Cook lasagne until tender; drain.
In buttered casserole dish, layer 3 noodles in bottom.
Add cottage cheese, sausage, Muenster cheese and 3/4 of the spaghetti sauce.
Layer rest of noodles on top.
Sprinkle rest of cheese, spaghetti sauce and Parmesan cheese on top.
Bake in 375° oven for 45 minutes.

title: mother's fruit cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs.
Mix flour with baking soda, baking powder and spices.
Add alternately with cream to the creamed butter, sugar and egg mixture.
Fold in raisins, dates and walnuts.
Bake at 350° to 375° for approximately 10 minutes.

title: magic cookie bars
directions: In
a 9 x 13-inch pan, melt margarine.	Sprinkle crumbs over margarine.	Press to make a crust in bottom of pan.
Pour condensed
milk
evenly over crust.
Top evenly with remaining ingredients.
Press
down
firmly.	Bake for 30 to 35 minutes, until lightly browned.
Cool thoroughly before cutting.

title: beef noodle bake
directions: Cook ground round in a nonstick skillet until browned and crumbled. Drain and pat dry with paper towels.

Combine ground round and pasta sauce, stirring well. Set mixture aside. Cook egg noodles according to package directions. Drain. Combine cottage cheese and next 5 ingredients in a large bowl. Add noodles. Stir well. Spoon half of noodle mixture into a 13 x 9 x 2 baking dish coated with cooking spray. Top with half of beef mixture.
Repeat layers. Cover and bake at 350° for 40 minutes. Uncover and sprinkle with Cheddar shreds. Bake 10 additional minutes. Let stand 10 minutes before serving.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix sausage, grated cheese and biscuit mix together with hands.
Make into small balls.
Cook on cookie sheet for 15 minutes at 350°.
Reduce heat to 325° and cook 15 minutes more.

title: cheese garlic biscuits
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Combine Bisquick, milk and cheese until soft dough forms.
Beat vigorously for 30 seconds.
Drop dough by heaping tablespoonfuls on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes, until golden brown.

title: ham casserole
directions: Blend all ingredients. Bake at 300° until cheese is melted and bubbly.

title: punch
directions: Mix and freeze.
Thaw until slushy.
Add 1 quart of ginger ale when ready to serve.

title: ruby's pineapple cake
directions: Bake cake according to package directions using pineapple juice for liquid in cake mix; if needed, add water to make amount desired for liquid.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes at 350° in 9 x 13-inch pan (well-greased and floured).

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: Drain potatoes. Preheat oven to 350°. Spray large casserole dish with cooking spray; put in half the potatoes. Sprinkle dehydrated onions over potatoes, then sprinkle with salt and pepper. Add 1/2 stick of butter or margarine. Add the rest of the potatoes and sprinkle with more onions. Heat both cans of soup with milk. Pour over potatoes. Sprinkle with paprika. Bake for 1 hour.

title: cheesy potatoes
directions: Spread hash browns in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Sprinkle with onion, salt and pepper and mix.
Melt oleo and pour half over potatoes.
Reserve remaining oleo for topping.
Heat soup and cheese in a medium saucepan, stirring until cheese is melted.
Mix in sour cream and pour mixture over potatoes.
Combine crushed corn flakes and reserved oleo; mix well.
Sprinkle evenly over top of sour cream and cheese mixture.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: grandma's old-fashioned sugar cookies
directions: Cream sugar and lard well; add eggs, milk and cream.
Dissolve soda in a little hot water.
Sift flour, baking powder and salt and add to first mixture.
Chill a few hours or overnight.
Roll out and sprinkle with sugar.
Cut out with favorite cutters.
Bake at 375°
until nice and brown.
Yields 4 dozen.

title: sausage stuffing
directions: Saute green peppers, onions and celery.
Mix all ingredients together.
Season to taste.
Cook for 30 to 45 minutes at 350°.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook squash and onion until soft.
Drain well; add butter, salt, pepper and stuffing mix.
Mix well.
Put in greased baking dish; cover with bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: sweet potatoes
directions: Place sweet potatoes in heavy pan. Add sugar and cinnamon. Cook on top of stove until the juice cooks low, almost to no juice. Turn stove off. Add marshmallows. Put top back on pan so marshmallows will melt.

title: tiramasu
directions: Mix together egg yolks and sugar. Add Marscapone cheese and mix.
Add lemon rind. Fold in egg whites.
Separately combine Espresso and rum.
Lightly toast ladyfingers. Dip ladyfingers into Espresso and cover bottom of baking pan.
Cover with layer of cheese mixture.
Continue to layer cheese mixture and coffee dipped ladyfingers. Cover and put in refrigerator overnight. Garnish with cocoa powder.

title: corn fritters
directions: Mix corn, flour, egg yolks and salt together.
Whip egg whites and fold with corn mixture.
Drop by spoonfuls in hot oil in frying pan.
Brown both sides.
Drain on paper towel.

title: todd's baked beans
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Brown beef and drain.
Stir in next 5 ingredients.
Bake until bubbly in 13 x 9-inch pan.
Top with cheese.

title: chicken and macaroni
directions: Prepare elbow macaroni as label directs; drain.
Keep warm. Meanwhile, in 3-quart saucepan over medium heat, melt butter or margarine.
Add green pepper and celery and cook until vegetables are tender, stirring occasionally.
Stir in flour, salt and pepper until blended.
Gradually stir in milk.
Cook, stirring constantly, until sauce is slightly thickened.
Gently stir in chicken and Cheddar cheese just until cheese is melted.
Remove saucepan from heat.
Stir cooked macaroni into cheese mixture until well blended.
Makes 4 servings.

title: pork chops and rice
directions: Brown pork chops in deep skillet.
Add tomato juice, onion, green pepper, salt and rice.
Cook on high heat until steaming. Turn to low heat; simmer for 1 1/2 hours.

title: acapulco's refried beans
directions: In large skillet, heat bacon drippings and add flour. Stir until flour is browned.
Add mashed beans and seasoning. Simmer 5 to 10 minutes. If beans seem dry, add some bean broth to make beans creamy. Serve as side dish or filling for taquitos.

title: fresh peach slush
directions: Place peaches in blender container.
Puree until smooth.
Add ice cream and blend for 30 seconds.
Add milk, lemon juice and almond extract.
Blend until foamy.
Serve immediately in chilled glasses.
Makes 4 servings.

title: patio chicken
directions: Sprinkle raw rice evenly in bottom of 12 x 9-inch baking dish. Cover with dry onion soup mix.
Arrange chicken pieces on top. Combine soup, water and pepper; pour over chicken.
Add mushrooms. Cover.
Bake in a 350° oven for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.
Remove cover; brush with butter and bake 10 to 20 minutes longer until chicken is brown.

title: no bake orange balls
directions: Mix all ingredients; shape into balls.
Roll in additional confectioners sugar.
Store in covered container.
Makes 4 dozen.

title: applesauce cake
directions: Use less sugar when adding raisins or cherries.
May add chopped dates or walnuts.

title: good apple pie
directions: Heap apples in pie crust. Sprinkle sugar and cinnamon over apples. Dot with butter. Cover top with other crust and cut slits in top crust. Dot with butter, sprinkle sugar and cinnamon on top and bake at 350 degrees for about 45 minutes or until golden brown. Great served with vanilla ice cream or a slice of cheese on top.

title: rotel chicken
directions: Cook chicken.
Debone and cut up.
Saute pepper and onion with oleo.
Add cheese to melt.
Add tomatoes.
Boil noodles in chicken broth, drain.
Add chicken to noodles and mixture.
Stir and put in casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: date nut bread
directions: Grease pan.
Heat oven at 375°.
Stir all ingredients in except dates and nuts in pan with fork for 1 minute.
Add dates and nuts.
Bake 45 to 55 minutes.
When cake leaves the pan, it is done.
Remove from pan and cool.

title: cherry pudding
directions: Mix
ingredients
together; add cherries last.	Bake in 9-inch pan at 375° about 40 minutes. Serve with milk.

title: salmon artichoke casserole
directions: Drain salmon.
Remove skin and large bones.
Break in pieces. Saute artichokes in melted butter 5 minutes.
Place artichokes and salmon in casserole.
Mix sour cream, salt, pepper and Tabasco sauce.
Pour mixture over salmon.
Sprinkle with bread crumbs. Bake 30 minutes at 350°.
Sprinkle with parsley before serving. Serves 4 to 6.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Cream together the sugar and butter. Add eggs and bananas. Alternately add the buttermilk, flour and soda mixture.
Stir in pecans. Pour into greased and floured Bundt pan.
Bake at 325° until done.

title: doughnuts
directions: Put eggs, sugar, shortening and milk into bowl; mix well. Sift together remaining ingredients.
Add to first mixture; mix well.
Roll out 1/4-inch thick on floured board; cut with doughnut cutter.
Fry in deep fat at 390° until light brown, turning only once.
Makes 24.

title: ziti with hearty meat sauce
directions: In heavy 4-quart pan over medium heat, cook oil, butter, parsley, onion and carrot until tender.
Add meat and cook until meat loses its pink color.
Increase heat to medium-high.
Add milk and cook until it evaporates, stirring often.
Stir in tomatoes and juice; add spices.
Heat to boiling.
Reduce heat to low and simmer, uncovered, 1 1/2 hours.
Cook ziti al dente and drain.
Serve sauce over noodles.
(Good with green salad and French bread.)

title: honey glaze and sauce(for baked ham)
directions: Combine honey, juice, horseradish, cinnamon and nutmeg.
Brush on ham during last 30 minutes of baking.

Just before serving, combine remaining glaze with water and cornstarch in a saucepan. Remove ham from oven and add juice from ham pan to the saucepan. Stir constantly over medium heat until sauce thickens and cook for 2 minutes.

title: hush puppies
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Drop by spoon or roll in balls. Fry in hot canola oil.

title: easy chicken pie
directions: Cook and bone 1 hen or frying chicken.
Place in baking dish. Mix together and cook for 2 minutes:
1 cup chicken broth, 1 can cream of celery or cream of chicken soup.
Pour over chicken mixture and let stand 30 minutes.
Add salt and pepper to taste.

title: sweet potato cookies
directions: Mix butter and sugar together.
Add egg and dry ingredients and then pecans and raisins.
Drop by teaspoonfuls.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: angel biscuits
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Mix all other ingredients, together, then add yeast.
Roll out to cut like biscuits.
Bake at 450° until done.

title: ida's sphyngie
directions: Beat eggs and water until creamy.
Set aside.
Mix flour, sugar, salt and baking powder.
Add slowly to egg mixture.
In skillet, heat 2 cups oil until hot.
Drop batter mixture by spoonful into oil until brown.
Roll in sugar.

title: candy pudding
directions: Cook to 238 degrees. Stir cream and sugar and Karo well. Start on medium high heat until boil; then turn down. Cook on medium low heat without stirring. Have a marble slab 20x18 inches or 24x24 inch cold and buttered top. Cut up fine, red and green cherries and pecans. Pour boiling mixture on marble slab. When warm to the touch, work with greased butter paddle until thick and creamy. Add fruit and nuts, and work with hands until like dough. Shape and cool. Cover with semi-sweet chocolate.

title: corn casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together with spoon.
Bake in casserole dish at 375° to 400° for approximately 30 to 35 minutes or until done.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Butter 13 x 9-inch pan.
Pour in drained peaches.
Mix sugar and cinnamon together to taste.
Sprinkle over top of peaches. Add yellow cake mix as a top layer, then cover the cake mix with thin slices of butter.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° until brown and bubbly!
Delicious.

title: icebox pickles
directions: Mix cucumbers and onion.
Heat other ingredients to boiling. Let simmer for 5 minutes.
Then pour the liquid over the cucumber mixture and let set until cool.
Store in the refrigerator for 7 days before using.
Keep refrigerated.

title: pie dough
directions: Mix flour, shortening, sugar and salt together.
Mix 1 egg, water and vinegar together and add to flour mixture; roll out. Recipe can be frozen for later use.
It can also be refrigerated for a few days.

title: spaghetti salad
directions: Cook spaghetti until tender and rinse under cool water.
Add dressing and rest of ingredients.
Refrigerate.
Stir occasionally.

title: cheese garlic biscuits(served at red lobster restaurants)
directions: Combine vinegar, water, 1 cup of the sugar and 2 teaspoons of the cinnamon.
Stir over low heat until sugar dissolves.
Cook over medium heat for 20 minutes.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cook and debone chicken; put in bottom of casserole.
Melt oleo and combine with crackers.
Mix together other ingredients and put over the chicken.
Top with the oleo and cracker mix. Bake at 325° for 25 minutes.

title: amish sugar cookies
directions: Cream sugars, oleo and oil.
Add eggs; beat.
Add dry ingredients, then vanilla.
Chill in refrigerator overnight or few hours.
Roll into walnut size balls; press with fork on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake in 375° oven 10 to 12 minutes.
Sprinkle with sugar before baking.

title: corey's candied yams
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Open yams and drain.
Empty yams into a casserole dish.
Mash with a fork.
Sprinkle yams with brown sugar, then cover with mini marshmallows.
Cook for 20 minutes or until marshmallows brown.

title: chicken tetrazzini
directions: Saute the mushrooms and the butter with lemon juice. Toss them with the cooked spaghetti and chicken and place them in a 9 x 13 casserole. Set aside.

title: angel food apricot nectar cake
directions: Tear angel food cake into pieces and put into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cook until thick the apricot juice, cornstarch and sugar. Pour over cake and cool.
Spread large bowl of Cool Whip over cake when cool.
Refrigerate.

title: barbecued garlic
directions: Peel outer layers of garlic, leaving cloves and head intact. Place all heads on double thickness of foil.
Top with butter and herbs.
Fold up and seal.
Cook over hot coals, turning occasionally, 40 to 45 minutes.
Serve one whole head per person. Squeeze cooked cloves from skin onto cooked meat and vegetables or on French bread or rye bread.
Serves 8.

title: yum yum cookies
directions: Cream sugar, shortening and eggs.
Add rest of ingredients and mix well.
Let stand in refrigerator 2 1/2 hours.
Wet hands; roll dough into little balls and then in powdered sugar.
Place on cookie sheets.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: chicken and broccoli casserole
directions: Partially cook broccoli and put in bottom of casserole dish, 13 x 9 x 2-inch.
Put chicken on top.
Mix soup, water or broth and mayonnaise together and pour over broccoli and chicken.
Top with cheese and bread crumbs.
Cook for 30 minutes or until hot and bubbly at 350°.

title: chicken-green chili casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients and cover with grated cheese.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.
Serves 6.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients together until creamy.
Mix in dry ingredients.
Add vanilla, oatmeal and raisins.
Drop by teaspoon on an ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes. Makes 14 dozen cookies.

title: coconut dream cake
directions: Make cake like directions on cake mix box.
Mix cream of coconut and sweetened condensed milk together.
While cake is warm, punch holes in cake and pour the mixture in the holes.
When cake is completely cool, spread on Cool Whip and top with the frozen coconut.
Make it a day or two in advance and cover.
Keep in refrigerator.

title: banana dressing for fruit salads
directions: Mix ingredients in blender very quickly until smooth.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Heat all ingredients, except juice and Worcestershire sauce. Bring to a boil in saucepan.
Stir in juice and Worcestershire sauce.
Heat until hot. Makes 2 cups.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Cut unpared zucchini into bite-sized pieces. Lightly cook and drain.
Mix stuffing with margarine.
Mix all ingredients with half of stuffing mixture.
Put in casserole dish and top with half of stuffing mixture.
Bake 25 minutes or until brown and bubbly at 350°.

title: do nothing cake
directions: Mix well until blended.
Pour into pan.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: watermelon pickles
directions: Cut off rind and red meat.
Soak overnight in salt water. Soak overnight in clear water.
Then boil in strong ginger water after weighing.

title: for-get-me-not tea
directions: Mix and blend well all of the ingredients.
Use 2 tablespoons of mix to 8 ounces of hot or cold water.

title: banana split pie(low calorie)
directions: Combine cracker crumbs and margarine; pat into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Top with bananas.
Prepare pudding, using skim milk.
Fold in pineapple.
Pour over bananas.
Let pudding set.
Cover with light nondairy whipped topping.
Chill.
Add strawberries before serving.

title: fudgy bonbons
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In medium saucepan combine chocolate chips and butter.
Cook and stir over low heat until chips are melted and smooth.
Add condensed milk; mix well.
Lightly spoon flour into measuring cup; combine in medium bowl with nuts, vanilla and chocolate mixture.
Mix well.

title: punch
directions: Mix bananas and cherries in blender.
Add enough pineapple juice to remove from blender.
Mix sugar in large container.
Add frozen juices and banana mix.
Use one quart of mixture to 2 (32 ounce) ginger ales.

title: southern style pecan fudge
directions: In a medium saucepan, heat sugar, margarine, cocoa, milk, vanilla and salt over low heat.
Stir until smooth.
Stir in nuts. Spread mixture quickly in a buttered 9 x 5-inch loaf pan.
Cool; cut into squares.
Yield:
2 dozen.

title: pronto pizzas deluxe(serves six)
directions: Heat oil in heavy large skillet over medium-high heat.
Add leeks and bell pepper and saute until just tender, about 8 minutes.
Add crushed red pepper and stir 30 seconds.
Transfer to plate.
Add sausage to skillet and cook until no longer pink, crumbling with fork, about 4 minutes.
Transfer to another plate. (Can be prepared 1 day ahead; cover vegetables and sausage separately and chill.)
Preheat oven to 450°.
Place pizza crusts on pizza pans or baking sheets.
Spread 1/4 cup olive paste over each.
Top with cheese.
Divide sausage and vegetables between pizzas.
Bake until cheese melts, about 15 minutes.
Top with basil.

title: mexicali beans and franks
directions: Brown in skillet ground beef, onions and peppers; drain off meat drippings.
Add sausage, wieners and brown sugar.
Add chili powder, pork and beans, ketchup and mustard.
Cook over medium heat in skillet until simmering.
Sprinkle cheeses on top.
Reduce heat to simmer until cheeses melt.
Serve with salad and garlic bread. Makes great quick meal.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients (except cheese) together in a large bowl. Butter a casserole dish (11 x 15-inch or 9 x 13-inch).
Pour in ingredients.
Bake, covered, for 35 minutes in a 425° oven.
Bake, uncovered, for 15 minutes.
Sprinkle cheese on top 5 or 10 minutes before removing from oven.

title: chocolate surprise
directions: In a glass bowl, alternate one layer of chocolate chip cookies (break up by hand).
Add peaches, then a few chocolate chips. Sprinkle some chocolate syrup on top and top with Cool Whip.
Make three layers, ending with Cool Whip.
Make some peaks with a fork. Sprinkle some cookie crumbs and a few chocolate chips on top.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli and drain.
Add milk, mushroom soup, Bisquick and butter and mix.
Pour into pan and sprinkle cheese.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.

title: zucchini cake
directions: Mix altogether and bake in lightly greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan for 50 minutes at 350°.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Drain green beans and corn.
Combine green beans, corn, sour cream, peppers, onions, celery, celery soup, cheese, salt and pepper.
Pour into lightly greased 2-quart casserole dish.
Melt 1/2 stick margarine and combine with Ritz cracker crumbs. Sprinkle over casserole.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Serves 8.

title: white cookies
directions: Mix flour and oil together.
Mix sugar and eggs in a different bowl.
Add the yogurt, milk and baking powder in the sugar and eggs mixture and keep on mixing for awhile.
Put together the two mixtures.
Take a little piece in your hand and shape it like a small ball.
Put a nut on top of each cookie.
Cook in the oven 25 minutes at 350°, until golden.

title: party cheese balls
directions: Combine cream cheese and Cheddar cheese; mix until blended. Add all other ingredients, except nuts.
Chill cheese mixture for several hours.
Shape into a ball.
Roll in chopped nuts.

title: encore casserole
directions: Melt 1 tablespoon margarine in skillet and brown meat.
Add tomato sauce, salt, pepper and basil.
In a bowl, cream together the cheeses, sour cream, onions and green pepper.
Cook noodles with 2 tablespoons salt for 8 to 10 minutes.
Drain noodles and toss with melted butter.
Put half of noodles in bottom of a 9 x 13-inch buttered pan.
Cover with cheese mixture.
Top with other half of noodles.
Pour meat sauce over top.
Bake for 40 minutes at 375°.
Serves 8.

title: stuffed pork chops
directions: Have butcher cut a pocket on the bone side of each chop. Combine remaining ingredients and mix well.
Stuff each chop with this mixture.
Place in shallow greased pan and bake at 350° for about 1 hour or until tender.
Yield: 2 servings.

title: cranberry raspberry salad
directions: Dissolve raspberry and lemon gelatin in boiling water.
Stir in frozen raspberries, breaking up large pieces.
Break up cranberry sauce with fork.
Stir into gelatin mixture.
Chill until partially set.
Carefully pour in 7-Up beverage.
Chill until set and serve with whipped cream on top.

title: golden punch
directions: Mix jello with boiling water. Stir until well dissolved. Add sugar and stir well. Add pineapple juice, lemon juice and water. Refrigerate. Add ginger ale just before serving.

title: chicken piccata
directions: Remove skin from chicken.
On cutting board with meat mallet, pound each chicken breast into about 1/4-inch thick cutlets.
Mix bread crumbs and salt.
In separate bowl mix egg and milk.
Dip chicken into egg mixture, then into bread crumbs, coating both sides.
Over medium heat, melt butter.
Cook cutlets until tender and golden on both sides (5 minutes each side).
Remove from heat. Keep warm.

title: bailey's cream mousse
directions: Dissolve gelatin in water until soft.
Separate eggs, place yolks in mixing bowl.
Add Baileys, place over simmering water and stir until thick.
Do not overcook.
Remove from heat, add coffee extract and gelatin mix until dissolved.
Place bowl over large bowl of ice, stir until cool.
Beat whipping cream and 1/4 cup sugar until thickened.
Whip egg whites and 3 tablespoons sugar into soft peaks.
Gently fold whipping cream into cooled Baileys mixture, add egg whites and fold until blended.
Set up glasses, pipe Baileys cream mixture into glasses, filling 3/4 full.
Add ladyfingers and chocolate shards on top.

title: french dressing
directions: Put all in jar and shake well.	Good over lettuce wedges or any tossed salad.

title: moist pound cake
directions: Cream sugar, eggs, shortening and margarine.
Add sifted flour slowly.
Add milk, baking powder and vanilla (lemon or almond flavoring may be substituted).
Pour batter into greased pan. Bake for
1 1/2 hours at 350°; do not overbake.

title: perfection salad
directions: Put in small pan and boil the sugar, vinegar and water. Dissolve in Jell-O; add 1 cup cold water.
Add the following when Jell-O starts to thicken: crushed pineapple, celery, cabbage and carrots.
Pour into an 8 x 8-inch container.
Cover and refrigerate.

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: Cook chicken with skin in 2 inches of water.
Add salt and pepper.
Remove chicken from water and add spaghetti to water and boil until tender.
Add boned chicken, soup and chopped vegetables and cook 10 minutes.
Add more salt and pepper, if desired.
Add peas, most of cheese and cook until cheese melts.
Put in buttered casserole dish and top with remaining cheese.
Bake until cheese melts on top.

title: pasta primavera
directions: Cut ham into bite-size pieces.
Combine ham, vegetables, 2 tablespoons butter, basil and 1/8 teaspoon garlic powder in large skillet.
Heat on medium for 10 minutes, until vegetables are tender-crisp, stirring occasionally.
Toss noodles with remaining butter, garlic powder and sour cream.
Place noodles on serving platter.
Top with ham and vegetables.
Serves 4.

title: strawberry and spinach salad
directions: Rinse, drain and remove stems from spinach; tear into bite-size pieces.
Hull and slice strawberries.
Place spinach in bowl.
Top with sliced strawberries.
Place sugar in medium bowl. Add lemon juice; whisk until sugar dissolved.
Add yolk, whisking until dissolved completely.
Whisk 6 tablespoons (one at a time) into mixture.
Can be refrigerated until ready to use.
Rewhisk and pour over spinach/strawberries.
Gently mix.
Serve and enjoy.

title: marinated garden salad
directions: Cut up vegetables into bite sized pieces.
Slice onion thin. Mix with the dressing.

title: vanilla ice cream
directions: Mix in a 1-gallon freezer. Use ice cubes and 1 pound table salt. It freezes in about 1 hour in an electric freezer.

title: amazing no-bake granola bars
directions: Stir together oats, rice cereal, and raisins.
In a large saucepan, combine corn syrup and brown sugar.
Heat just until boiling; remove from heat and immediately stir in peanut butter and vanilla.
Add dry ingredients; stir in chocolate chips.
Pat into a large greased cookie sheet and let cool.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Put chicken in baking dish.
Mix soups and sour cream together and pour over chicken.
Melt 1 stick of margarine with crumbled crackers.
Put on top of soup.
Bake 30 minutes at 350° or until mixture bubbles.

title: *sour cream chocolate cake
directions: Melt chocolate in water over low heat; blend.
Cool thoroughly.
Sift flour, baking powder, soda and salt.
Mix sour cream into cooled chocolate.
Cream butter and sugars well.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Beat in vanilla.
Add flour and chocolate mixture alternately, mixing well.

title: harold's sugarless cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cook raisins in 2 cups of water until all the water is gone.
Chop bananas and set aside with raisins. Mix remaining ingredients with a spoon.
When well mixed, add raisins and bananas.
Bake in a greased and floured 9-inch round or square cake pan for 1 hour at 350°.

title: pistachio banana bread
directions: Line 2 loaf pans with wax paper and grease the sides and the paper or spray with cooking spray.
In a large bowl, combine the dry ingredients and mix until well blended.
Pour the batter into the prepared pans.
Bake in a 350° oven for 50 to 60 minutes. Makes 2 loaves.

title: spiced tea mix
directions: Mix together and store in airtight container.

title: burgers italiano
directions: In a 10-inch skillet, heat dressing.
Add vegetables and cook, covered.
Over medium heat, stirring occasionally, 7 minutes or until vegetables are tender.

title: jeanette's pimento and cheese special
directions: Mix first four ingredients together well.
Add Tabasco to taste.
Served with crackers, makes a great snack.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Saute bacon and onion, drain most of grease.
Mix everything together in big bowl.
Pour in an 8 x 8-inch baking dish.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.
Sprinkle with cheese, then put back in oven for 5 minutes.

title: cabbage casserole
directions: Grate cabbage and cook until wilted.
Brown ground beef; add rice.
Mix together the soup, water and tomato sauce.
Spread beef and rice over cabbage and add tomato mixture on top.
Cover and bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: gazpacho
directions: Combine garlic, sugar, salt, tomato juice, oil, lemon juice and Worcestershire in large bowl.
Beat until well blended.
Stir in tomatoes, cucumber, green pepper, carrots, celery and green onions.
Cover and chill for several days.

title: coffee flavored liqueur
directions: Combine water and sugars in saucepan.
Bring to boil and simmer 10 minutes.
Add instant coffee to sugar mixture and let cool. When cool, add vodka and vanilla.
Pour into bottles and store in cool place.
Makes about 2 quarts.

title: squash hush puppies
directions: Mix all ingredients and drop by tablespoons into hot oil.
Fry until golden brown.
Drain on paper towels.

title: cornbread salad
directions: Bake cornbread.
Cook.
Crumble and chill.
Chop all vegetables and put in covered bowl.
Chill 2 to 3 hours.
Thirty minutes before serving, mix cornbread and vegetables.
Chill for 20 minutes.
Add dressing and toss lightly 10 minutes before serving.

title: pumpkin pudding
directions: Combine sugar and butter; mix well.
Add eggs one at a time, beating after each addition.
Stir in flour and milk, add pumpkin and cinnamon.
Mix until smooth.
Stir in 1 cup coconut and pecans.
Pour into greased 2-quart casserole.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 5 minutes.
To serve, add whipped cream and cherry or toasted coconut.

title: dill pickle slices
directions: Drain pickles on paper towels.
Take cream cheese and spread on bread.
Take 1 slice of trimmed bread, place 1 dill pickle and wrap a little more than half.
Roll up in wax paper.
Chill and slice.

title: pepper jelly
directions: Mix sugar, green and hot pepper and vinegar; bring to boil and boil 1 minute.
Add Certo and let set for 15 minutes.
Put in jars and seal.

title: cheese cake
directions: Combine cake mix, 1 egg and butter.
Mix together and line pan like a pie crust on sides and bottom.

title: minted pears
directions: Bring sugar and water to a boil for 5 minutes.
Add mint flavoring and a generous 2 or 3 shakes of the green food coloring; mix well.
Add about 9 pears which have been peeled, halved and cored.
Return to boil and cook about 5 minutes, depending on variety and ripeness of pears.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Mix together and bake in 2 loaf pans at 350° for 45 minutes or until done.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Beat eggs in a large bowl.
Stir in oil, sugars, zucchini and vanilla.
Sift flour, baking powder, soda and cinnamon.
Stir into egg mixture.
Stir in raisins.
Spoon into two well-greased loaf pans.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour (until center springs back when touched).
Cool in pans 10 minutes.
Remove and cool. Freezes well.

title: hot dill pickles
directions: Slice
cucumbers in quart jars.
Add hot peppers, dill, garlic and alum.
Pack tightly in jars.

title: green bean casserole
directions: In 1 1/2 qt. Casserole dish, mix soup, milk and pepper. Stir in beans and 2/3 c. fried onions. Bake 25 minutes at 350 degrees until hot. Stir; top with 2/3 cup onions. Bake 5 minutes until onions are golden brown. Makes 6 servings.

title: oven chicken thighs with onions and potatoes
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Slice onions and potatoes. Alternate layers in casserole dish with onions at bottom (first layer). Salt, pepper and season after each potato layer. Chop up garlic and place under the skin of chicken (so that garlic is between skin and chicken). Place chicken on top layer. Salt, pepper and season. Place in oven, covered with foil, for 45 minutes. Take off foil and bake 30 minutes more or until chicken is brown.

title: fancy biscuits
directions: Melt oleo and add all dry ingredients; let stand for 30 minutes.
Cut biscuits in half; dip in mixture.
Bake as directed.

title: ding bats
directions: Combine dates, sugar, butter and egg; stir. Add water. Cook for 10 minutes. Add Rice Krispies, vanilla and nuts. Cool and drop from a teaspoon into bowl of coconut; roll into small balls. Store in airtight container. Will keep for weeks. Very pretty for special occasions when the coconut is tinted.

title: jamie's blueberry salad
directions: Dissolve Jello in water.
Add pineapple and pie filling. Pour into a 9x13x2 inch dish.
Chill until firm.

title: macaroni salad
directions: Cook macaroni; drain.
While still hot, drizzle with oil and vinegar.
Add
onion,
seasonings
and
cheese; toss well. Gently mix in Spam and remaining ingredients.
Chill.
Serve on salad greens.

title: apple raisin bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Spray an 8 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan with vegetable spray.
In large bowl, sift flour, baking soda, baking powder and sugar.
Add whole wheat flour, wheat germ, cinnamon and allspice and set aside.
In another large bowl, mix egg whites, water and apple juice concentrate.
Mix in flour mixture.
Pour mixture into pan.
Bake 50 to 60 minutes or until a toothpick inserted in the middle comes out clean.
Makes 12 (1 slice) servings.

title: toasted cornbread
directions: Cut left-over cornbread into serving-size pieces.
Split each piece through the middle.
Lay cut-side down in medium hot iron skillet with melted butter.
Toast until brown and crisp, about 5 minutes.
Turn and toast other side 1 to 2 minutes.
Serve hot.

title: stuffed peppers
directions: Mix together all ingredients except green pepper and tomato sauce.
Cut the tops out of the green peppers and clean the insides of the peppers.
Fill peppers with the ground beef mixture.
Cover the tops of the peppers with tomato sauce and bake at 325 degrees for approximately one hour, or until meat is cooked through.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Save enough onion rings to cover top of casserole. Grease casserole dish with margarine, then spread 1 can mushroom soup, then 1/2 of remaining onions, 1/2 of liquid reserved from beans and 1/2 cheese. Repeat. Bake at 375° for 40 minutes. Remove from oven. Crumble remaining onions on top. Return to oven and brown.

title: tomato soup cake
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Set aside.
Blend sugar, shortening and eggs.
Add tomato soup and milk.
Bake at 375° for 40 minutes in a greased 9 x 9-inch pan.
Frost with Cream Cheese Frosting.

title: cold zucchini soup
directions: Brown coarsely chopped onion in butter.
Add sliced zucchini, broth and water; simmer until tender.
Cool.
Puree in blender with cream and seasoning for several minutes.
Refrigerate.
Add parsley for garnish.

title: chicken in swiss cheese sauce
directions: Place boneless chicken breasts in baking dish.
Cover with white sauce.
Sprinkle with oregano, salt and pepper.
Bake covered 1 hour at 300°.
Remove from oven and add 1 slice Swiss cheese on each breast.
Place dressing which has been prepared over each breast.
Bake 1 hour more.
Last half hour uncover and turn oven down to 250°.
Serve with white and wild rice, mixed.

title: fancy cheez-its
directions: Put a dab of peanut butter between two crackers. Melt white chocolate in a double boiler. Dip cracker in chocolate and let cool on wax paper. (Will freeze.)

title: poached shrimp(microwave)
directions: Place shrimp on outer edge of serving dish, leaving center open.
Mix garlic, onion, celery seed, bay leaf and lemon juice. Then spoon over shrimp.
Cover tightly with plastic wrap.
Cook 2 1/2 minutes on High. Turn shrimp over after 1 1/2 minutes.
Shrimp can be chilled or served warmed.

title: "mom" denler's sugar cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar. Add egg and vanilla and beat well. Add sour cream and flour, a little at a time, and beat until it gets thick, then mix rest of flour in well.
Dough will be sticky and soft.
Put on wax paper and dip hand in flour and shape into ball.
Chill overnight.
Cut dough in half after it has warmed up a little.
Roll out about 1/4 to 1/2-inch thick and cut round cookies and place on ungreased cookie sheet. Sprinkle granulated sugar on top and roll lightly with rolling pin to pat down.
Bake at 375° for six to eight minutes.
Do not let them brown.

title: caramel layer chocolate squares
directions: Stir cake mix, butter, nuts and evaporated milk.
Press 1/2 of dough into greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 6 minutes.
Sprinkle on chocolate chips.
Pour caramel mixture over chips.
Crumble rest of dough over top.
Bake 20 minutes more.
Cool in fridge for 30 minutes.
Cut into squares.

title: keebler krumblies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cover cookie sheet with aluminum foil. Bring butter, margarine and sugar to a boil.
Boil two minutes. Line cookie sheet with graham crackers.
Pour butter/sugar/margarine mixture over crackers.
Sprinkle with nuts. Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes or until bubbling good.
Cool and break into pieces.

title: chicken scallopini
directions: Pound chicken breasts thin.
Dip chicken into beaten egg, then into seasoned bread crumbs.
Heat oil with garlic and remove garlic.
Brown chicken in oil for 3 minutes on each side over medium heat.
Add sherry, basil and lemon juice.
Top with capers. Simmer 5 to 6 minutes or until tender.
Makes 4 servings.

title: baked quail
directions: Split whole quail down back only.
Salt and pepper birds and stuff with favorite cornbread, giblet or rice dressing.
Wrap a strip of bacon around each bird and sprinkle with Worcestershire sauce.
Bake in 350° oven and baste frequently with bouillon. Cook 1 hour and 45 minutes to 2 hours.

title: broiled chicken breasts(heart healthy)
directions: Place chicken breasts in a bowl.
Combine remaining ingredients and pour over chicken.
Marinate at least 2 hours.
Place breasts on broiler pan and broil close to heat for 5 minutes on each side. Yield:
8 servings.

title: caramel icing
directions: Boil for 1 minute and let cool slightly.
Mix in 3 cups confectioners sugar.

title: one pan bars
directions: Melt margarine in a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Sprinkle next five ingredients over margarine.
Drizzle Eagle Brand milk over all. Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: chocolate pizza
directions: Melt chocolate chips with 14 ounces of almond bark over low heat, stirring until smooth.
Remove from heat.
Use a large pan. Stir in marshmallows, cereal and peanuts.
Pour onto greased 12-inch pizza pan.
Top with cherries.
Sprinkle with coconut. Melt remaining 2 ounces almond bark with oil over low heat, stirring until smooth.
Preparation Time: 15 minutes plus chilling.
Smaller pizzas 4 (6-inch) and 12 (4-inch).

title: yummy potatoes
directions: Prepare and cook broccoli. Place the oil, butter or margarine in a saucepan. Add broccoli. Cook and stir until broccoli is delicate brown. Sprinkle with the Parmesan cheese.

title: dump cake
directions: Dump the crushed pineapple into a 9 x 13-inch ungreased cake pan and spread evenly.
Dump the pie filling and spread evenly. Dump the yellow cake mix (dry, do not add anything) over the pie filling and spread evenly.
Spread nuts over dry cake mix.
Slice 2 sticks of butter into pats and place on top of nuts.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: orange dessert
directions: Drain pineapple and oranges.
Do not use liquid.
Combine all ingredients and chill.

title: acorn squash with cranberry filling
directions: Cut squash in half; remove seeds, butter cut surfaces and bake in a 400° oven, cut side down, for 30 minutes.
Turn squash, cut side up; season lightly with salt and pepper.

title: heavenly shrimp
directions: Blend all ingredients and chill for at least 1 hour before serving.
Serve with chips or crackers.
Makes 1 2/3 cups.
Recipe may be doubled.

title: breakfast sausage gravy and biscuits
directions: Cook sausage thoroughly in a 10-inch skillet with sage.
Drain grease and set aside.
In a separate 1-quart saucepan, add 1 cup of milk and 1 cup of water.
To this, add all spices and heat, but do not boil.

title: medley of vegetables
directions: Mix together all ingredients in large bowl.
Pour into casserole dish. Bake in moderate oven at 350° for at least 1 hour. Yields 3 quarts.

title: banana muffins
directions: In a bowl, combine flour, sugar, baking powder, baking soda and salt. In another bowl, combine the egg, butter and bananas, then stir into dry ingredients just until moistened. Fold in chips. Fill greased or paper-lined muffin tins 3/4 full. Bake in 375° oven for 18 to 20 minutes. Let cool for 5 to 7 minutes before removing from pan.

title: buttermilk cake
directions: Sift flour, soda and salt together.
Cream butter and sugar until light and fluffy.
Add egg yolks and beat until very light. Add vanilla and lemon extract, blending well.
Add dry ingredients alternately with combined buttermilk and vinegar.
Beat until batter is smooth.
Fold in stiffly beaten egg whites.
Pour into 2 greased 8-inch cake pans.
Bake at 375° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: dried beef dip
directions: Add mayo or milk to the cream cheese until it becomes the creamy consistency of a dip.
Add the dried beef (chopped into tiny pieces), onion and horseradish.
(Increase or decrease onion/horseradish according to your taste.)
Mix together.

title: lemon loaf
directions: Cream 1 cup sugar and butter.
Add eggs and 1 grated lemon rind.
Sprinkle salt and baking powder over mixture.
Then add alternately in small amounts of flour and milk.
Mix each addition by hand.
Stir in cherries.
Bake in greased loaf pan at 350° (325° if pan is glass) for 45 minutes to 1 hour.
Test with toothpick for doneness.
Remove and poke with fork and pour juice of 1 lemon with 1/3 cup sugar over loaf.

title: sweet onion crappie pie
directions: Mix cracker crumbs with melted butter and press into an 8-inch pie plate.
Saute onions in 2 tablespoons of butter over medium heat until lightly brown.
Pour in the chicken stock and stir.
Put onions into cracker pie crust.
Place fillets over the onions. Beat eggs with milk, salt and pepper.
Pour over crappie.
Sprinkle paprika, then cheese over fillets.
Bake at 350° for at least 30 minutes.
Sprinkle with parsley (optional) when fillets are cooked. Cool for 10 minutes.
Serves 4 to 6 people.

title: blackened fish spice mix
directions: Use 1/2-inch fillets of redfish, golden tile, snapper or grouper.
Heat cast-iron skillet until white hot.
Coat fish fillets with melted butter and sprinkle with spice mix until well coated on each side.
This recipe makes about 1 cup and will keep very well in sealed container.

title: cheese balls
directions: Mix all together and roll into round of pecans.
Chill for several hours.

title: fruit pizza
directions: Cut cookie dough into slices and pat into pizza pan.
Bake 20 minutes at temperature given on cookie package.
Blend 8 ounces cream cheese with powdered sugar.
Put cheese mixture on top of baked dough.
Add fruits of choice (peaches, pineapple, apples, strawberries, kiwi, cherries, raisins, nuts, etc.).
Glaze fruit with preserves and chill.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Layer tortilla chips, mixture of beef, onion, garlic salt, tomato sauce, olives, mixture of sour cream, cottage cheese, chilies, tortilla chips and Monterey Jack cheese.
Repeat the 5 layers again.
Bake at 375° for 35 minutes.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Brown sausage over medium heat.
Stir occasionally.
Drain well.
Spread bread cubes into large buttered casserole dish.
Top with sausage and cheese.
Combine eggs, milk and seasonings.
Mix well and pour over cheese.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes or until set.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: chili
directions: Brown hamburger, sausage and onion; add other ingredients and simmer.

title: banana breakfast bars(serves 12 to 16)
directions: Grease a 9 x 13-inch pan. Cream sugar, margarine and egg.
Mix well.
Add salt and cinnamon.
Mix well.
Add flour and the rest of the ingredients. Mix well.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes. Cool completely before cutting. They can be frozen.

title: easy lemon chess pie
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients in a medium bowl, stirring well. Add oleo, milk and lemon juice; mix well.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after addition.
Pour filling into 9-inch unbaked pie shell. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes. Cool and chill before serving.

title: icebox cake
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Mix until all ingredients are moist with milk. Spoon and pack into loaf pans. Cover with aluminum foil.
Let set in refrigerator for 24 hours before eating. This recipe makes 2 cakes. Will keep in refrigerator for 2 to 3 weeks.

title: cabbage salad
directions: Slice cabbage long but not fine.
Also, slice peppers and onions in rings.
Mix together.
Mix and heat the following to boiling and pour over the cabbage mixture:
