sugar, celery seed, pepper, white vinegar, salt and mustard seed.
Cover and store in refrigerator.
This will keep a long time.

title: no meat pizza hors d'oeuvres
directions: Mix all ingredients in large bowl.
Slice bread in thin slices.
Spread with mix.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes at 425°.
May be made ahead and frozen.

title: bimbo bill's barbecue bash sauce
directions: Put all ingredients in saucepan.
Boil for 5 minutes.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Mix soup and milk together.
Cook broccoli according to package directions; drain slightly.
Layer: broccoli, soup mixture and cheese or mix everything together.
Bake at 350° until bubbly and cheese melts.

title: orange julius
directions: Blend in blender. Top with drop of Cool Whip or whipped cream. Serve immediately.

title: mexican pizza
directions: Toast tortillas under broiler briefly until slightly crisp, but not brown.
Spread tortillas with salsa.
Sprinkle cheese over top.
Broil under broiler until cheese is melted.
Sprinkle with chopped cilantro.
You may add your favorite precooked toppings.

title: french cheese puffs with ham
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Bring water, butter and salt to a boil in medium saucepan.
Remove from heat and add flour all at once beating vigorously until dough is blended and begins to come away from sides of pan, forming a ball.
Stir in ham and cheese.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each.
Drop by heaping teaspoonfuls, 2-inches apart on cookie sheet.
Bake until puffed and golden, 15 to 20 minutes.

title: apricot salad
directions: Mix jello, sugar and water until boiling.
Add cream cheese and beat 2 to 4 minutes until well blended.
Let stand 10 to 15 minutes until slightly thick.
Add baby food, pineapple and nuts. Fold in Cool Whip.
Pour into large mold.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: chocolate cherry cake
directions: Combine ingredients in a large bowl.
Stir until well blended. Pour into a greased and floured 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes or until done.
Can be served with Cool Whip or put chocolate frosting on it.

title: ham and cheese rolls
directions: Slice rolls in halves; put ham and cheese on them and replace the top. Bring margarine, mustard and Worcestershire sauce to a boil. Pour over top of rolls; cover with foil and put in a warm oven for about 20 minutes.

title: pistachio salad
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Chill and serve.
Marshmallows can be increased or decreased.
Pecans can also be added.

title: perfect brownies
directions: Melt chocolate over hot water.
Cream the butter and sugar. Add eggs and beat well.
Blend in chocolate, vanilla and flour. Mix nuts into batter.
Bake in greased 9 x 13 1/2-inch pan at 325° for 35 minutes.

title: puddin' cake and dip
directions: Dissolve sugar by heating, but do not boil.
Pour over the puddin' cake.

title: fresh peach pie
directions: Mix oil and milk together and add salt, sugar and flour.
Pack into 9 or 10-inch pie pan.
Bake at 400° for 10 to 12 minutes; prick crust where sides meet bottom before baking.
Cool.
Cook until clear (5 minutes) sugar, water and cornstarch.
Add peach Jell-O and stir until dissolved.
Cool.
Line bottom of cooled crust with peach slices, alternating in crust with cooled Jell-O mixture, making sure all peaches are covered.
Set at least 6 hours in refrigerator.
Serve with Cool Whip.

title: potato puffs
directions: Combine all ingredients except oil in bowl; mix well.
Drop by teaspoonfuls into sizzling, hot oil in skillet.
Brown on both sides.
Drain on paper towels.
Serve hot.

title: parmesan duck breast
directions: Heat oil in skillet.
Dip pieces of duck breast in beaten egg and roll in Parmesan cheese.
Fry in hot oil.

title: round steak casserole
directions: Take first 2 ingredients and brown the round steak.
Then cut it into 1-inch squares.
Put meat on bottom of pan.
On top of that, put a layer of onion, then a layer of potatoes.
Then mix the mushroom soup and milk. Put over casserole.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Drain green beans, then put them over the top and bake for another 15 minutes.

title: french dressing supreme
directions: Put all together in top of double boiler over boiling water (or in heavy saucepan) over low heat (flame!).
Stir well.
Feel with finger to see that mixture gets no more than blood warm!
Will not thicken if it gets too warm.
When "blood warm", same temperature as finger, take off fire (heat) and beat with rotary beater until thick.
Keep in refrigerator and shake well before using.
Makes 3 1/2 cups.

title: chicken tarragon
directions: Saute chicken on both sides in olive oil, butter and garlic. Add 1/4 cup of chicken broth (set aside remaining for later).
Let simmer until almost all liquid is evaporated.
Add white wine.
Let simmer until almost all liquid evaporates.
Add tarragon.
Turn chicken and bake.
Add last 1/4 cup chicken broth, cover and let cook on low heat for approximately 20 minutes.

title: 3 minute coconut pie
directions: Stir all ingredients together. Pour into pie shell and bake for 40 minutes at 325 degrees.
Good Pie!!

title: pickled salad
directions: Pour over vegetables and refrigerate.
This keeps several days in the refrigerator.

title: english pea casserole
directions: Saute onions in butter. Add pepper. Cook 5 minutes. Add flour until blended. Slowly add half and half. Cook 1 minute. Add peas with onions. Add salt and nutmeg. Heat until warm.

title: vanilla wafer cake
directions: Cream the margarine and sugar. Add the eggs, one at a time, milk, vanilla wafers, baking powder, vanilla flavoring, coconut and pecans. Bake in oblong pan 30 to 35 minutes at 350°.

title: sweet popcorn
directions: Melt almond bark in microwave bowl. Add popcorn and coat.

title: sweet and sour pork
directions: Brown meat in small amount of oil; season.
Stir in combined barbecue sauce, pineapple syrup, vinegar and cornstarch.
Cover; simmer for 35 minutes.
Add pineapple and green pepper; simmer 10 minutes longer.
Serve with rice.
Serves 6.

title: pineapple salad
directions: In saucepan, heat to boiling the pineapple and sugar.
Add jello and stir until melted.
Remove from heat.
Add softened cream cheese, a little at a time, and stir until most of the lumps disappear.
In large bowl, beat evaporated milk.
Fold cooled mixture into this.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch cake pan and refrigerate several hours.

title: mandarin orange cake
directions: Mix in order.
Bake in 3 round cake pans.
Follow baking directions on box.
Let cool before icing.

title: scalloped corn
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Grease 1-quart casserole.
Saute onion and green pepper into oleo until tender.
Remove from heat.
Stir in rest of ingredients.
Pour into casserole.
Bake at 375° for 35 to 40 minutes or until set.
Makes 6 (1/2 cup) servings.

title: greek butter cookies(covlovrakia)
directions: Cream butter until light and creamy.
Add sugar and beat well in separate bowl.
Combine soda and orange juice; be careful, mixture may overflow.
Add to creamed mixture.
Pour in brandy and beat well.
Gradually add flour; mix in thoroughly.
Shape as desired into braided twist or wreath.
Brush lightly with beaten egg.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes.
Makes 12 dozen.

title: cukes in vinaigrette dressing
directions: Peel and slice cucumber (thick or thin slices depending on your taste). Cover with water and stir in salt. Refrigerate for at least 30 minutes. Then drain and thoroughly rinse. Add sugar, vinegar and onions (if desired). Mix well. Add water, a little at a time, until dressing is at desired strength. (The less water you add, the stronger the vinaigrette.)

title: baked beans
directions: Mix and stir with bacon.
Bake in a greased casserole at 300° for 2 hours.
Don't cover.

title: strawberry bread
directions: Sift together first 5 ingredients in large bowl.
Combine and mix well the eggs, strawberries, nuts and vegetable oil.
Make a well in dry ingredients.
Add liquid ingredients.
Mix just enough to moisten.
Pour into greased pans and bake at 350° for 40 minutes for small pans or 1 hour for large loaves until done.

title: chocolate breeze
directions: First Layer:
Mix flour and butter; stir in nuts.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes in 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Cool.

title: play doh
directions: Mix together flour, alum and salt.
Mix oil with a few drops of food coloring.
Add to dry ingredients.
Add water slowly, working in only as much as needed to make dough.
Store in airtight container.
Makes 1 pint.

title: pudding cake
directions: Line pan with graham crackers.

Mix 2 boxes of instant vanilla pudding and 3 cups of milk; stir in 1 large carton of Cool Whip. Spoon half of pudding and Cool Whip mixture onto graham crackers. Put on another layer of graham crackers.
Spoon on rest of pudding mixture.
Put on another layer of graham crackers.
Ice with chocolate icing, mixed with cream cheese.

title: caramel corn
directions: Combine brown sugar, margarine, syrup and salt in medium saucepan.

Bring to a boil and boil 5 minutes. Remove from heat and add baking soda. Pour over popped corn and spread on cookie sheet. Bake at 200° for 1 hour, turning at 15 minute intervals. Cool and break apart.

title: german chocolate pie
directions: Mix all ingredients; pour in unbaked pie shells.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: e-z pie crusts
directions: Blend shortening into flour until pea size.
Mix the egg and vinegar well.
Add cold water and blend into flour mixture.
Knead on a floured surface.
Makes 6 pies; 3 double crust pies.

title: mexican dinner(100 to 110 servings)
directions: Saute all together the meat, onions and bell pepper until all of red color is gone.
Add seasoning.
Drain off fat.
Add tomato soup; simmer until seasoned well.
Make up regular corn bread recipe for topping.
Place hot meat in shallow steam table pans, about 1/2 full.
Add drained corn over top of meat.
Pour corn bread mixture over top.
Bake in a 400° oven until bread is browned.
Cut into 18 servings per pan.

title: potato casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients, adding cheese a little at a time.

title: cottage cheese pancakes
directions: Blend in blender.
Spoon onto hot skillet, which has been prepared with several tablespoons of oil.
Add more oil if needed. Turn when top is firm.
Serve warm with syrup, cinnamon, sugar, jam or fruit.

title: butterscotch squares
directions: Melt oleo over low heat.
Add sugar.
Stir until melted.
Let cool to lukewarm.
Add eggs one at a time.
Beat after each addition.
Add flour, baking powder and vanilla.
Pour into well-greased and floured pan.
Cook at 350° for about 30 minutes.

title: slow cooker beef stroganoff
directions: Heat oil in large skillet over medium-high heat. Roll the beef in flour and saut in oil until well browned, about 5 minutes. Transfer the meat to the slow cooker and mix with the soup, water and bouillon. Cook on high setting for 4 to 5 hours. Stir in sour cream during the last 30 minutes.
Cook the pasta according to package directions. Serve the meat over the noodles.

title: jellied tomato cheese salad
directions: Heat the soup to boiling; remove from heat.
Add the cheese; beat with a hand beater or an electric beater until thoroughly blended.

title: lemon dessert
directions: Fix the jello according to directions on box, adding the honey and juice.
Boil canned milk for 10 to 13 minutes, chill in refrigerator.
Whip the chilled milk and fold into jello as the jello begins to thicken.

title: crock-pot vegetable soup
directions: Put all ingredients in a crock-pot.
Cover and cook on low for 24 hours.

title: punch
directions: Use punch to make the ice cubes.
(Add 7-Up just before serving.)
Makes 8 gallons.
Serves 50 people.

title: congealed strawberry salad
directions: Mix pretzel crumbs with melted butter.
Spread evenly in 9 x 13 pan.
Bake 10 min. at 350 degrees.
Let cool.
Beat cream cheese and sugar until smooth, fold in whipped topping.
Spread over crumbs and refrigerate.
Blend strawberries with gelatin that has been dissolved in hot water.
Refrigerate until slightly thickened.
Spread over cheese mixture and return to refrigerator and chill until firm.
Cut into squares to serve. Makes 15 servings.

title: upside-down pizza
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Have a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan ready. Brown beef in skillet over medium heat, breaking up beef as it gets hot.
Drain off excess fat and let stand 5 minutes to cool slightly.
Add all but 1 tablespoon of the eggs to the beef and stir in the sauce until well blended.

title: sherwood salad
directions: Drain and rinse kidney beans.
Combine with rice, eggs and vegetables.
Blend salt, pepper, mayonnaise and vinegar.
Mix lightly with salad and chill.
Makes 6 servings.
Good with baked ham or cold cuts.

title: pot roast
directions: Put roast and mushroom soup, water and season in roasting bag. Cut up potatoes, carrots, mushrooms and onion; put in the bag. Cook at 350° for 2 hours.

title: bing cherry ring salad
directions: Combine juices, wine and sugar.
Bring to boil.
Pour over jello.
Add cherries which have been stuffed with pecan halves. Pour into greased ring mold.
Refrigerate until set.

title: microwave irish stew
directions: Cut beef into 1-inch square cubes.
Chop celery and carrots. Peel potatoes and cut into eighths.
Place beef cubes in 3-quart microproof dish.
Sprinkle salt on beef.
Stir together gravy mix and water.
Pour over meat.
Cook on 70% power for 50 minutes, covered.
Stir once while cooking.
Add vegetables and mix to cover with gravy.
Cook, covered, on 50% power for 40 to 50 minutes or until vegies and meat are tender.
Let stand 5 minutes.

title: spicy corn casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Mix all ingredients until well blended. Place the mixture into a lightly buttered 8 x 8 baking dish. Bake for 40 to 45 minutes or until lightly browned on top.
Test for doneness when toothpick inserted in center comes out clean.

title: low-fat banana bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix sugar, applesauce and egg.
Add flour, baking powder, baking soda and salt.
Mix in banana.
Bake in a greased pan until toothpick comes out clean.

title: baked corn pudding
directions: Saute pepper and onion in margarine.
Add dash of salt and pepper.
Mix with corn, eggs and Jiffy muffin mix.
Put in 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan and cook for 40 minutes at 400°.
Good hot or cold. Grated cheese may be added if desired.

title: friendship soup
directions: Mix ingredients together and heat, stirring constantly.
Serves 4-6.

title: pumpkin oat bran muffins
directions: Combine the first 6 ingredients in a large bowl; stir well. Make a well in center of mixture.
Combine pumpkin and the next 3 ingredients; stir well.
Add to dry ingredients, stirring just until moistened.
Spoon into muffin tins coated with cooking spray, filling 3/4 full.
Bake at 425° for 20 minutes.
Remove from pans immediately.
Serve warm or at room temperature. Yields 1 dozen.
Each muffin contains about 138 calories.

title: chicken curry casserole
directions: In a deep microwave-safe dish sprayed with pan coating, layer chicken and broccoli.
Mix together mayonnaise and yogurt; add curry powder.
Spread evenly over broccoli.
Sprinkle cheese over mayonnaise mixture.
Sprinkle bread crumbs over cheese.
Cover with paper towel.
Microwave on High 10 minutes or until broccoli is tender-crisp.
Serve over white rice or pasta.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients (use large bowl) and place in greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle with 2 cups crushed corn flakes (I use Frosted Flakes) and dot with butter.
Bake 1 hour at 350° or until bubbly and brown.

title: amaretto mousse cheesecake
directions: Combine graham cracker crumbs with butter.
Press onto bottom and sides of 9-inch spring-form pan.
Chill.
In saucepan, sprinkle gelatin over cold water; let stand 1 minute.
Stir over low heat until completely dissolved (about 3 minutes).
In electric mixer, beat cream cheese with sugar until fluffy. Gradually add evaporated milk and lemon juice; beat at high speed until fluffy (2 minutes).
Gradually beat in gelatin mix, liqueur and vanilla until blended.
Fold in whipped cream.
Pour into crust.
Chill 8 hours or overnight.
Garnish with chocolate chips or berries.
Serves 12.

title: blount's dip
directions: In a large skillet, brown hamburger and drain.
Cut the Velveeta cheeses into cubes and add a dash of milk.
Melt in a large pan, over medium-low heat, then add diced tomatoes, green onions, diced green chilies and cooked hamburger; stir well.
Add about 1/2 cup of picante sauce for additional flavor, if you wish. Serve with tortilla chips.

title: creamed lobster
directions: Cook lobster in butter 3 minutes over moderate heat.
Sprinkle with flour and stir well.
Add milk.
Cook slowly and stir until well heated and thickened.
Season to taste with salt, nutmeg, cayenne and lemon juice.
Serve on toast, in patty shells or with fluffy boiled rice.
If you like, add chopped parsley, strips of canned pimiento or sliced sauteed mushrooms.
Serves 3 or 4.

title: seafood cheese ball
directions: Mix together.
Shape in circle.
Mix 3/4 cup chili sauce and 2 tablespoons sweet pickle relish together.
Spread on top of circle. Place 6 ounces of drained crab meat in the middle and 4 ounces of drained shrimp on sides.

title: crock-pot bread stuffing
directions: Melt butter and saute onion, celery and parsley.
Pour over bread cubes in a very large mixing bowl.
Add seasonings and toss together well.
Pour in enough broth to moisten.
Cooked giblets and mushrooms may be added at this time.
Add beaten eggs and mix together well.
Pack lightly into crock-pot.
Cover and set to high for 45 minutes, then reduce to low to cook for 4 to 8 hours.

title: layered salad
directions: Tear lettuce into small pieces.
Layer ingredients in order in a large straight-sided glass bowl.
Combine mayonnaise and sugar and spread over other ingredients.
Cover with plastic wrap and refrigerate at least 4 hours.
Garnish with bacon bits and grated Parmesan cheese.

title: strawberry jam
directions: Put all in big pot and bring to boil.
Boil at a full rolling boil 1 minute, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat.
Skim off foam.
Jar and seal.
Makes 5 pints.

title: blueberry peach pie
directions: Preheat oven
to
Prepare
pastry.
Mix together flour, sugar
and
cinnamon.
Mix
blueberries
and
peaches together. Add flour
mixture; turn gently to coat peaches and blueberries. Place mixture into pie shell and dot with slices of margarine. Cover
with
slitted
top crust; seal and crimp edges.
Cover edges
with
aluminum
foil
to prevent too much browning. Uncover edges
the last 10 minutes of baking.
Bake at 425° for 40 to 50 minutes.
Cool before serving.

title: date bread
directions: Pour boiling water over dates.
Dissolve soda in it, let stand a few minutes.
Add other ingredients.
Bake at 300° 1-1 1/2 hours.
Makes two small loaves.

title: terry's chocolate cake
directions: Use a 9 x 13-inch greased pan.
Bring water to a boil.
Add to mixture of first 5 ingredients.
Mix well.
Add the remaining ingredients.
Beat well.
Bake 45 minutes at 300°.
Put frosting on cake 5 minutes before being done.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Combine green beans, milk, pepper and mushroom soup and 1/2 can of onion rings.
Mix well.

title: vanilla wafer bars
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients together.
(If mixture is too thick, add a little more sweetened condensed milk.)
Sprinkle a 9x13-inch pan with confectioners sugar.
Spoon mixture out into pan. Refrigerate until set.
Cut into squares and serve.

title: exceptional banana bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cream butter, sugar and eggs. Sift dry ingredients and combine with butter mixture. Blend well. Add bananas, vanilla and sour cream.
Stir very well.
Mix in nuts and pour into a well greased and floured 9x5x3 inch loaf pan. Bake 1 hour 10 mins.
Remove from pan and cook on rack.
I have used yogurt in place of sour cream with no change.

title: stuffed mushrooms
directions: Fry bacon; drain grease.
Crumble bacon.
Remove stems from mushrooms.
Chop stems and fry in skillet.
Drain.
Add bread crumbs and cheese.
Add crumbled bacon; stuff mushroom caps with filling.
Bake caps at 450° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Serve hot. Optional:
Add 1/2 pound browned sausage.

title: easy tomato aspic
directions: Mix
lemon
Jell-O
as	printed on package in bowl with lid. Stir
well	and add 2 cans of tomato sauce.
Add vinegar and salt.
Stir
well.	Place in refrigerator overnight until firm. Serve cold.

title: corn pudding
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Pour into greased baking dish.
Dot with butter.

title: south of the border quiche
directions: Mix together eggs, flour and baking powder; beat well.
Add cottage cheese, Cheddar cheese and Monterey Jack; stir well.
Add butter and green chilies.
Pour in a 13 x 9-inch baking dish. Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Mix shortening, peanut butter, sugar, brown sugar and egg. Sift together and stir in remaining ingredients.
Chill dough. Roll into balls the size of large walnuts.
Place 3 inches apart on lightly greased baking sheet.
Flatten with fork dipped in flour, crisscross.
Bake until set, but not hard, at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Makes about 3 dozen 2 1/2-inch cookies.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Line greased casserole with bread cubes.
Brown and drain sausage.
Place layer of toast, then sausage, then cheese.
Repeat the process until all is used.
Beat eggs with salt and pepper. Add milk.
Pour over casserole and refrigerate overnight.
Top with cornflakes.
Bake 45 to 60 minutes at 375°.

title: vegetable bars
directions: Spread crescent rolls on cookie sheet, 10 x 15-inches or larger.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 15 minutes or until golden brown. Cool.
Whip together the cream cheese, mayonnaise and Ranch dressing mix.
Spread over cooled crust. Top with fresh vegetables cut into small pieces.
Refrigerate.
Cut into 1 x 2-inch bars when ready to serve.
Serves 24 (many).

title: christmas salad
directions: Combine eggs and sugar in small saucepan, beat well with wire whisk.
Add
vinegar
and
butter.	Cook
over
low heat, stirring constantly until smooth and thickened.
Cool.
Fold in whipped cream.
Combine
fruits and marshmallows.
Fold in egg and	cream mixture.
Chill at least 3 hours.
Spoon into individual dishes. Yield:
12 servings.

title: chicken enchiladas
directions: Simmer sour cream, soup and chillies on low heat in saucepan. In a large skillet, stir-fry chicken, then add chicken to sauce. Grate cheese.

title: chicken pasta primavera
directions: In a 10-inch skillet over medium heat, cook and stir broccoli, onion, garlic and carrot in oil until crisp-tender, about 10 to 12 minutes. Stir in chicken, salt and tomatoes.
Heat just until chicken is hot, about 3 minutes. Spoon over hot macaroni. Sprinkle with cheese and parsley. Serves 4 to 6.

title: pumpkin dream dessert
directions: Combine margarine and sugar and beat until fluffy.
Add oatmeal and flour.
Mix; bake 18 to 20 minutes at 350° in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cool.
Beat cream cheese and sugar until fluffy. Add the eggs, one at a time, beating after each.
Mix in pumpkin, syrup and cinnamon.
Pour over crust and bake 45 to 50 minutes at 350°.
Refrigerate; top with Cool Whip.

title: stuffed baked fryer
directions: Chop one onion, celery, bell pepper and onion tops.
Mix with salt and pepper.
Stuff inside of fryer and close to keep in. Spread mustard on outside of fryer.
Put in roaster with 1 onion, sliced, and 1/2 cup water.
For gravy, thicken with flour as desired.

title: mount everest
directions: Mix together Cool Whip, Eagle Brand milk and lemon juice.
Add remaining ingredients.
Chill overnight.

title: no bake chocolate cookies
directions: Boil sugar, cocoa, butter and milk for 2 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Add peanut butter, oats and vanilla; stir until mixed well. Drop onto waxed paper by teaspoonful.
Cool.

title: bunny salad
directions: Invert halves of pears on individual beds of lettuce leaves, shredded.
Insert
blanched almonds for the ears of the rabbit, cloves or pink candy for the eyes and nose.
Use a bit of marshmallow for the tail.
Serve with dressing made with cream cheese.

title: pretzel salad
directions: Melt butter.
Mix in pretzels and 1/4 cup sugar and press into bottom
of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 375° and let cool.

title: vanilla pudding
directions: Pour milk and water into saucepan. Blend sugar and cornstarch together and add to milk mixture, stirring until dry ingredients are dissolved. Cook over medium-low heat, stirring often, until mixture comes to a full boil; boil 1 minute. Mixture should begin to thicken. Remove from heat. Stir 1/2 cup of the hot mixture into the beaten egg; then add egg mixture to saucepan. Heat over low heat, stirring constantly, until thick. Remove from heat and stir in vanilla. Pour into bowl and chill. Makes 5 servings, 1/2 cup each.

title: three-cheese meat loaf
directions: Mix in a large bowl with hands the meat, onion, green pepper, bread crumbs, pepper, salt, paprika, Italian seasoning, eggs (beaten with milk) and cheeses.
Don't overmix.
Use pan bigger than meat loaf.
Shape into loaf.
Bake at 350°
for 1 hour.
May cook ahead.
Use microwave to warm up.
Sprinkle the top with Italian seasoning.
Serve with mustards, chutneys or hot curried fruit.

title: sausage balls
directions: Combine the first 4 ingredients; mix well.
Shape into balls the size of quarters.
Brown and drain.
Drain fat from skillet, then add catsup, chili sauce, soy sauce, brown sugar, vinegar and water; stir well.
Return meat balls to skillet; cover and simmer for 30 minutes.
Refrigerate or freeze.
When ready to serve, just reheat.

title: veal and spinach cannelloni
directions: Cook cannelloni according to box.
Drain well.
Melt 1 ounce butter in a pan and saute onion until tender. Add veal and cook gently for 15 minutes, stirring frequently.
Add spinach, nutmeg and seasonings.
Cook for 10 minutes.

title: chicken tetrazzini(fern chew's recipe)
directions: Cook chicken in hot water to which salt, celery salt and onion has been added until tender enough to come off bones.
Remove chicken and reserve 4 or 5 cups of the broth.
To the rest, add 2 or 3 quarts of water and 2 teaspoons salt.
Bring to boil.
Add broken spaghetti.
Cook until tender.
Drain and place in baking pan.
Remove meat from bones.
Place in large bowl.
Heat 3 tablespoons margarine in skillet.
Add mushroom pieces; sprinkle lemon juice.
Cover and cook over low heat but do not brown until tender.
Add to the spaghetti and spread in pan.
Melt 3 tablespoons margarine in saucepan.
Add flour, pepper, paprika and nutmeg.
Add broth and cook until thickened.
Add milk and pour over chicken.
Refrigerate both chicken and spaghetti overnight, if desired.
One hour before serving, heat sauce and chicken and pour over spaghetti and mix well.
Spread in pan.
Bake 45 minutes at 375°.

title: juicy meat loaf
directions: Combine ingredients and pack in pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: ruth hough's frozen salad
directions: Mix ingredients; fold Cool Whip in last and put into a 9 x 13-inch dish.
Freeze and cut into squares.

title: buttercream frosting
directions: Cream margarine and Crisco until smooth.
Add sugar gradually, beating at medium speed.
You may double this recipe for layer cakes.

title: banana cake
directions: Mix sugar and shortening until smooth. Beat in eggs. In a separate bowl, combine salt, flour, baking powder and baking soda. Gradually add dry mix to wet mix, alternating with milk.
Mix in bananas and then vanilla. Pour into a greased 13 x 9-inch pan. Bake at 325° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Toothpick test.

title: hearts of palm salad
directions: Toss together spinach and carrot.
Cover; chill.
In a screwtop jar, place salad dressing and oregano.
Cover and shake to combine.
Chill.
Before serving, mound spinach onto 6 salad plates.
Top with hearts of palm.
Drizzle dressing mixture over. Garnish with savory and oregano, if desired.
Serve immediately. Yield:
6 servings.

title: carrot salad
directions: Drop chopped apple into pineapple juice for a few seconds to keep them from turning brown.
Drain well and mix with other ingredients.
Chill at least 1 hour before serving.

title: banana bread
directions: Cream the sugar and oleo together. Add dry ingredients.
Mix together. Add nuts and bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: no-crust cheese and spinach pie
directions: Combine Ricotta cheese, drained spinach, grated cheese, eggs, oil, seasonings and vegetables.
Pour mixture into deep pie plate or a 9 x 9 x 2-inch lightly oiled casserole dish.
Bake in preheated 350° oven about 40 minutes.
Butter may be dotted on top of casserole.
Pie can be eaten hot or cold, served as a brunch, luncheon entree or an appetizer.

title: tomato gravy and rice(quick and easy)
directions: Brown ground beef in large frying pan. Season to your desired taste. DO NOT DRAIN. When beef is brown completely, add 2 heaping tablespoons of flour; stir (flour should soak up all of the fat from the beef). Add 1 can tomatoes with liquid, and 1 tomato can of water. Stir and simmer until gravy thickens. Serve over rice.

title: never fail fudge
directions: Combine sugar, margarine, milk and Marshmallow Creme in a large glass bowl.
Microwave on High for 3 minutes.
Remove and stir well.
Continue to microwave on High 2 to 3 minutes, or until mixture boils.
Reduce power to Medium and boil 5 minutes.
Remove and add chocolate chips.
Stir until melted.
Add vanilla and nuts.
Turn into
a buttered 8-inch square pan.
Cut into squares when cool.
Makes 2 pounds.

title: potato casserole
directions: Melt margarine, mix all ingredients and toss with hash browns until coated.

title: chicken casserole
directions: In greased, shallow casserole, arrange ingredients in layers, starting with crumbs and ending with chicken.
Blend soup and milk.
Pour over chicken.
Moisten 1 1/3 cups crumbs with water and melted margarine.
Spread over casserole.
Bake in 400° oven for 30 minutes.

title: taco salad
directions: Prepare hamburger and taco mix as directed on package of taco mix. Pour over lettuce, tomatoes and onion.
Top with layer of shredded cheese. Place olives decoratively around top and place taco chips all around the sides of platter.
Serve with salsa, taco sauce or Ranch dressing.

title: easy 7 layer cookies
directions: Mix crumbs and melted margarine.
Spread in 9 x 13-inch pan. Sprinkle chocolate chips, butterscotch chips, nuts and coconut in this order in pan.
Pour condensed milk over all.
Bake 25 mintues at 350°.
When cool, cut into squares.

title: pineapple glaze
directions: Put all ingredients in saucepan; cook on medium heat.
Let boil 1 minute.
Pour over ham and bake.

title: pasta with broccoli and pesto
directions: Oil 9 x 13-inch glass pan or 9-inch casserole.
Coat with bread crumbs.
Cook pasta according to directions.
Preheat oven to 350°.
In skillet, heat oil and garlic over medium heat; add broccoli.
Stir-fry 4 to 5 minutes until crisp-tender.
Stir in pesto sauce and remove from heat.
Drain pasta and put into large bowl.
Add eggs and mix well.
Add broccoli mixture to pasta. Stir in Mozzarella.
Pour half of mixture into pan; sprinkle with Parmesan.
Add remaining pasta and sprinkle on more Parmesan. Bake 30 minutes until top browns slightly.

title: pull apart buns
directions: Mix sugar and cinnamon in bowl.
Shake in biscuit pieces. Melt butter and add to bowl mixture.
Put in Bundt pan (grease first).
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Cool 10 minutes and remove from pan.
Pull apart to eat.

title: pralines
directions: Boil sugar, molasses and water until hardens in water.
Add butter; beat.
Add nut meats and stir until it sugars.

title: swiss vegetable medley
directions: Drain vegetables; then combine with 1/2 cup cheese, 1/2 cup onions, soup, sour cream and pepper.
Pour into a 1-quart casserole dish.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.
Top with remaining cheese and onions.
Bake, uncovered, for 5 minutes.

title: banana bread
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Add eggs, margarine, sour cream and banana.
Stir in nuts.
Bake 25 minutes at 350° in floured and greased bread pans.

title: spinach balls
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Form into small balls.
Place on cookie sheet and freeze.
After frozen, place in plastic freezer bags until needed.
Bake frozen in a preheated 375° oven for 20 minutes.

title: vinegar egg pastry
directions: Beat eggs and vinegar and ice water.
Combine flour, sugar and salt.
Cut in Crisco and add egg mixture
and quickly mix with fork.
Cover and chill.
Makes one 9-inch double crust.

title: monterey chicken
directions: Pound breasts until thin and arrange in baking dish.
Top with cheese and spread undiluted soup over cheese.
Top with stuffing and drizzle with melted margarine.
Bake at 300° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: strawberry shortcake
directions: Mix cake by directions on box.
Add drained pineapple.
Pour into oblong pan.
Bake as directed on box.
While cake is hot, poke holes in cake with meat fork.
Spread on cream of coconut; let cool.
Stir together the sliced berries and glaze.
Spread over cooled cake.
Next, spread thawed Cool Whip and chill.
Let set overnight or all day before serving.

title: diet soup
directions: Mix all vegetables in a large pot.
Add water to cover.
Boil until cabbage is tender (about 45 minutes).

title: green beans and burger bake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Brown hamburg and onions.
Add seasonings, rice and 1/2 cup cheese.
Turn into a 2-quart casserole.
Top with green beans and pimentos.
Blend soup, mayonnaise and milk.
Pour over beans.
Sprinkle with remaining cheese.
Bake in preheated oven 30 minutes.

title: cinnamon popcorn
directions: Melt together butter, red hots, sugar and Karo syrup.
Drizzle over popcorn.
Bake at 300° for 30 minutes, stirring every 10 minutes.
Pour out on wax paper.
Let cool and then break apart. Yield: 24 cups.

title: cinnamon buns
directions: Grease a 1 piece tube pan (Bundt).
Sprinkle nuts and raisins on the bottom.
Roll each dinner roll in cinnamon and place around pan.
Sprinkle pudding on top.
Sprinkle brown sugar on top.
Melt butter and drizzle on top.
Cover with a towel.
Leave overnight. Bake the next morning at 350° for 30 minutes.
Turn out on plate.

title: little applesauce muffins
directions: In large bowl, cream softened butter and sugar until fluffy. Beat in eggs, one at a time, until light and fluffy.
Beat in applesauce. Sift dry ingredients and add to butter mixture; stir just enough to moisten.
Spoon into 36 greased tea-size muffin cups.
Bake at 425° about 15 minutes.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix together all ingredients except bacon.
Put in loaf pan with bacon on top.
Bake at 375° until done.

title: basic brownies
directions: Set oven at 350°.
Grease an 8 x 8 x 2-inch pan.
Sift flour. Melt margarine, then stir in cocoa.
Add sugar to beaten eggs.
Add chocolate mixture; blend well.
Add flour; mix well, then mix in vanilla.
Spread in greased pan.
Bake for 25 minutes, or until done.
Cool in pan, then cut into squares.

title: asparagus casserole
directions: Melt cheese in asparagus liquid.
Place asparagus in casserole dish.
Slice eggs and place on asparagus.
Crumble crackers on top.
Pour liquid over these ingredients.
Place in 350° oven until hot.

title: squash casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients and bake in glass casserole dish for 1 hour at 350°.

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: Boil chicken and save broth.
Saute onions and peppers in sticks of margarine.
Pour tomatoes in onion and pepper mixture and melt cheese in this mixture.
Cook spaghetti in chicken broth. When done, combine all ingredients and cook at 350° until bubbly.

title: lima beans and pork chops
directions: In heavy skillet, saute the chops until brown.
Remove the chops and cut meat into bite size pieces.
Saute the onions and rice in the butter in a large heavy skillet until the onions are golden and the grains of rice have chalky edges.
Add the tomatoes, beans and reserved pork.
Add chicken broth, bay leaf, rosemary and season to taste.
Cover the pan and reduce heat; simmer for 30 minutes without stirring; fluff the rice with fork. Arrange the stew on a large platter and sprinkle with parsley.

title: cream cheese spread
directions: Mix butter and cream cheese until well mixed.
Add powdered sugar until all lumps are gone.
Refrigerate.
Can be served with pumpkin bread, etc.

title: dieter's downfall
directions: Melt margarine in a 9 x 13-inch or 9-inch square pan; sprinkle crumbs evenly over margarine.
Spread butterscotch chips, coconut, chocolate chips and nuts evenly in layers over crumb mixture. Drizzle condensed milk evenly over top of layers.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
When cool, cut into 48 bars.
Let set up before serving.
If desired, two additional tablespoons butter may be added.

title: chocolate nut loaf
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour 9 x 5-inch loaf pan. In a large bowl, combine flour, sugar, baking soda, salt and nutmeg.
Stir in chocolate morsels and walnuts.
In small bowl, combine egg, buttermilk, orange juice, butter and orange peel; mix well.
Add egg mixture, stirring just until flour mixture is moist.
Spoon batter into pan.
Bake 50 to 55 minutes at 350°. Let cool for 10 minutes.

title: copper carrot pennies
directions: Peel carrots.
Slice and boil in salt water until tender.
Do not overcook!
When cool, mix with chopped onion and pepper.
Make marinade of remaining ingredients.
Beat well.
Pour over vegetables and refrigerate.
Will keep a week or longer in refrigerator.

title: baked rice
directions: Pour the milk into a baking dish.
Add the rice and stir together.
Bake at 325°, stirring it each time it gets a thin crust on top.
Bake until thick.
Remove from oven and add enough sugar to sweeten.
Serve warm or cold.

title: refrigerator pickles
directions: Put salt on cucumbers, onion and pepper.
Let set 1 hour; drain well.
Mix remaining ingredients and pour over vegetables. Place in jars and refrigerate.
Ready to eat in 10 days, but flavor improves if left longer.
Can be kept for weeks.
Two and a half batches of syrup makes 1 gallon of pickles.

title: potato and onion spanish omelet (andalusian)(tortilla andaluz de patata y cebolba)
directions: Peel and dice potatoes and onions.
Heat iron skillet over low heat after pouring in small amount of olive oil.
First, slowly cook potatoes, adding them gradually to skillet, then push them aside and start adding and cooking slowly the onions.
Stir constantly.
Beat eggs in a bowl and after potatoes and onions are cooked soft, start adding eggs gradually - low heat, remember. When omelet is firm, sprinkle on top the parsley and bacon bits if desired.
Use spatula to make sure omelet is loose at sides and underneath.
Then put under broiler briefly to achieve a golden brown appearance.
Remove from broiler and skillet.
Slice in tiny wedges; serve hot or cold.
Good for cocktail parties.
In large slices, can be basis for a meal with a salad.
Spaniards use this, with bread and wine, as a meal in the fields or as picnic fare.

title: peanut butter bars
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients.
Add confectioners sugar until right consistency (about 1 cup sifted).
Cool.
Cut into 2-inch squares.

title: potato casserole
directions: Mix all
except
corn flakes and 1/2 of margarine.
Put in a 9 x 13-inch Pyrex dish.
Spread corn flakes and margarine on top. Bake
at
350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.
Can be made up ahead and put in refrigerator or frozen for later.
If made up ahead, wait until you are ready to bake before you put corn flake mix on top.

title: applesauce muffins
directions: Cream margarine and sugar.
Add eggs and beat.
Heat applesauce; stir in baking soda and add to mixture.
Combine flour and spices; add to mixture, along with vanilla.
Bake in tiny greased muffin tins at 350° until light brown.
Roll in powdered sugar.

title: braunschweiger dip
directions: Have ingredients at room temperature for easier blend.
Mix by hand, not beating too hard.
Combine all ingredients and form in a roll or mound and put in bowl lined with foil or plastic wrap for easier removal.

title: rolls
directions: Sift dry ingredients together.
Add Crisco to flour with pastry blender until it looks like coarse meal.
Make a well in the flour and pour in the water.
Stir until it can be turned out on floured board.
Knead 10 times.
Roll and cut out.
Dip in melted oleo and put in pans.
Cover with plastic wrap and refrigerate or freeze.
Let rise until double.
Bake at 425° for about 15 minutes.

title: ice cream cake
directions: Melt chocolate and add to mayonnaise.
Add boiling water and mix well.
Add sugar and eggs, singly.
Mix flour, soda and salt. Sift and add alternately with milk.
Add vanilla.
Pour into 2 (9-inch) pans, greased and floured.
Bake 30 minutes in a 350° oven.
When cake is cool, quickly put a layer of ice cream between layers of cake, then ice the cake with Cool Whip.
Freeze immediately.

title: pound cake
directions: Cream sugar and butter until light and creamy.
Add eggs one at a time, beating constantly.
Add flour, salt and baking powder. Mix well.
Add vanilla.
Bake in greased and floured Bundt pan at 350° for 1 1/4 hours.

title: debbie's chicken casserole
directions: Mix first seven ingredients.
Put in medium sized casserole. Mix melted butter and corn flakes.
Sprinkle over mixture.
Bake for 45 minutes at 350°.

title: peanut butter balls
directions: Mix together.
Form into balls.
Refrigerate for a couple of hours.
Melt chocolate in microwave and dip peanut balls in it.

title: golden cornbread
directions: Sift together dry ingredients into a bowl.
Add milk, egg and oil or shortening.
Beat with mixer until smooth, about one minute.
Bake either in pan or muffin tins in hot oven (425°) for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: broccoli soup
directions: Cook broccoli and onion in small amount of water until tender (10 to 12 minutes). Put into blender 1 cup at a time and chop. Slowly make cream sauce by melting margarine over medium heat, then stir in flour until blended.
Gradually add milk and stir constantly until thickened.
Add warmed broth, stirring well. Then add cheese and spices and blend well.
Mix sauce and vegetables and heat thoroughly.

title: chicken cigars
directions: Preheat oven to 425°. Place chicken in a bowl and mix with spices and parsley. Place a piece of phyllo on a nonstick cookie sheet, butter it and top with a second sheet. Divide the chicken in half. form a 1-inch thick log the length of the long side of the phyllo dough. Roll the log in phyllo
tightly. Cut the chicken filled phyllo into 4 "cigars" and brush with a dab more butter. Repeat to make a total of 8 chicken and phyllo roll-ups. Bake 12 to 15 minutes until golden.

title: sweet and sour pork
directions: Brown pork in hot fat.
Add water.
Cover and simmer for 1 hour.

title: english muffin spread
directions: Mix all of the ingredients.
Cut muffins in half.
Bake for 15 minutes at 350°.

title: sausage casserole
directions: Cook sausage until no pink remains.
Grease a 2-quart baking dish with fat drained from sausage.
Layer sliced potatoes in bottom of dish.
Continue to layer onions, rice, carrots, sausage and tomatoes.
Last, mix salt, pepper and sugar.
Sprinkle over top of casserole and cover tightly.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 to 2 hours.

title: pralines
directions: Add cream to sugar and stir well.
Add nuts.
Melt butter in iron frypan and cool slightly.
Add sugar mixture.
Have frypan medium hot to start.
Turn heat to low as soon as mixture begins to bubble.
Cook until it becomes dark and spins a thread from the spoon.
Try to keep mixture cooking evenly on outside and inside of pan by stirring constantly.
Drop by spoonful on greased cookie sheet.

title: cherry cream cheese pie(icebox pie)
directions: Beat cream cheese until lite and fluffy; add Eagle Brand milk and lemon juice; beat well.
Stir in vanilla; pour into graham cracker crust.
Refrigerate for 3 hours.
Before serving top with cherry pie filling.

title: cottage cheese salad
directions: May use freshly sliced strawberries.

title: italian breaded fish fillets(cookbook winner, 1994)
directions: In shallow dish, combine croutons, Parmesan cheese, parsley flakes and paprika; blend well.
In another shallow dish, combine egg, water and lemon juice; blend well.
Cut fish into 2 1/2 to 3 inch pieces.
Dip fish pieces into egg mixture, then coat with crouton mixture.
Tuck thin ends of fish under to form pieces of uniform thickness.
Place half of the fish on microwave-safe roasting rack.
Microwave on high for 3 to 3 1/2 minutes, or until fish flakes easily with fork, rotating rack once halfway through cooking.
Place fish on serving plate; keep warm.
Repeat with remaining fish pieces.
Serves. 4

title: quiche
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Put cheese, onions, green peppers and ham (salt and pepper as desired) in unbaked pie crust.
Sprinkle with paprika.
In bowl, mix eggs and whipping cream until bubbles appear.
Pour in prepared pie crust pans and sprinkle with paprika.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes and then at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes until toothpick comes out clean.

title: spinach dip
directions: After spinach is cooked and cooled, combine all ingredients. Use one round loaf of crusty French bread, hollowed out in the center.
Pour mix into center of hollowed out shell of French bread.
Dip with bite-size pieces of bread, chips or crackers.

title: french canadian shepherd's pie
directions: Brown the hamburger and onions. Drain.
Place in the bottom of a deep dish pie plate or casserole dish. Top with corn. Top with mashed potatoes and egg mixed together.
Spread like icing to seal the top. Sprinkle with a touch of grated American or Parmesan cheese, if desired. Bake at 400° until potatoes are slightly browned.

title: matador mania
directions: Cook ground chuck in a large skillet until browned, stirring to crumble; drain well.
Add chopped onion, water, chili powder, salt, cumin and pepper to ground chuck.
Cook, uncovered, about 5 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Remove skillet from heat; stir in refried beans and set mixture aside.
Spread about 1/2 cup taco sauce in a greased 12 x 7-inch baking dish.
Arrange 2 tortillas on top of sauce; cover with half of meat mixture, sour cream and an additional 1/2 cup taco sauce.
Arrange 2 additional tortillas on top of sauce; cover with additional 1/2 cup taco sauce, the remaining meat mixture and half the cheese.
Arrange remaining tortillas, taco sauce and cheese on top.
Cover and bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Let stand 5 minutes before serving.

title: dutch oven baked potatoes
directions: Cook bacon until nearly done.
Add margarine.
Add sliced potatoes, onions and mushrooms.
Stir gently to mix bacon through potatoes.
Cover; bake in oven at 350° until done.
Do not stir. When done, lay sliced cheese on top; let melt through.

title: spice cake
directions: Follow cake mix receipt.
Add dry pudding and add spice mix. Used electric beater until spices are blended.
Bake in tube pan greased and floured pan and put wax paper in pan.
Bake at box temperature and time.
Test to see if done.
Let cool on wet cloth before removing from pan.

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: Saute pepper and onion in butter until tender.
Drain spaghetti and mix with cheese and other ingredients.
Bake until cheese is melted.

title: easy-cheesy lemon bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease 9 x 13-inch pan on bottom only. Combine in large bowl first three ingredients until well mixed. Press into prepared pan.
Blend in large bowl frosting mix and cream cheese.
Reserve 1/2 cup for frosting baked bars.
Add 2 eggs to remaining frosting mixture.
Beat 3 to 5 minutes.
Spread over base.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Cool; frost. Makes about 3 dozen bars.

title: yellow rose of texas
directions: Saute chicken quickly in garlic and butter.
Remove to casserole dish.
Saute celery and onion in drippings.
Add Ro-Tel tomatoes and heat to a simmer.
Add cheese and heat thoroughly. Pour sauce over chicken breasts.
Bake for 20 minutes in 350° oven.
Serve over rice.

title: praline pie
directions: Cream together the cream cheese, Cool Whip and Eagle Brand milk.
Pour into graham cracker crusts.
Toast in oven at 450° until golden brown the coconut and slivered almonds.
Sprinkle on top and pour the caramel topping on top of this.

title: minute steak scramble
directions: Season meat with garlic and ginger.
Heat half of the oil in a skillet, add meat and brown quickly on all sided.
Remove meat and add remaining oil, heat and add peppers and celery.
Cook until slightly tender, about 3 minutes.
Mix cornstarch and cold water and soy sauce.
Add to skillet and cook, stirring until mixture thickens.
Add meat & tomatoes.
Heat.
Serve with rice and pass the soy sauce.

title: granny's angel biscuits
directions: Dissolve yeast, sugar and warm water.
Set aside.
Combine dry ingredients.
Cut in margarine until crumbly.
Add yeast mixture and buttermilk.
Mix well.
Turn out on floured surface.
Knead about 1 minute.
Roll or pat out and cut into biscuits.
Bake in preheated oven after allowing to rise a few minutes.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes.
This dough keeps well in refrigerator for weeks.

title: hungarian chicken liver pate
directions: Saute livers and onions together; let cool.
Grind and add 2 chopped, hard-boiled eggs.
Mix with other ingredients.
Shape into your favorite mold and chill.
Unmold and top with grated egg.
Serve with crackers.

title: salinas valley special appetizer
directions: Pour reserved artichoke liquid from 1 jar into skillet and saute garlic and onion until soft but not brown.
Beat eggs.
Add bread crumbs, garlic, onion, seasonings and parsley.
Stir in cheese and chopped artichokes.
Pour mixture into a greased 7 x 11-inch pan and bake at 325° for 30 minutes.
Cut into cubes and serve warm.

title: chicken cardinal
directions: Soak tomatoes in wine overnight.
Drain and reserve the wine. Chop tomatoes.
Heat oil in large skillet.
Dust chicken in seasoned flour.
Lightly brown chicken on both sides in oil.
Add all other ingredients to skillet, including reserved wine and bring to a boil.
Reduce heat to a simmer and cook for 5 to 8 minutes or until chicken is tender.
Serve over pasta.

title: crab dip
directions: Chop crab meat.
Chop celery and red onion; add to crab meat. Add cocktail sauce, cream cheese, lemon juice, dill weed, hot pepper sauce and white pepper.
Mix until well blended.
Serve on mini bagels.

title: pork casserole
directions: Sear chops or steaks in a skillet.
Pour 1 can of soup in casserole dish. Line chops or steaks across dish.
Pour second can of soup over chops or steaks.
Bake at 375° for 2 hours.

title: fruit cocktail pudding
directions: Mix dry ingredients; stir in fruit cocktail with juice.
Pour into greased 8 x 10-inch pan.
Mix brown sugar with chopped nuts. Sprinkle over top of dessert.
Bake 1 hour at 300°.
Serve with whipped cream or ice cream.

title: taco cheese dip
directions: Mix all together and cook in crock-pot until melted and well blended.

title: honey glazed ham
directions: Preheat oven to 325 degrees.
Score ham and stud with the whole cloves.
Place ham in foil-lined pan.
In the top half of a double boiler, heat the corn syrup, honey and butter.
Keep glaze warm while baking ham. Brush glaze over ham, and bake for 1 hour and 15 minutes in the preheated oven.
Baste ham every 10 to 15 minutes with the honey glaze.
During the last 4 to 5 minutes of baking, turn on broiler to caramelize the glaze.
Remove from oven and let sit for a few minutes before serving.

title: bourbon bing salad
directions: Another Jell-O salad!
This one is messy to make, but eaten happily by even salad haters.
(Children won't care for it.)

title: cranberry apple cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease Bundt pan.
Put flour, baking soda, salt, nutmeg and cinnamon in a bowl; mix.
Quarter and core apples.
Cut into 1/4-inch chunks.
Put brown sugar, oil, eggs and vanilla into large bowl.
Beat until smooth.
Stir in flour mixture.
Stir in cranberries, apples and nuts.
Batter will be stiff and seem like there is too much fruit.
Pour batter into pan.
Bake 1 hour and 5 minutes.
Cool 30 minutes then remove from pan.

title: easy cheese cake
directions: Beat cheese until smooth.
Gradually beat in sugar.
Blend in sour cream and vanilla.
Fold in Cool Whip, blending well.
Spoon into crust and chill until set, approximately 4 hours.
Spoon pie filling on top.

title: cavitini
directions: Boil noodles.
Brown meat and drain.
Mix together first 8 ingredients and top with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes or until cheese melts.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together and spread over 8-inch graham cracker crust.
Chill well.

title: potato, tomato and onion casserole
directions: In medium bowl cook onion, garlic, thyme and 1 tablespoon oil, covered, on High 5 to 7 minutes, until tender, stirring halfway through cooking.
Meanwhile, peel potatoes and slice 1/4 inch thick.
Stir potatoes, tomatoes, pepper and salt into onions. Spoon into 2-quart shallow casserole.
Cook, covered, on High 20 to 24 minutes, until tender, stirring 3 times during cooking.
In a 1-cup glass measure combine 1 tablespoon oil, bread crumbs and Parmesan cheese.
Cook on High 1 1/2 to 2 1/2 minutes, until crumbs are browned, stirring twice during cooking.
Sprinkle crumb mixture over potatoes.
Makes 4 servings.
Each serving: About 265 calories, 8 g fat, 1 mg cholesterol and 490 mg sodium.

title: pie crust
directions: Mix flour and salt with shortening.
Add egg, vinegar and cold water; mix well.
Makes 4 or 5 crusts, depending on thickness. May be refrigerated 7 to 10 days.

title: taco twist
directions: Brown hamburger; drain.
Stir in seasoning mix, tomato sauce and green pepper.
Bring to a boil and remove from heat.
Combine cooked macaroni, 1/2 cup cheese and the sour cream.
Place on bottom of a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish or pan.
Top with meat mixture and remaining cheese.
Bake at 350°
for 30 minutes.

title: chinese style roast beef(cold dish)
directions: *Items can be purchased from Chinese supermarket.

title: strawberry pretzel salad
directions: Crush pretzels slightly enough for 2 cups.
Add margarine and 3 tablespoons of sugar.
Mix together and press into a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes at 350°.
Cool.

title: no bake cocoa chip nut cookies
directions: In a saucepan, bring sugar, butter, cocoa, milk and nuts to a full boil.
Reduce heat and boil for 3 to 4 minutes (soft boil stage).
Remove from heat and add oatmeal and vanilla. Quickly drop onto waxed paper by teaspoon.
Let harden and refrigerate.

title: chicken or turkey tetrazzini
directions: Using a large pan, add 1 quart of water, chicken breasts, 2 tablespoons of chicken base, celery, onion, carrot, garlic and Cajun seasoning to taste; cook until tender. Pan-fry mushrooms in butter; melt 1 tablespoons of flour and stir until smooth. Strain the broth from the cooked chicken, saving the vegetables and chicken. Put 1 pint of the broth in a container and add 1/2 pint of heavy cream. Slowly add the broth and cream mixture to the pan that has the flour and butter; increase the heat to medium (do not boil). Beat 4 egg yolks and add them to the mixture; stir and lower the heat. Slice the chicken.

title: mexico delight
directions: Brown hamburger and drain.
Add taco mix and 1 cup water.
Cook until water is gone.
Layer a 9 x 13-inch pan with 3 tortillas, then hamburger and salsa, then 3 more tortillas, then beans and sour cream.
Sprinkle olives next and then 3 more tortillas.
Top with cheeses and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: 1-2-3 cake
directions: Add all the ingredients together and bake in 13 x 9-inch pan at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes.

title: italian biscotti
directions: Mix oil, eggs and sugar until well blended (by hand).
Add dry ingredients mix until well moistened.
Add flavoring, mix well.
Add nuts or chocolate chips if desired.

title: magic squares
directions: Melt butter in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Add graham cracker crumbs evenly over butter.
Pour milk over crumbs, then add chocolate chips, nuts and coconut.
(Pour evenly over in layers.)
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: chicken pasta
directions: Bake or grill chicken.
Cut into 1-inch cubes after cooked. Combine sauces, wine and onion.
Cook until onion is browned.
Add tomato sauce, peppers and mushrooms.
Simmer until sauces are warmed; add chicken.
Simmer about 10 minutes.
Boil pasta per directions.
Drain.
Add cold water and drain again.
Pour sauce on pasta.
Add fresh tomato; sprinkle with basil and cheese to taste.

title: simply "three" frosting
directions: Place the sugar, water and eggs in a double boiler. The water in the lower part of the double boiler needs to be rapidly boiling. Constantly beat the mixture with an electric mixer or whisk for 7 minutes. When slightly cool, spread the frosting.

title: cavatini
directions: Spray a 9 x 13-inch pan with Pam.
Cook Italian sausage.
Mix together the first 3 ingredients.
Pour into pan and top with cheese.
Bake at 350° until cheese melts.
Serve with salad and garlic bread.

title: fruit salad dressing
directions: Cook first 5 ingredients until consistency of cream. Put this into the beaten egg whites.
Add whipped cream.
Serve over salad when ready to use.

title: three bean vinaigrette
directions: Drain cans of three bean salad, reserving liquid from 1 can. Discard remainder.
Combine beans, reserved liquid, rice, kidney beans, artichoke hearts, pepper and salt in large bowl.
Toss and chill.
Serve over lettuce leaves.
Makes 6 servings.

title: roasted vegetables
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
In 13 x 9-inch pan melt butter in oven (5 to 6 minutes).
Stir in thyme, pepper and garlic powder.
Add the rest of the ingredients; toss to coat.
Cover with foil and bake 22 to 30 minutes or until vegetables are crisp-tender.

title: broccoli cheese topper
directions: In 1 1/2-quart saucepan, stir soup, sour cream and mustard. Heat through, stirring occasionally. Stir in broccoli (flowerets) and heat through.

title: baked rice
directions: Melt oleo in skillet.
Add rice and brown slowly for 15 minutes, stirring constantly.
Add other ingredients and place in ungreased baking dish (10 x 6 1/2-inches).
Cover with foil.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: bridget's creamed corn
directions: Bring all ingredients to boil, then simmer 5 minutes.
Blend together 2 tablespoons of flour and 2 tablespoons of butter.
Add to corn and remove to heat.

title: chicken casserole
directions: In a saucepan, bring chicken broth and rice to a boil.
Reduce heat.
Cook, covered, for 15 minutes.
Remove from heat; let stand, covered, for 10 minutes.
Meanwhile, cook broccoli according to package directions; drain.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Beat shortening and sugar; add eggs.
Add dry ingredients. Chill 1 hour.
Roll in balls and coat with sugar and cinnamon. Mash to flatten with fork.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheet at 350° for 10 minutes.
They are good without sugar and cinnamon.

title: eggplant parmigiana
directions: Wash and trim eggplant and cut into 1/2-inch slices.
Combine crumbs and 1/4 cup of Parmesan cheese.
Spread mayonnaise on both sides of eggplant, then dip in crumb mixture, coating both sides. Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 425° for 10 to 15 minutes.
Remove pan and reduce heat to 375°.
Transfer eggplant to a 9 x 13-inch greased pan.

title: oven baked pork chops
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Butter baking pan.
Sprinkle rice on bottom of pan.
Lay pork chops on rice.
In another bowl, combine the cream of chicken and cream of mushroom soups with water.
Mix and pour over pork chops.
Sprinkle dry onion soup over the pork chops.
Cover with foil.
Bake for 2 to 2 1/4 hours.

title: judith's hummus tahini
directions: Blend all ingredients in food processor or blender until very smooth.
Serve on saltines or toasted pita bread or as a dip for raw vegetables.

title: angel squares
directions: In a mixing bowl with an electric mixer, beat egg whites until stiff.
Beat in salt, baking powder and sugar.
Fold in crushed cookies and pecans.
Pour into a greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
Bake in a preheated 350° oven 35 to 40 minutes.

title: shorter mansion punch
directions: Dilute lemonade as described on the can with dry sherry rather than water.
Add soda water as desired.
Serve from punch bowl in cups with shaved ice.
Ice ring of lemonade is attractive in punch bowl and will not dilute punch.

title: biscuit mix
directions: Mix dry ingredients together.
Cut in shortening until well blended.
Store in container on shelf.

title: pumpkin cookies
directions: Cream shortening; add sugar gradually.
Cream until light and fluffy.
Add eggs and pumpkin; mix well.
Sift flour, baking powder, salt and spices together.
Stir in dry ingredients and mix well until blended.
Drop on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° approximately 15 minutes.

title: fettucine alfredo
directions: Cook noodles until tender, 8 to 10 minutes in salted water with 1 tablespoon oil.
Drain.
Melt butter in chafing dish or electric skillet over medium heat.
Add cheese, parsley, cream and beaten egg gradually.
Blend until slightly thickened.
Add noodles, salt and pepper to taste.
Toss lightly until noodles are coated evenly with sauce.
Serve on hot plates and garnish with additional cheese.

title: spinach casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 375°. Butter 1-quart casserole dish.
Cook noodles per package directions.
Strain and set aside.
Prepare spinach per package directions.
Strain and mix with noodles in a large mixing bowl.

title: chicken rice dressing
directions: Combine margarine and lemon juice; brush chicken with mixture.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Place in 12 x 9 x 2 inch baking dish; bake at 400 degrees for 30 minutes.
Combine rice, chicken broth, and water in a medium pan; bring to a boil.
Reduce heat.
Cover and simmer about 5 minutes or until all broth is absorbed.
Set aside.
Cook sausage, onion, and celery in a skillet until sausage is done, stirring occasionally to crumble sausage.
Combine sausage and rice mixture.
Season with salt and pepper to taste; stir well.
Spoon mixture around chicken and bake for an additional 30 minutes.

title: lodge of the four seasons baked beans
directions: Saute bacon and onions.
Caramelize with brown sugar.
Add other sauce ingredients.
Simmer 10 minutes.
Stir sauce into beans.
Bake (or place covered pans on side of grill at barbecue stand!).
Makes 300 servings.
Perfect for your next Jobie barbecue fundraiser.

title: raw apple cake
directions: Beat eggs. Add sugar, then oil. Sift dry ingredients together and add to mixture.
Mix well, then add vanilla and nuts.
Bake in a 9 x 13-inch pan at 300° for 25 minutes.

title: oven fried chicken
directions: Coat baking sheet with non-stick coating spray.
Put flour and seasonings in plastic bag and add chicken one piece at a time, shaking to coat chicken.
Place skin side down on baking sheet and cook at 350° for 30 minutes.
Then turn chicken over and continue about 30 minutes more until golden brown.

title: dressing(for corn-on-the-cob or potato)
directions: Mix and bake on potato or microwave corn with husk on and serve.

title: yellow squash casserole
directions: Mash cooked squash.
Add all other ingredients and mix well. Pour into a greased baking dish and bake at 375° for approximately 45 minutes.
Yields 6 ample servings.

title: turkey tetrazzini
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Make white sauce with margarine, flour, milk and seasonings.
Stir in mayonnaise.
Add spaghetti, turkey, peas and 1/3 cup of cheese; mix lightly.
Pour into 2-quart casserole.
Sprinkle with remaining cheese.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Makes 6 servings.

title: triple orange ambrosia salad
directions: Pour boiling liquid over gelatin in bowl; stirring until gelatin is dissolved.
Add orange sherbet; stir until melted. Stir in one can of mandarin oranges.
Chill until firm in a ring mold.
Combine remaining ingredients; folding in sour cream. Chill at least 3 hours.
Fill in center of salad mold with fruit mixture.

title: party mix
directions: Mix buttermilk mix, garlic salt, dill weed, lemon pepper and oil together.
Pour over crackers, stirring often.
Let set for 3 hours.

title: favorite lemon pie *
directions: Combine all ingredients in top of double boiler.
Cook over hot water, using low heat, until mixture thickens.
Stir constantly. Chill in refrigerator before pouring into baked pie shell.
Top with meringue.
This may also be used as filling for layer cake.

title: orange glazed pecans
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a medium saucepan, combine sugars, sour cream and orange juice.
Stirring constantly, cook over medium-low heat until sugars dissolve.
Using a pastry brush dipped in hot water, wash down any sugar crystals on sides of pan. Attach candy thermometer to pan, making sure thermometer does not touch bottom of pan.
Increase heat to medium and bring to a boil. Cook, without stirring, until syrup reaches soft ball stage (approximately 234° to 240°).
Test about 1/2 teaspoon syrup in ice water.
Syrup should easily form a ball in ice water but flatten when held in your hand.
Remove from heat.
Stir in orange extract.
Add pecans and stir until well coated.
Spread pecan mixture on buttered aluminum foil.
Allow to dry uncovered at room temperature 24 hours.
Break apart and store in airtight container.
Yields about 4 1/2 cups pecans.

title: garlic and oil sauce
directions: Heat the oil until warm.
Add the garlic and simmer slowly for about 5 minutes or until the garlic is golden.
Do not burn.
You may remove the garlic at this point or leave it in if you enjoy a strong garlic flavor.
Add the black and red pepper, parsley and basil.
Stir well and use as desired.

title: fruit cup
directions: Add cantaloupe, grapes, watermelon and blueberries to first 3 ingredients (if in season or as available).
Cut fruit up and cover with orange juice.
Add defrosted strawberries just before serving.

title: sour cream chocolate cake
directions: Line two 8-inch layer cake pans with parchment paper.
Melt chocolate in double boiler.
Sift dry ingredients together and whisk.
In another bowl mix oil, coffee and whisk sour cream together.
Mix to dry ingredients.
Blend on low speed.
Add eggs (one at a time) and mix on medium speed.
Add chocolate and mix until blended, about 10 seconds.
Fill cake pans with mixture. Bake at 345° for 35 minutes.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Mix all ingredients except cheese and chips.
Turn into shallow buttered pan.
Combine cheese and chips over top.
Bake, uncovered, at 375° for 20 minutes.

title: coconut macaroon pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour into a greased and floured glass pie plate.
Bake in a 350° oven for 30 to 40 minutes or until firm.

title: okra and tomatoes
directions: Cook bacon slightly. Saute onion with bacon until tender. Add tomatoes, chicken broth, sugar, and pepper. Simmer 20 minutes. Add okra and simmer 20 more minutes.

title: ratatouille(basic recipe)
directions: Cut eggplant into 1/2-inch slices (then cut zucchini, onions and peppers into 1/4-inch slices, then cut into 1-inch cubes). Saute eggplant in 1/4 cup oil until lightly browned, about 5 minutes.
Repeat until used up.
Remove to Dutch oven.
Saute zucchini in 1/4 cup oil, about 5 minutes.
Remove to Dutch oven. Saute onions, peppers and garlic about 5 minutes.
Add to Dutch oven.
Add tomatoes, parsley, salt, pepper, oregano and basil. Stir gently to combine.
Simmer mixture over low heat covered for 15 minutes.
Remove cover and cook 10 minutes longer.

title: cheese straws
directions: Blend cheese and butter.
Gradually add flour, then add other ingredients.
Shape into whatever and place on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Place on wire rack to cool. Makes 3 1/2 dozen, depending on size and shape.

title: luscious lemon bars
directions: Place the shortening in a large bowl and beat with electric mixer at medium speed for 30 seconds.
Add sugar and beat until fluffy.
Stir in flour and milk until crumbly and well mixed. Turn into pan.
Press evenly against bottom.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: quick chocolate icing
directions: Melt chocolate and butter over water.
Beat egg yolks, mixing with some sugar until stiff.
Mix both adding cream and the remainder of sugar alternately.
Beat until creamy, then spread on cooled cake.

title: citrus chiffon pie
directions: Thoroughly mix gelatin, 1/2 cup sugar and salt in saucepan. Beat together egg yolks, fruit juices and water.
Stir into gelatin mixture.
Cook and stir over medium heat just until mixture comes to boiling.
Remove from heat and stir in peels. Chill, stirring occasionally, until mixture mounds slightly when dropped from a spoon.

title: old fashioned vanilla homemade ice cream
directions: Beat eggs until lemon colored.
Add sugar; stir until dissolved.
Add rest.
Add milk to 3 inches from top of freezer.

title: easy chicken pie
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Grease shallow 2-quart baking dish. Spread chicken and vegetables evenly in prepared dish.
Stir together soup, broth and pepper in a small mixing bowl.
Stir until smooth.
Pour evenly over chicken mixture.
Combine baking mix, milk and butter in separate bowl.
Stir until smooth.
Pour flour mixture over ingredients in baking dish.
Bake 45 to 50 minutes or until golden brown.
Cool for 10 minutes before serving.

title: pepper relish
directions: Wash 3 (1 pint) jars with soapy water and rinse well.
Put the jars in a large saucepan; cover with water and bring to a boil. Boil for 20 minutes.
Turn off the heat and leave the jars in the water while you make the relish.
Wash, rinse and sterilize the lids in the same way, using a separate pan.
Drain the jars and lids just before using, so they are dry but still hot.
Put the peppers and onion in a bowl.
Cover with boiling water.
Let stand for 5 minutes and drain in a colander.

title: cube steak and onion bake
directions: On a piece of waxed paper, mix flour and salt.
Coat meat pieces.
Melt margarine in large heavy skillet.
Add meat and brown on both sides.
Transfer meat to covered baking dish.
Add onion to skillet and saute briefly.
Spoon over meat.
Stir any leftover flour into skillet and blend in bouillon.
Add thyme and milk. Cook, stirring constantly, until sauce boils and thickens slightly. Pour over meat.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours, until very tender. Gravy Master may be added to darken gravy, if desired.

title: mini pizzas
directions: Mix and spread over muffins.
Cut into 6 pieces.
Freeze on cookie sheets.
Bake at 350° until heated through, 25 to 30 minutes.

title: easy egg custard pie
directions: Beat eggs; add sugar and other seasonings. Pour into pie shell. Bake at 375° for 45 minutes or until firm when knife inserted in center comes out clean.

title: apple-pineapple dip
directions: Combine ingredients, except cheese.
Refrigerate.
Pour over cream cheese.
Serve with Triscuits crackers.

title: italian cream cake icing
directions: Mix cream cheese and margarine together; then add powdered sugar.
Mix well.
Add vanilla and nuts.
Put nuts on top of cake, if desired.

title: frances' potato salad
directions: Combine first 8 ingredients.
Add mayonnaise, mustard and vinegar.
Mix well.
Dice eggs and add to mixture.
Toss gently. Sprinkle with paprika.
Cover and chill for 3 to 4
hours.
Yields 6 to 8 servings.

title: beef an louse
directions: Cook in a 10-inch skillet over medium heat.
Brown the ground beef and onion.
Drain off grease.
Add to the ground beef and onion the Worcestershire sauce, tomato juice and egg noodles. Cover and stir occasionally until the egg noodles are tender. Remove from heat; stir in the sour cream.

title: breakfast burritos
directions: In a casserole dish, combine Velveeta, salsa and sausage. Cook eggs (do not add salt) in lightly oiled skillet.
Add eggs to cheese mixture.
Warm flour tortillas according to package directions.
Place 4 to 5 tablespoons of mixture in each tortilla and roll up.
Place on platter.
Serve with extra salsa and sour cream.

title: quick chocolate sauce
directions: Combine sugar and cocoa in a saucepan; stir over low heat for 2 minutes.
Add butter and evaporated milk.
Turn up heat, add vanilla.
Serve over vanilla ice cream or cake.

title: chile rellenos bake
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients and bake until done at 400°.

title: stu's venison chili
directions: Brown venison in reserved bacon fat, then add onion, carrots, green pepper, chili powder and oregano and cook for 10 minutes. Add tomatoes, tomato paste and bacon and let simmer 45 minutes. Add kidney beans and simmer 30 minutes longer.
May be served with rice, if desired.

title: fruit cocktail cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Poke holes in cake and pour topping over top.

title: texas slaw
directions: Alternate cabbage and onions in layers in a large bowl.
Top with 7/8 cup sugar.

title: coleslaw
directions: Combine ingredients for dressing and refrigerate.

title: caramels
directions: Mix sugar, butter and Karo thoroughly.
Let come to a boil, stirring constantly.
Add milk.
Keep mixture boiling and continue stirring until a hard ball is formed in cold water.
Remove from fire; stir in nuts and vanilla.
Pour into a well buttered pan, 13 x 9-inches.
When cold, cut in strips, then bite-size pieces. Wrap in cellophane squares.

title: pork chop dinner
directions: Season chops with salt and pepper; brown on both sides in hot oil.
Remove chops and add onion soup mix and water to pan drippings; bring to a boil.

title: cabbage casserole
directions: Brown beef and onions in saucepan.
Layer cabbage, meat and soup in 13 x 9-inch pan.
Sprinkle with cheese. Cover and bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: tea cakes
directions: Cream butter and sugar. Add eggs, cream of tartar, soda, salt and vanilla. Add flour a little at a time. Mix well. Chill. Roll dough into small marble-size balls.
Place onto greased silver cookie sheet. Place pecan half on top of each cookie. Bake at 325° for 20 minutes or until done.

title: cabbage slaw
directions: Prepare each vegetable.
Mix together with mayonnaise, salt and pepper.
Chill well before serving.

title: broccoli spaghetti salad
directions: Cook broccoli; drain.
Stir in mushrooms, butter, salt and pepper.
Cook about 5 minutes.
Cook spaghetti; drain.
Toss all together.

title: fruit pizza
directions: Press cookie dough in pan and bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes until golden brown.
Cool completely.
Combine cream cheese, powdered sugar and Cool Whip.
Spread on cooled crust. Arrange fruit in circles or however way you prefer.
(Soak sliced bananas in pineapple juice.)
Drain all fruit well.

title: pumpkin roll
directions: Beat eggs at high speed for 5 minutes. Gradually add 1 cup sugar.
Stir in pumpkin and lemon juice.
Sift and fold flour mixture (the remaining dry ingredients except pecans) into pumpkin mixture.
Spread into greased and floured cookie sheet.
Top with pecans.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Watch closely.
When done, turn out on tea towel.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar.
Roll up towel and cake and cool completely.
Then, unroll and spread with Pumpkin Roll Filling.

title: chicken rice casserole
directions: Quickly brown fryer in melted butter.
Remove.
Add rice to oleo and stir.
Add water and soup.
Lay chicken pieces on top of rice.
Cover and place in 350° oven for 45 minutes.

title: pizza meatballs
directions: Makes 5 servings (20 balls).

title: after thanksgiving special
directions: Mix all ingredients together and cook on low until all mixture is hot.
Serve with bread or crackers.

title: lacy and bryan's favorite caesar salad
directions: Prepare croutons by frying the Pepperidge Farm stuffing over a low flame in 3 tablespoons olive oil flavored with the garlic. Into a garlic-rubbed wooden bowl, tear the chilled romaine heads into medium-size pieces and sprinkle with the dry mustard, black pepper, salt (to taste) and grated Parmesan cheese.
Add 6 tablespoons olive oil and the lemon juice.
Break 2 eggs on the greens and toss enough to mix thoroughly, but not so vigorously as to bruise the greens and until no trace of egg can be seen.
The leaves should be coated, but there must not be excess liquid in bowl.
Taste for seasoning.
An instant before serving, all the croutons, tossing the salad briefly to mix in the croutons without making them soggy.
Add bacon slices cut into small pieces and fried until crisp.
Add Worcestershire.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Boil chicken until tender.
Reserve 2 cups of broth.
Remove chicken from bone and cut in fine pieces.
Mix soups with chicken broth and can of cream.
Mix stuffing with 1 stick margarine (melted).
Put half of stuffing mix in a 9 x 13-inch pan, then put chicken in pan.
Pour soup mixture over chicken.
Sprinkle remaining stuffing mix on top.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: raisin cream pie
directions: Soak raisins in hot water 20 minutes and drain well; set aside.
Combine flour, sugar, salt and egg whites in medium saucepan.
Mix well.
Gradually add milk and water.
Cook on medium-high heat, stirring constantly until thick.
Add margarine, vanilla and raisins.
Cool and pour into a baked pie crust.
Cover with meringue or Cool Whip if desired.

title: french toast bake
directions: Arrange bread in a greased 13 x 9 x 2 inch baking dish. In a bowl combine eggs, milk, 3/4 c. brown sugar, vanilla and nutmeg; pour over bread. Cover and refrigerate 8 hours or overnight. remove from the fridge 30 minutes before baking. Sprinkle pecans over egg mixture. Combine butter and remaining sugar; drizzle over top. Bake uncovered at 400° for 25 minutes. Sprinkle with blueberries. Bake 10 minutes longer.

title: cream cheese beef dip
directions: Soak 2 tablespoons onion overnight in bourbon.
Combine cream cheese, beef, pickle relish, mayonnaise and the onion soaked in bourbon.
Mix well with fork.
Form into ball and pat chopped walnuts on top or, put in dip dish and serve with crackers.

title: meatballs
directions: Make into 1-inch meatballs.
Bake in 400° oven for 10 to 15 minutes.
Makes approximately 144 meatballs.
Can make 1/2 recipe, if desired, and these freeze very well after cooked.

title: holiday punch
directions: Heat slowly, stirring occasionally, approximately 15 minutes until hot.

title: boiled cookies
directions: Mix together and let boil 1 minute the sugar, cocoa, milk and butter.
Then add peanut butter, vanilla and oatmeal.
Mix well while warm and drop by teaspoons on cookie sheet lined with wax paper.
Chill.

title: man catching biscuits
directions: Mix dry ingredients, then cut in shortening, add liquids.

title: blueberry tea cake
directions: Sift together flour, baking powder and salt.
Cream butter. Gradually beat in sugar.
Add egg and milk; beat until smooth. Add dry ingredients.
Fold in blueberries (will be stiff).
Spread batter in greased and floured 8 or 9-inch pan.

title: italian fried chicken
directions: Dip chicken in beaten eggs and then roll in bread crumbs. Heat oil in frying pan to 370°.
Gradually add salad dressing. Brown on both sides.
Reduce heat to 300° and cook for 40 minutes. For crispness, raise heat to 370° for last 10 minutes of cooking time.
Serves 6.

title: mayonnaise biscuits
directions: Combine ingredients.
Drop into greased and floured muffin tins.
Bake in 450° oven until golden brown.

title: aioli sauce
directions: Sauce for seafood or beef.
Soak bread in milk and wring dry. Place all ingredients except olive oil in blender or processor. Blend until smooth, slowly adding oil.
Serves 4.

title: pumpkin squares(bake at 350~; 35 to 45 minutes)
directions: Combine oats, flour, nuts, butter and dry pudding mix.
Press into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix rest of ingredients in same bowl and pour over first mixture.
Bake until knife inserted in center comes out clean.
