Cool, cut in squares and top with whipped cream or ice cream.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Combine margarine, brown sugar and eggs.
Sift flour, baking soda, salt and cinnamon and add.
Stir in oats and chocolate chips. Refrigerate dough overnight preferably.
Drop by rounded tablespoonfuls onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° until cookies just start to turn brown on the bottom (about 15 to 20 minutes).
Do not let cookies overbake.
They can get very hard.

title: vegetable salad
directions: Drain all vegetables.
Add celery, onion, green pepper, and pimentos; toss all together.
In saucepan heat sugar, vinegar, and oil until sugar dissolves.
Cool; pour over vegetables and mix. This will keep for several weeks in refrigerator and can also be put in freezer.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Bake whole chicken.
Take all meat off and put in large pot. Mix in all other ingredients (except cheese and dinner rolls). Heat until bubbly.
Pour into ungreased casserole dish.
Top with grated cheese and cover with crescent rolls.
(Unroll dinner rolls and lay flat on top.)
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes (or until brown).

title: easy microwave enchiladas
directions: Fry chicken and onion in oil until onion is tender.
Mix in picante sauce.
Combine chili sauce and soup.
Spoon meat into tortillas.
Roll and place in microwave-safe baking dish.
Cover with sauce-soup mixture.

title: dinner in one dish
directions: Brown ground beef.
Pour off excess fat.
Place alternate layers of ground beef and fresh vegetables in a greased casserole dish in the order listed.
Add salt and pepper as needed.
Pour canned tomatoes over all.
Top with cheese slices; dot with margarine.
Cover casserole; bake for 1 1/2 hours at 350°, or until vegetables are done.
Serves 6.

title: chicken and water chestnut casserole
directions: Skin and cook chicken breasts in water with a few celery tops. Discard bones and celery tops.
Cut chicken in large pieces. Combine all except dressing mix and butter; place in lightly buttered 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Mix dressing with melted butter. Place on top of casserole.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Can be made a day or two ahead and topping added when ready to bake.

title: picante sauce
directions: Peel tomatoes and chop up fine. Add peppers (both kinds), onions, vinegar, salt, sugar and garlic.
Simmer over low heat for 25 minutes.
Stir in oregano, cumin and cayenne pepper.
Put in sterilized jars and water bath for 15 minutes in boiling water. Makes approximately 6 1/2 quarts.

title: mazetti
directions: Brown meat in large skillet.
Remove excess fat.
Add celery, onions and garlic with 1 tablespoon water.
Cover and steam until vegetables are tender.
Cook the noodles and add to beef mixture. Mix in all other ingredients except cheese.
Spread mixture in 2 1/2 or 3-quart casserole.
Top with cheese.
Put in a cold oven set at 350°.
Bake, uncovered, about 1 hour or until bubbling. (Freezes well.)

title: million dollar pie
directions: Mix and spread in graham cracker pie shells. Chill for 2 hours.
Makes 2 pies.

title: foil-wrapped chick
directions: Season all ingredients with salt, pepper, celery salt and McKay's chicken seasoning.
Wrap in foil and bake for 1/2 hour at 425°.

title: overnight tossed salad
directions: Mix all together, except lettuce, then refrigerate overnight. Before serving, add lettuce and mix well.

title: curried rice pilaf
directions: Heat oil in a large skillet over medium heat.
Add onion; saute until browned about 7 minutes.
Stir in curry powder and rice.
Add currants, cinnamon stick and broth.
Bring to boiling, lower heat, cover and simmer 10 minutes.

title: pepper steak
directions: Brown meat in oil. Add salt and pepper to taste.
Saute onion and peppers.
Add to meat. Add tomatoes and steak sauce. Cook slowly on top of stove for 1 hour in covered pan or until tender. Serve on bed of rice with hot sauce, if desired.

title: chicken and dumplings
directions: In large pot add; chicken, water, salt and pepper.
Cook chicken until tender, remove chicken, cool to touch.
Turn down heat to save broth.
Remove bones and cut chicken to desired size, set aside.
Open biscuits, tear or cut each piece into 4 pieces, set aside.
Turn heat back up on broth, to a slow boil.
Add bouillon to taste.
Add biscuits to broth all at once.
Stir easily but quickly to coat dumplings, stir occasionally.
Turn heat down and cook dumplings 5 to 10 minutes.
Add chicken and gently stir to mix together.
Serve hot.

title: carrot cake
directions: In large bowl, beat together eggs, sugar, oil and cinnamon. Set aside.
In separate bowl, sift together flour, soda and baking powder.
Add to egg mixture.
Stir in nuts, carrots and pineapple. Grease and flour two 9-inch pans and divide mixture between them. Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Cool and frost.

title: no baked cookies
directions: Mix cocoa, sugar, margarine, vanilla and milk in a saucepan and bring to a boil for 2 minutes.
Take from heat and add remaining ingredients.
Spoon out on waxed paper.
Cool and refrigerate.

title: pineapple casserole
directions: Drain pineapple, reserve liquid.
Put pineapple in casserole. Cook pineapple juice, sugar, flour and cheese until thick, stirring constantly.
Pour over pineapple and top with buttered Ritz crackers.
Bake 20 minutes at 350°.
This dish is great as a side dish with ham!

title: garlic potatoes
directions: Bring to a boil the milk and garlic cloves (smashed).
Line pan with butter (2 teaspoons).
Peel potatoes and slice thin. Layer potatoes, Swiss cheese, 1/2 of salt and pepper.
Dot with butter.
Repeat for second layer exactly, plus add Parmesan, then add milk mixture.
Cook, uncovered, at 400° for 45 minutes, or until done.

title: christmas pudding
directions: Cream together shortening and sugar; beat in thoroughly the eggs.
Mix cocoa with water; add to the above.
Add and beat until thoroughly mixed the flour, soda, salt, vanilla and buttermilk. Pour into loaf pan; bake at 300° for 35 to 45 minutes.
While cake is baking, prepare vanilla pudding according to directions.
When cake is done, cut it into squares immediately.
Put layer of cake in bottom and around sides of large serving dish.
Alternate layering of pudding and cake.
Cover with whipped topping. Decorate with maraschino cherries.

title: "dr. byrd's" banana cake
directions: Set oven to 350°.
Place all ingredients in 1 bowl.
Mix by hand with a large spoon.
Do not use a mixer or blender.
Bake in 2 loaf pans (greased and floured) or 1 tube pan (greased and floured) for 60 minutes.

title: fruit dip
directions: In small mixing bowl, whisk pudding, cinnamon and nutmeg; gradually add milk.
Beat at low speed until well blended.
Add sour cream.
Mix well.
Chill for 2 hours or overnight.

title: bob andy pie
directions: Mix together sugar, flour, cinnamon and cloves.
Add butter to mixture.
Add eggs and milk.
Beat the 3 egg whites; fold in mixture.
Pour into 2 large unbaked pie shells.
Bake in 350° oven until knife inserted comes out clean.
It will get brown before done.
Don't overbake.
Take out of oven when a little shaky.
If you have more mixture, put in center of pie before done.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli, according to package directions; drain.
Add cheese that has been cut in small pieces.
Cover and allow cheese to melt.

title: orange sally lunn bread
directions: Sprinkle yeast over warm water.
Stir until dissolved and set aside.
Scald milk in medium saucepan.
Add sugar, butter, orange rind and salt; stir until sugar is dissolved and butter melts. Cool.

title: hearty minestrone
directions: In large saucepot, combine oil, garlic, onion, ham, basil, oregano and pepper.
Cook over medium heat until onion is soft, stirring occasionally.
Add water, tomatoes, broth, celery, carrots, zucchini and potatoes.
Bring mixture to a boil over high heat; reduce heat and simmer for about 30 minutes.
Cut escarole into strips; add to soup with beans and pasta.
Cover and simmer for about 30 minutes, until pasta and vegetables are tender.
If desired, serve the soup topped with grated Parmesan cheese.

title: snickers apple salad
directions: Core and slice apples into bite size chunks.
Chop candy bars into small bite size chunks.
Add apples and candy chunks into Cool Whip.
Chill and serve.
Serve as a salad or dessert.

title: rhubarb pie
directions: Cut rhubarb in small pieces.
Add sugar and mix well.
Beat egg and blend with butter and flour. Add to rhubarb and mix well. Pour in unbaked crust.
Bake in hot oven at 400° for 10 minutes. Then lower heat to 350°, until filling is set.

title: grape-nuts roast
directions: Mix together all ingredients and bake at 375° for 45 minutes.

title: banana-carrot bread
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease loaf pan.
In large bowl, combine all ingredients, except nuts, with mixer at medium speed until well blended.
Stir in nuts. Spoon batter into prepared pan. Bake 55 to 60 minutes or until toothpick comes out clean.
Cool in pan 5 minutes, then turn out on wire rack.
Makes 1 large loaf.

title: pizza burgers
directions: Mix all together and make into patties.
Cook as you would burgers normally.
Top with Mozzarella cheese slices.
Makes approximately 8 burgers.

title: kielbasa bake
directions: Place cut up kielbasa into 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Combine pineapple, brown sugar and chili sauce and pour over kielbasa. Bake, uncovered, at 375° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: monkey bread
directions: Cut each biscuit in fourths.
Dip in cinnamon and sugar mixture.
It may take more cinnamon and sugar; if so, use comparable amounts.
Layer in Bundt or angel food cake pan.
Add chopped nuts on each layer.
Boil brown sugar and oleo.
Drizzle a little over each layer.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes or until done.
Cool at least 5 minutes before removing from pan.

title: mother-in-law cake
directions: Mix dry ingredients, then add eggs, milk, oil and vanilla. Beat well before adding hot water.
Batter will be very thin. Pour into greased or wax paper lined 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Slice cake into 1/2 lengthwise.
Place ice cream between two layers of cake.
Put in freezer until ready to serve.
Serve with hot fudge topping.

title: uncle don's chicken nuggets
directions: Cut chicken breast meat into small pieces and dip into a mixture of the flour, salt, white pepper, marjoram and nutmeg. Then dip into the egg and water. Then dip into the bread crumbs and Parmesan cheese. Fry in olive oil and margarine mixture. You will probably have to make larger quantities of everything. This is a very tasty dish.

title: baked spaghetti
directions: Generously grease a casserole dish with margarine.
Add macaroni, tomato juice, salt, pepper and sugar.
Stir.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes, uncovered.

title: corn casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes; sprinkle with cheese and return to oven until cheese is melted.

title: english pastry for meat pies
directions: Sift together flour, baking powder and salt.
Mix shortening and hot water together.
Add lemon juice and egg yolk.
Mix well and stir into flour mixture.
Press half of dough into pie plate. Fill with meat mixture.
Top with rest of dough.
Bake at 425° for 25 minutes.

title: easy herb drying
directions: Remove stems from herbs.
Rinse well and drain well.
Dry each variety separately.
Loosely pack one cup of leaves, then spread on a paper towel.
Place in microwave and cover herb with another towel.
Microwave on High for 2 minutes.
If desired, crumble. Store in airtight container.
(Empty spice and herb jars, well washed and dried, will work well.)

title: grapefruit bread pudding
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Spread one side of each bread slice with butter.
In 1 1/2-quart shallow baking dish, arrange bread so slices overlap, buttered-side down and sprinkle with raisins.
In medium bowl, beat together milk, grapefruit juice, eggs, 1/3 cup brown sugar and cinnamon until combined.
Pour over bread slices and let stand 30 minutes.
Set baking dish in pan of hot water. Place in oven for 45 to 60 minutes or until tip of knife comes out clean.

title: sweet and spicy meat loaf
directions: Mix together beef, salt, pepper, onions, egg, green pepper and cracker meal.
Combine tomato sauce, vinegar, mustard and brown sugar.
Mix until smooth.
Add 1/2 cup of mixture to meat; mix until absorbed.
Pour meat mixture into loaf pan (greased).
Spoon remaining tomato mixture on top.
Bake at 400° for 45 minutes, basting occasionally.

title: bojangle's biscuits
directions: Sift dry ingredients.
Cut in the shortening.
Add buttermilk. Turn on floured surface and knead dough to about 1/2-inch thick. Dust with flour.
Cut biscuits.
Bake at 450° for 12 minutes or until golden.
Brush with butter.

title: shrimp saute
directions: Cut up onions, bell pepper, mushrooms and garlic; saute in butter.
Add shrimp; cook 2 minutes.
Add remaining ingredients and cook 5 minutes.
Thicken with cornstarch.
Serves 2.

title: red beet salad (rooibeet slaai)
directions: Combine beets and onion in bowl.
Add other ingredients; mix well.

title: chili with beans
directions: Combine onion, bell pepper and oil; brown over medium heat. Add ground beef and brown.
Add remaining ingredients.
Simmer for 30 minutes.

title: tuna-zucchini-macaroni salad
directions: Mix ingredients together gently and chill. Serve on lettuce leaf with wedges of tomato.

title: raspberry poppy seed dressing
directions: Whip first four ingredients well.
Add oil in a slow, steady stream while whipping.
Add poppy seed.
Taste to check vinegar to oil ratio.
Add one or the other to desired taste.
Makes about 2 cups.

title: caramel cake
directions: 1) Heat oven to 350 degrees. Grease a 10 cup bundt pan. Prepare cake mix according to package directions, using pound - cake variation (add instant pudding and an extra egg). Stir in toffee bits and pour evenly into pan, Bake 55 to 65 minutes, cool 10 minutes in pan. Invert cake onto a wire rack and cool completely.

title: pork chop onion rice bake
directions: Brown chops in fat.
Spread rice in bottom of rectangular baking dish (13 x 9 x 2-inch).
Reserve part of seasoning from onion soup mix and sprinkle remaining seasoning and bits of onion over rice.
Add enough hot water to mushroom soup to make 3 cups liquid.
Place pimentos over rice, then pour in liquid.
Arrange brown chops on top and sprinkle small amount of onion soup mixture.
Cover tightly with foil and bake at 350° for 1 hour. Remove foil and bake 10 minutes longer.

title: april's pie crust
directions: In a large bowl, combine flour, butter, shortening and salt until mixture resembles meal.
Add 2 tablespoons ice water, tossing mixture until water is incorporated.
Add additional ice water, if necessary, to form a dough.
Form dough into a ball; dust with flour and chill for 1 hour.
Makes one 9-inch crust.

title: icebox cherry pie
directions: Put Eagle Brand milk in a bowl.
Add lemon juice and cherries; stir well.
Fold in whipped cream and nuts.
Pour into a graham cracker crust.
Chill 2 hours.
Very rich, but delicious!

title: sesame chicken wings
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Coat 9 x 13-inch pan with nonstick cooking spray.
In pan, mix soy sauce, sherry, ginger, sesame oil and 2 tablespoons syrup.
Add wings; turn to coat.
Bake 45 minutes, basting often.
Add water if gets too dry.
Brush wings with 2 tablespoons syrup; sprinkle with seed.
Bake 15 minutes longer.

title: summer antipasto
directions: Arrange alternately slices of tomato and cheese on plate.
Top with your favorite Italian dressing.

title: 5 pounds can't fail fudge
directions: Melt margarine in a large pan.
Add sugar and milk.
Bring to a boil, after it reaches a rolling boil, start timing and boil 6 minutes.
Remove from heat and add
marshmallows and chocolate chips.
Beat until all melts.
Add nuts.
Pour into a buttered jelly roll pan.
Cut into squares.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Saut sausage and drain well. Beat eggs, milk and mustard. Add sausage and cheese and remaining ingredients. Cover bottom of 9 x 13 baking dish with bread pieces. Pour egg and sausage mixture over bread. Refrigerate overnight. Bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes. Serve hot.

title: taco dip
directions: Layer bean dip 1st in dish and guacamole dip 2nd.
Mix sour cream, taco seasoning and mayo together and layer 3rd.
Top with remaining ingredients.
Chill.
Serve with taco or corn chips.

title: chocolate oatmeal cookies
directions: Boil sugar, cocoa, butter and milk for 1 minute in cast-iron frying pan.
Remove from heat.
Add remaining ingredients; mix well.
Drop onto wax paper.

title: punch bowl cake
directions: Crumble 1/3 of cake into bottom of punch bowl; add a layer of pudding, pie filling, pineapple, whipped topping and pecans. Repeat until all ingredients are gone, ending with whipped topping and pecans.
Keep chilled until ready to serve.
Yields 20 to 25 servings.

title: booze dogs
directions: Combine
all ingredients except hot dogs and boil until it forms a syrup.
Add hot dogs and simmer slowly for 2 hours. Serve hot.

title: chili con queso
directions: Microwave both cheeses and
canned milk until bubbly on High, stirring often.
Add
other
ingredients
and
microwave until smooth and creamy.	Serve with tortilla chips as a dip.

title: copper carrot pennies
directions: Boil carrots in salt water until tender; cool.
Drain.
Mix all other ingredients.
Pour over carrots and chill.

title: breakfast souffle
directions: Cook sausage over medium heat until done, stirring to a crumble.
Drain well and set aside.
Combine remaining ingredients in large mixing bowl.
Last, add sausage.

title: cherry supreme
directions: Break cake into small pieces.
Set aside.
Whip vanilla pudding with milk.
Combine Cool Whip and pudding with cake.
Put mixture in a glass bowl.
Top with pie filling.

title: asparagus-lima casserole
directions: Cook limas slightly less than normal time; drain.
Place half of limas in a 1 1/2-quart buttered casserole.
Add can of asparagus (drained) on top of limas.
Add half of the water chestnuts.
Add half of the mushroom soup and sprinkle with half of the cheese.
Repeat layers.
Top with buttered crumbs and bake at 350° for about 40 minutes.
Serves 4.

title: gourmet oriental chicken
directions: Cook rice according to package directions.
Add chicken on top, then add vegetables on top of the chicken.
Slice mushrooms and add with other vegetables.
Simmer until liquid from rice is absorbed.
This is attractively prepared in an au gratin pan or Corning type serving dish.
(Real good and easy.)

title: cheese and corn chowder
directions: In saucepan, combine first 5 ingredients.
Bring to a boil. Reduce heat, cover and simmer until potatoes are tender.
Stir in 2 1/2 cups milk, then the corn.

title: flour tortilla
directions: Mix flour, salt and baking powder in very large mixing bowl. With hands, break in Crisco until fine.
Add water a little at a time until a soft, non sticky dough is formed.
Knead several times; let sit 5 to 10 minutes.
Make dough balls; roll each dough ball out.
(Size will depend on size of your ball).
Cook on an ungreased griddle or Teflon skillet (electric skillets work very well).
Skillet should be on medium high.
Cook them as you roll them or they will dry out.
Cook first side about 20 seconds, turn and cook other side 30 to 40 seconds, turn to original side and finish cooking about 30 seconds.
Only turn 3 times or tortillas will be hard.
Makes about 60 tortillas.
I divide into dozens, wrap in foil, store in baggie and freeze.
They are ready to use just thaw at room temperature.
To warm just heat quickly on skillet.
Microwaving to warm temperature works if you put between paper towels otherwise they become dry and "rubbery".

title: squash boats
directions: Boil yellow crookneck squash (cut off ends) until tender. Boil red-skin potatoes.
Cut squash in half lengthwise.
Scoop out pulp.
Add potatoes, butter, salt, pepper, potato toppers and Cheez Whiz.
Mix with a fork.
Stuff mixture into squash shells. Sprinkle with paprika and bake at 325° for 15 minutes.

title: stuffed meat roll
directions: With rolling pin or hand rinsed in water, flatten beef to 12 x 8-inch rectangle.
Mix remaining ingredients well.
Spread lengthwise down center of beef.
Roll up jelly fashion and place, seam side down, in greased shallow pan.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for 30 minutes or until done.
Let stand for 10 minutes before slicing.
Serves 4 to 5.

title: 7th grade peanut butter snacks
directions: Blend together over medium heat:
sugar, peanut butter and syrup until mixture is thin.
Remove from heat.
Stir in corn flakes.
Mix until flakes are well coated with the peanut butter mixture.
Drop by teaspoonfuls on wax paper.
Cool 10 minutes.

title: sausage balls
directions: Combine all ingredients by hand.
Shape into balls.
Place on ungreased baking sheet.
Bake at 350° for about 15 minutes.

title: candied yams
directions: Boil sweet potatoes in jackets.
When done, slice and place in bowl.
Combine butter, sugars, pineapple, vanilla flavor together in pot.
Cook until syrupy.
Sprinkle sliced potatoes with nutmeg. Pour syrup over sliced sweet potatoes.
Bake in 350° to 375° oven until candied.

title: orange slice cookies
directions: Cut candy orange slices into small pieces in 1/2 cup flour. Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs, salt and baking powder to sifted flour.
Add vanilla and orange slices.
Drop from spoon onto greased cooking sheet.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: lemon cake deluxe
directions: Empty cake mix into large bowl; add gelatin and water.
Beat vigorously for 5 minutes.
Add eggs and beat again.
Add oil and mix well.
Bake in 9 x 13 pan until cake shrinks from sides.
As soon as cake comes out of oven, insert table fork completely into cake approximately every inch.
Pour glaze over cake while still hot.

title: easy cheese cake
directions: Beat eggs until thick and lemon colored.
Gradually add sugar, then softened cream cheese.
Beat until smooth and creamy.
Grease glass pie pan and fill.
Bake in 350° oven for 20 to 25 minutes. Cool for 1/2 hour.

title: yellow angel cake
directions: Beat egg yolks real fluffy, then beat in sugar, beating well as added.
Then beat in water, vanilla and lemon extract, then add flour sifted with baking powder and salt.
Put in angel food cake pan.
Bake at 375° for 30 to 35 minutes or until done.
Cool as for angel food cake.

title: white fruit cake
directions: Melt butter; blend in sugar.
Add beaten eggs and mix well. Add 2 cups flour and baking powder.
Mix in lemon extract.
Cut fruit up and pour 2 cups flour over; coat real good.
Fold into your batter.
Bake at 300° for 1 1/2 hours, then at 350° for about 30 minutes.

title: spinach souffle(serves 12)
directions: Cook spinach and drain.
Add sour cream and onion soup.
Brown sesame seed in 1/4 pound butter or margarine.
Combine both mixtures and bake in uncovered casserole at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: chocolate pound cake(a great make ahead dessert)
directions: Mix dry ingredients together and set aside.
Cream butter and shortening.
Add sugar and mix well.
Add eggs and half of dry ingredients, then add milk and beat well.
Add remainder of dry ingredients and beat well.
Add vanilla and continue to beat well. Pour into ungreased tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 60 to 70 minutes. Allow cake to cool for about an hour before removing from pan. Sprinkle with confectioners sugar, if desired.
Will keep well in freezer
or for 1 to 1 1/2 weeks, wrapped well, in the refrigerator.

title: monkey bread
directions: Combine brown sugar, sugar and cinnamon.
Drop in biscuits. Stir and put into Bundt pan.
Pour margarine over.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.

title: no cook peanut butter fudge
directions: Melt butter and peanut butter together.
Mix confectioners sugar and work together until desired thickness is reached.
Pack into dish and refrigerate for about 1 hour before cutting into desired number of pieces.

title: canned apple pie mix
directions: Mix and cook until thick and bubbly.
Slice apples and place into 7 quart jars.
Pour mix over the apples; seal and cook in hot water bath for 20 minutes or pressure at 10 pounds pressure for 5 or 10 minutes.

title: spaghetti salad
directions: Break spaghetti into 3 pieces.
Drop into boiling water.
Cool and drain.
Add remaining ingredients.
Mix well.
Refrigerate overnight before serving.

title: chocolate crunch brownies
directions: In a mixing bowl, cream butter and sugar; add eggs and mix. Stir in cocoa, flour, vanilla and salt.
Spread in a greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Cool.
Spread Marshmallow Creme over top.
In a small saucepan, melt peanut butter and chocolate chips over low heat, stirring constantly. Remove from the heat; stir in cereal.
Spread over marshmallow layer.
Chill before cutting.
Store in the refrigerator.
Yields 3 dozen.

title: super seafood salad
directions: Cut Crab Delights in half or shred.
Combine with mayonnaise, celery and onion.
Refrigerate until ready to use.
Serve with crackers.

title: whacky cake
directions: Mix well dry ingredients (flour, sugar and cocoa) and make 3 holes (1 for the oil, 1 for the vinegar and 1 for vanilla).
Pour all water over entire ingredients.
Beat until smooth.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: gourmet chicken breasts
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients and pour over chicken breasts. Sprinkle with paprika.
Bake 1 1/4 hours at 350°.
Serve sauce over noodles or rice as well as chicken.

title: sour red cherry pie
directions: Combine sugar, salt, 1/4 cup cherry juice and food color in a saucepan.
Cook to a rolling boil.
Add cherries and butter.
Cook 2 minutes.
Make a smooth paste of cornstarch and 1/4 cup cherry juice.
Add this to cherry mixture and stir well until thickened. Cool before adding to pie shell.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Debone	chicken
and
cut
into
bite-size pieces.
Mix together
the following:
chicken, soup, sour cream, broth and dressing.
Place in buttered casserole and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: french onion soup
directions: Melt butter in a large saucepan.
Add onions; cook until tender and golden brown.
Add broth, water, Worcestershire sauce, onion powder, garlic powder, Accent and pepper.
Bring just to a boil.
Immediately reduce heat; cover and cook for 45 minutes.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix with hands.
Roll into ball and chill.
Then roll in 1/2 cup chopped nuts.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix this together thoroughly.
Use as dip for crackers.

title: pierogi
directions: Combine all ingredients in large bowl.
Knead until smooth and elastic.
Separate into 4 balls.
Roll out on floured board to 1/8-inch thickness.
Cut into 2-inch squares.
Fill with desired filling and pinch edges to seal.
Drop pierogi into boiling water and boil until pierogi rises to the top.
Remove with strainer. Good to fry in butter.
You can freeze pierogis and use as you want.

title: pudding delightroswell, new mexico
directions: Cut oleo into flour as for pie crust.
Add pecans.
Press into bottom of 9 X 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Cool.

title: croutons
directions: Trim crusts off of bread.
Butter and salt on
both sides. Cut in cubes.
Bake on cookie sheet for 20 to 30 minutes or until brown in 350° oven.

title: spinach squares
directions: Melt butter in 9 x 13-inch pan.
In mixing bowl, beat eggs, milk and then dry ingredients.
Stir in cheese and spinach. Spread mixture in pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Cool 20 minutes, then cut into 1 1/2-inch squares for appetizers or 4-inch squares for luncheon dish.
Serve at room temperature.

title: ground meat and potato casserole
directions: Fry potatoes in Pam slowly for 10 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Season with a little salt and pepper.
Put potatoes in a shallow 1 1/2-quart baking dish.

In same skillet you cooked the potatoes, cook the ground beef or turkey and onion until the meat loses its pinkish color, breaking it up with a fork and drain. Put the meat mixture on top of the potatoes.
Cover with spaghetti sauce.
Bake in a preheated 350° oven for about 45 minutes.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: dream bars
directions: Mix the first 4 ingredients like pie dough and pat in a 9 x 12-inch pan.
Bake 15 minutes at 350°.

title: easy dip
directions: In a microwavable bowl cut Velveeta into 2-inch cubes.
Pour Ro-Tel tomatoes over cut cheese.
Microwave on High for 3 minutes. Stir and microwave for another 3 minutes or until completely melted and bubbly.

title: jane's apricot cream salad
directions: Prepare jello with 1 cup boiling water and 2 cups juice drained from apricots and pineapple.
Save remaining juice.
Add chopped apricots and crushed pineapple. Pour in 9 x 13-inch Pyrex and chill until firm.
Cook sugar, flour, slightly beaten egg, remaining juice and margarine until thick.
Cool and fold in Dream Whip.
Spread on jello and sprinkle with grated cheese.

title: no fail pie crust
directions: Mix dry ingredients. Add oil and water. Mix. Roll out on floured board to size.

title: mom's parmesan yard bird(chicken)
directions: Wash chicken and pat dry.
Salt and pepper it.
Fill a baggy with eggs and water.
Shake chicken in the baggy (1 piece at a time).
Fill another baggy with flour and cheese.
Shake chicken in the baggy (1 piece at a time).
Pam the pan; place the chicken in the pan and dot butter.
Bake about an hour at 375°, turning once after 1/2 hour.

title: vegetable pizza
directions: Spread crescent rolls on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 5 to 7 minutes; cool.
Spread topping over crust; add vegetables.
Top with grated cheese (Cheddar or whatever you prefer).
Let set in refrigerator overnight.

title: friendship tea
directions: Combine all ingredients.
To serve, add 1 Tbsp. mix to a cup of hot water.

title: mushroom sauce
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Heat over low heat for 5 minutes. Pour over meat that has been browned and bake according to meat. This sauce goes well with beef or chicken.

title: overnight french toast
directions: Put in greased baking dish and top with prepared bread. Sprinkle with cinnamon and sugar and bake for 20 to 25 minutes in 450° oven.

title: frosted creams
directions: Cream well sugar, eggs and shortening.
Sift dry ingredients together.
With creamed mixture in bowl, alternately add dry ingredients and the coffee, molasses and hot water mixture until smooth.
Bake in 10 x 14-inch pan for 15 minutes at 375°.
Cool and frost with thin butter icing.

title: salmon patties
directions: Clean and debone salmon.
Mash salmon together with meal, flour and black pepper.
Add mayonnaise until desired thickness. Fry in nonstick pan 20 to 25 minutes or until done.

title: fresh fig cake
directions: Cream shortening, sugar and eggs.
Add dry ingredients and mashed figs.
Mix well; add nuts.
Pour into well-greased and floured tube pan.
Bake 1 hour more or less.
Do not cut for at least 24 hours.
This freezes well.

title: punch
directions: Mix in gallon container.
Fill with water.
May make up other half package Kool-Aid.
Freeze in ice tray and add to punch.

title: lemon bars
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients until crumbly; press into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Beat the next 5 ingredients for 2 minutes.
Pour over crust and bake at 350° for another 20 to 25 minutes.

title: virgie's german chocolate pralines
directions: In thick walled pot over medium heat, melt sugar, evaporated milk, butter, salt and chocolate.
Add coconut and pecans.
Cook for 18 to 20 minutes over medium heat to low heat.
Remove from heat.
Add vanilla extract.
Cool slightly.
Scoop onto waxed paper laid over paper towels with a small ice cream scoop.
Makes 28 to 32 pralines depending on size of scoop.
For firmer pralines, decrease butter by 1/2 stick.

title: crock-pot brisket
directions: Excluding brisket, mix all ingredients together in a large bowl.
Place brisket in marinade.
Cover and put into the refrigerator.
Marinate overnight.
The next morning, before going to school, pour all of the marinade in the crock-pot and place the brisket in the crock-pot.
Turn the crock-pot on low and cook approximately 8 hours or until you get home.
The brisket should fall apart.
It's yummy!

title: chili con carne
directions: Saute onions and peppers in oil until tender.
Add ground chuck and just brown it.
Add tomato sauce, spices, salt and pepper to taste.
(You may want to increase the quantity of garlic powder and chili powder if you like spicy chili).
Simmer over low heat for 1 hour.
Add kidney beans and continue to simmer for another 30 minutes.
Add cheese and stir gently until melted.

title: hot cheese ball
directions: Grate cheese.
Combine all ingredients.
Form into a ball. Roll in chopped nuts if desired.
The longer this is refrigerated, the spicier it will become.

title: chicken pie
directions: Remove chicken from bones.
Place in buttered casserole.
Pour broth and soup over chicken.
Mix margarine, flour and milk. Spoon over other ingredients.
Bake at 400° for 35 to 40 minutes or until brown.

title: saucy crab spread
directions: Using a food processor or chopper, chop crabmeat until minced. Set aside.
Slice cream cheese lengthwise and lay the halves down side by side on a serving dish or tray.
Using a spoon, smooth the "seam" between the cream cheese halves and along the entire outer edge to blend down to the serving dish.
Next, take the reserved crabmeat and spread it generously over the cream cheese, being sure to press it firmly and evenly.
Pour the seafood sauce directly over the center of the "spread" allowing the sauce to drizzle toward the corners.
Garnish top of spread with the reserved crab strips.
Place "Toasteds" all around and it's ready to serve!
Be sure to set out plenty of table knives for your guests.
Everyone will "crowd" this appetizer!

title: cornmeal cookies
directions: Mix margarine and sugar in a large bowl.
Add egg and beat well.
Add rest of ingredients and mix well.
Drop dough from a teaspoon on greased baking pan.
Bake at 350° for about 15 minutes until lightly brown.
Makes 3 dozen.

title: special potato salad
directions: Combine all ingredients; blend well.
Add dressing as directed on package last.
Chill well.

title: lone star steak sauce
directions: In a saucepan combine all ingredients, heat until butter melts and the mixture is smooth.

title: some more hor d'oeuvres
directions: Combine all ingredients except crackers and mix well.
Top each cracker with 1 teaspoon mix and place on paper towel lined plate.
Microwave for 60 seconds; turn plate often to melt cheese.

title: easy coconut pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour into pie shells.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes, then turn down to 325° for 45 to 60 minutes.

title: brownie fudge nut pie
directions: Coarsely chop 1 1/2 cups nuts.
In medium saucepan, over low heat, stir condensed milk, margarine and cocoa until margarine melts and mixture is warm; remove from heat.
Stir in eggs, flour, vanilla and chopped nuts; pour into prepared crust.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes, or until center is firm.

title: fun rum balls
directions: In large bowl, combine all ingredients (except powdered sugar); stir until well blended.
Shape into balls.
Roll in powdered sugar.
Store rum balls in tightly covered container.

title: lemon buttermilk pound cake
directions: Cream shortening and margarine together, blending well.
Add sugar gradually and cream until light and fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Sift flour and salt together and add alternately with buttermilk, mixing well.
Add lemon extract and blend with mixer at lowest speed.
Add soda and hot water.
Pour into spout pan.
Bake for 1 hour and 15 minutes at 325°.

title: cocoa mix
directions: Mix well and store in airtight container. Use 1/3 cup mix to 1 cup hot water.

title: squash quiche pie
directions: Mix squash, onion, salt and pepper; set aside.
In second bowl, beat eggs, then add oil, Bisquick, cheese and parsley; mix well.
Add squash mixture; mix thoroughly.
Pour into greased 8 x 8-inch dish and bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes, until golden brown and set in middle.
Serve while hot.

title: celery seed bread
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients, stirring well to blend.
Spread on cut sides of each roll.
Place on baking sheet.
Broil until golden brown.
Yields 4 servings.

title: sombrero dip
directions: Brown meat and 1/4 cup onion in skillet.
Place catsup, chili powder, salt and beans in blender.
Turn blender on high for 30 seconds.
Add mixture to meat and heat.
Garnish with cheese, 1/4 cup onion and the olives.
Makes 1 1/2 cups.
Serve hot as a dip for corn chips.

title: blender egg custard
directions: Mix all ingredients in order listed in blender.
Mix for 18 to 20 seconds.
Pour into a well-greased 9-inch or 10-inch pie plate. Bake at 300° for approximately 40 minutes.

title: spaghetti sauce
directions: Put meat in skillet and cook until done.
Drain off fat.
Add onion, celery and green pepper.
Cook slowly until done.
Add other ingredients and simmer for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: taco salad
directions: Cook meat and seasoning mix as directed.
Cool.
Mix all vegetables and cheese together.
Add chips and dressing just before serving.
Yum!

title: "papa's seafood gumbo"
directions: Make roux with flour and butter.
Add garlic, onions, bell pepper and celery.
Cover and cook until transparent.
Add water, tomato sauce and okra.
Simmer until done.
Add seasoning, shrimp, oysters and crab.
Simmer 2 hours and serve over rice.

title: hot crab dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes. Serve with crackers.

title: applesauce cake
directions: Cover raisins, nuts and fruit with flour to keep from sinking to bottom of pan.
Mix all ingredients together, adding soda last. Bake in a greased and floured tube pan at 300° for 2 1/2 hours. Do not open oven door.
Remove from pan when cooled.

title: cheese ball
directions: Beat cheeses until fluffy.
Beat in onion and Worcestershire sauce.
Cover and chill 3 to 4 hours.
Mold cheese in a large ball.
Roll in parsley or pecans.
I usually use pecans.

title: hawaiian tea
directions: Combine, add more tea, if needed, to make 1 gallon.

title: jambalaya
directions: Cook chicken breasts with fat and skin.
Use enough water to cook for broth needed.
Debone, remove skin and fat and cut in small chunks.
Cut sausage in thin slices.

title: fresh coconut cake
directions: Cream the shortening and gradually add sugar; beat until light and fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Combine flour, baking powder and salt; add to creamed mixture alternately with milk, beginning and ending with flour mixture.
Stir in vanilla.
Pour batter into 2 greased and floured 9-inch round cake pans.
Bake at 375° for 20 to 25 minutes or until wooden pick inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool in pans 10 minutes.
Remove from pans and cool completely.
Split cake layers in half horizontally to make 4 layers.
Spread Custard Filling between layers and spread top and sides with Snow Peak Frosting.
Sprinkle with coconut.
Yields one 4-layer cake.

title: impossible french apple pie
directions: Heat oven to 325°.
Grease a 10 x 1/2-inch pie plate. Mix apples, cinnamon and nutmeg. Turn into plate.
Beat sugar, milk, baking mix, eggs and margarine until smooth, 15 seconds in blender on high or 1 minute with hand beater.
Pour into plate. Sprinkle with Streusel.
Bake until knife inserted in center comes out clean, 55 to 60 minutes.
Makes 8 servings.

title: carrot cake
directions: Cream oil, sugar and add egg yolks beaten with water.
Add grated carrots.
Sift dry ingredients together and add to Wesson oil mixture.
Fold in stiffly beaten egg whites.
Bake in three layer pans at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: hot mama dip
directions: Brown sausage and hamburger and drain.
In crock-pot, melt cheeses.
Add meat, soup, tomatoes, green chilies and onions.
Mix well and serve hot.

title: extra crunchy tuna salad
directions: Combine all ingredients in medium mixing bowl, mix well.
Chill till time to serve.

title: stuffed onions
directions: Cut off root ends of onions.
Peel, rinse and cut off 1/2-inch slice from top of each.
Put onions in boiling salted water to cover in a large saucepan. Cook 10 to 15 minutes or until onions are slightly tender. Drain well and cool.

title: chocolate flavored coffee creamer
directions: Mix together. Use 2 to 3 heaping teaspoonfuls per cup of coffee. Store in airtight container.

title: shrimp arnaud
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Add sauce to boiled, peeled and cooled shrimp; blend until well coated.
Refrigerate, covered, at least 45 minutes.
Serve on shredded lettuce, topped with a tomato slice and shrimp with sauce (6 or 8 shrimp if good sized, about 40 to 50 count).
Serves 6 to 8.

title: onion-cheese french bread
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients; mix well.
Slice bread in half lengthwise.
Spread cheese mixture on bread.
Broil 6 inches from heat 2 minutes or until bubbly.

title: old fashioned rice pudding
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
In medium mixing bowl, combine milk, honey, egg whites, vanilla and cinnamon.
Beat with rotary beater or hand mixer until smooth.
Stir in rice, raisins and dates. Spoon mixture into custard cups.
Sprinkle lightly with nutmeg.

title: apricot jello salad
directions: Dissolve jello in 2 cups boiling water.
Boil pineapple, sugar and 1 cup hot water.
Mix the jello and pineapple mixture together.
Cool and refrigerate until partially jelled.
Whip together Dream Whip and cream cheese.
Blend with celery and nuts (if desired).
Fold into partially jelled jello and refrigerate overnight.

title: danish puff pastry
directions: Bring water and margarine to rolling boil.
Remove from heat and add almond flavoring.
Add flour, beating until smooth and stiff.
Add eggs one at a time, beating well after each addition. Spread this on top of crust, being sure to spread to edge.
Bake 50 minutes at 350°.
Cool.
Frost with thin icing.
Cut crosswise in 2-inch strips.

title: two flavor fudge
directions: In a saucepan, combine the brown sugar, granulated sugar, milk and oleo.
Bring to a full boil over moderate heat, stirring frequently.
Boil for 15 minutes.
Remove from heat, add the Marshmallow Creme, butterscotch morsels and the chocolate morsels, stir until morsels are melted and mixture is smooth.
Blend in the vanilla and walnuts.
Pour into a greased 9-inch square pan. Chill until firm.
Yield:
about 2 1/2 pounds.

title: no bake rice pudding
directions: Place rice in saucepan.
Cover with one inch of water.
Bring to a boil and simmer rice until it absorbs water.
Add 1 3/4 quarts milk and cook slowly until rice is tender.
Mix remaining ingredients in bowl.
Add to rice mixture.
Cook until thick.
Use a wire whisk vigorously, it makes it creamy.
Add raisins.
Be very careful.
Do not cook fast, it will scorch and burn.

title: impossible bacon pie
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Lightly grease a 10-inch pie plate. Sprinkle bacon, cheese and onion into pie plate.
Beat remaining ingredients together until smooth.
Pour into pie plate.
Bake until golden brown and knife inserted in center comes out clean (35 to 40 minutes).
Let stand for 5 minutes before cutting. Makes 6 servings.

title: onion soup(this soup won't make you cry.)
directions: In the top of a double boiler, put in butter, onions and celery, then stir.
Cook 5 minutes.
Stir in flour, milk, salt and pepper.
Cook for 15 minutes, then serve hot with croutons. Serves 4.
(Makes 4 cups.)

title: pumpkin bars
directions: Mix together eggs, oil, sugar and pumpkin.
Add flour, salt, baking powder, soda and cinnamon.
Put in ungreased 15 1/2 x 10 1/2 x 1-inch pan.
Bake 25 minutes at 350°.
Cool and ice.

title: country kitchen minestrone soup
directions: Place beans (kidney and peas) and vegetable mixture in large cooking pot. Add 5 cups water; bring to boil. Cover and simmer 2 hours until beans are tender. Stir frequently. Remove skin from sausage; break into small pieces. Brown in skillet. To cooking pot, add bouillon cubes, seasoning spices, 7 cups of water, tomatoes and coked sausage. Bring to boil; simmer 30 minutes. Add macaroni. Simmer 30 more minutes. Add salt and pepper to taste. Stir frequently.

title: dream date bars
directions: Grease a 9-inch square pan. Blend butter, 1/4 cup brown sugar and 1 1/4 cups flour. Spread on bottom of pan. Bake at 325° for 20 minutes.

title: german casserole
directions: Combine the first 4 ingredients and form into 1-inch meatballs. Brown in skillet, then drain.

title: lasagna
directions: Boil water in a large pan.
Place lasagna noodles in with salt and oil (1/2 teaspoon).
Stir often to keep from sticking.
Brown beef and sausage.
Warm sauce.
Add cooked meat.
Simmer.
Mix together cottage cheese, Ricotta, Parmesan and 1/4 cup shredded mozzarella.
When noodles are lighter in color, they are done.

title: phyllis' sausage balls
directions: Mix all three ingredients.
Mixture will be dry.
Form in 1-inch balls and place on cookie sheet.
Bake in preheated 375° oven for about 15 minutes.

title: squash puppies
directions: Mix cornmeal, flour and soda.
Mash squash; mix with egg, onion and buttermilk.
Add to dry ingredients.
Drop by teaspoon into hot deep fat.

title: weight watchers strawberry ice cream
directions: Puree berries if desired.
Add sweetener.
Put cottage cheese and lemon juice in blender and liquify.
Mix this mixture with berries and beat until smooth with rotary beater.
Transfer to shallow container.
Cover with wax paper and freeze firm for 2 to 3 hours.
Makes 4 servings.

title: oatmeal pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together. Pour into unbaked pie shell. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: chicken and rice
directions: Place rice in the bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle onion soup mix over rice.
Season chicken and place in pan.
Frost chicken with cream of chicken soup.
Carefully pour 2 1/2 cups of water in pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 to 1 3/4 hours.

title: easy tomato soup
directions: In a large saucepan, break up tomatoes; sprinkle with baking soda.
Bring to a boil.
Add salt, pepper and milk; heat thoroughly.
Do not boil.

title: grandma's salad
directions: Mix lemon gelatin with 1 cup boiling water.
Set aside.
Heat 1 cup water (use pineapple juice if desired) to boiling; add marshmallows and cream cheese; cook until combined.
Stir in lemon gelatin and pineapple.
Remove from heat, let set.
Prepare dessert topping, fold into cheese mixture.
Pour into 9 x 12-inch pan. Prepare raspberry gelatin according to directions.
When lukewarm, pour over cream cheese and refrigerate until set.

title: banana split cake
directions: Mix graham cracker crumbs with one stick melted butter.
Press into bottom of glass container, 9 x 13-inch.
Beat sugar, 2 sticks of butter and eggs for 15 minutes on high.
Layer bananas, strawberries and pineapple.
Layer Cool Whip on top.
Sprinkle pecans on top and top with cherries.
Let stay in refrigerator for 48 hours.

title: divinity fudge(century-old recipe)
directions: Cook sugar, syrup, water, vinegar and salt to 262°.
Beat slowly into well beaten egg whites.
Add walnuts and vanilla. When it begins to thicken, drop by spoonfuls on heavy waxed paper. Pack fudge in airtight boxes or cans.

title: cheesecake
directions: Mix cheesecake mix and milk with blender until smooth.
Pour into graham cracker crust.
Refrigerate for an hour.

title: tapioca dessert
directions: Bring to boil pudding and water; cook 2 minutes.
Add orange jello.
Cool.
Drain oranges; cut in half.
Add pineapple and Cool Whip.
Fold together.

title: ham loaf
directions: Grind meats together.
Mix meat, milk crumbs and eggs together.
Place in 8 or 9-inch baking dish, flattened not in a loaf.
Combine remaining ingredients and heat until dissolved. Pour over meat.
Bake at 300° for 2 1/2 hours.

title: grandma's casserole
directions: Cook and brown hamburger meat in oil.
Add all other ingredients and heat mixture to boiling point.
Reduce heat and simmer 15 minutes.
Layer tomatoes, meat mixture and 1 package of uncooked wide lasagna noodles, alternating.
Top with Mozzarella cheese.
Make sure noodles are well covered by sauce.
Cover pan with aluminum foil and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Cut as you would lasagna.
Serves 6.

title: deep fried fish
directions: Heat oil (2 to 3-inches) in deep
fryer
or
kettle
to 375°. If fish fillets are large, cut
into
to 12 serving pieces. Mix flour, salt and pepper.
Coat
fish
with
flour mixture; dip into eggs, then coat with
bread
crumbs.
Fry in hot oil until golden brown, about 4
minutes.
Makes
10 to 12 servings.

title: baked corn
directions: Pour all ingredients in large bowl and let set 10 minutes before mixing.
Stir ingredients with spoon (do not use mixer) until mixed.
Pour into greased casserole and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: homemade oyster stew with eggplant
directions: Peel eggplant and cut into small pieces the size of peanuts. Put into a small boiler of water.
Cut onion into small pieces and add to boiler.
Boil for about 15 to 20 minutes, drain water.
Add the quart of sweet milk to onion and eggplant.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Add butter or margarine.
Heat mixture, but do not allow to boil.
Eat with crackers.

title: vegetable dip
directions: Mix all ingredients until creamy and serve with raw vegetables, chips, etc.

title: candied peanuts
directions: Dissolve sugar in water and heat at medium heat.
Pour in peanuts and stir constantly.
Stir until all mixture has disappeared.
Spread peanuts on baking pan (do not grease pan). Put peanuts in oven at 300° for 25 minutes.

title: cranberry jello salad
directions: Mix raspberry Jell-O and boiling water.
Let set in refrigerator until very lightly set.
Then add sherbet (mix in well); add 1 can whole cranberry sauce (mashed).
Put in ring mold.
Cover with chopped walnuts.
Serve on bed of lettuce.

title: e-z chicken pie
directions: Pour 1 can chicken and 1 can chicken a la king into 2 pie shells.
Use other two pie shells as the top crusts.
Bake, following directions for browning the crust.

title: mama's cheese balls(recipe originated with mrs. etma weeks, b. j.'s mother)
directions: Mix all except 1 cup of pecans.
Form a ball and roll in rest of nuts.
Refrigerate for 1 hour or overnight.

title: buffet potatoes
directions: Thaw potatoes for approximately 45 minutes.
Mix other ingredients, then add potatoes.
Pour into greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle with buttered bread crumbs.
Bake for 45 minutes at 350°.

title: milk gravy
directions: Melt the butter in the saucepan and add the flour gradually, letting it blend without browning in the least.
Add the milk and stir without stopping.
Add salt and pepper to taste and serve over fresh, hot biscuits or broiled fish.

title: heavenly hash
directions: Drain fruit and mix.
Add coconut and marshmallows.
Toss with sour cream until creamy.

title: tropical chicken salad
directions: Cook, dice and chill chicken.
Dice or cut with melon baller into balls the cantaloupe and honeydew melons.

title: a crazy crust pie
directions: Mix flour, baking powder, salt, sugar, eggs shortening and water. Blend well. Pour batter into pie pan. Combine pie filling and lemon juice. Pour into center of pan. Do NOT stir.
Bake at 400° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: tuna dinner
directions: Prepare macaroni and cheese dinner as directed.
Stir in soup and milk.
Gently stir in tuna.
Heat to serving temperature.

title: margarita pie
directions: Mix gelatin, 1/2 cup granulated sugar and salt in saucepan. In bowl, beat egg yolks and lime juice until foamy.
Add to gelatin mixture.
Cook over low heat, stirring until gelatin is dissolved, 3 to 5 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Stir in lime peel, tequila and Triple Sec.
Chill until thickened, but not firmly set.
In separate bowl, beat egg whites until stiff.
Slowly add 1/2 cup granulated sugar.
Fold into chilled gelatin mixture. Pour into pie shell.
Chill until set.
Whip cream until peaks form; add powdered sugar.
Top pie with cream.
Decorate with lime twists.

title: banana nut loaf
directions: Grease a 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan.
Beat butter, sugar and egg until fluffy.
Combine bananas and milk.
Sift flour, baking powder and baking soda onto wax paper.
Stir into sugar mixture alternately with banana-milk mixture.
Stir in nuts.
Turn into prepared pan.
Bake in 350° oven 1 hour.
Cool in pan.

title: zippy zucchini
directions: Saute onions in butter until lightly browned.
Add zucchini and tomato; stir in salad dressing mix.
Bring to a boil; reduce heat, cover and simmer for 10 minutes or until zucchini is tender. Makes 6 cups or 10 to 12 servings.

title: "dump" cake
directions: Grease a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Spread layers in pan in the above order.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: the very best wedding punch
directions: Freeze until slushy and serve.

title: otmer's too two barbecue
directions: Cook over low heat until done.

title: golden pound cake
directions: Make sure all ingredients are at room temperature.

title: chicken and dumplings
directions: Boil chicken in large Dutch oven with carrots, celery and onion and seasonings until chicken falls off of bones.
Remove all bones. Add 1 batch of Rich Biscuits (See Rich Biscuit recipe in bread section) using 1 cup of milk instead of 3/4 cup.
Drop by spoonfuls into broth.
Cook until balls float to top, looking fluffy.
Remove from heat and eat promptly.
(The dough forms its own thickening for the soup.)

title: natalie's meat loaf
directions: Mix together all ingredients.
Add more Wheaties if too wet. Form into a loaf.
Cover with remainder of tomato sauce.
Bake in microwave with probe to 160° or bake 1 1/2 hours in conventional oven at 350°.

title: hot spicy punch
directions: Tie together in cheesecloth (or put in large metal tea bag) tea leaves, stick cinnamon and cloves.
Submerge in boiling water; then remove bag.
Add sugar, fruit juices and cider.
Heat just to boiling, stirring.
Pour ginger ale into 2 gallon punch bowl; then pour in hot tea (a metal spoon in punch bowl will keep hot liquid from breaking it.)
Makes about 2 gallons.

title: dump cake
directions: Spray a 13 x 9-inch pan with Pam.
Dump fruit into pan and mix.
Sprinkle dry cake mix over top.
Sprinkle chopped nuts. Drizzle melted butter over top.
Bake at 350° for approximately 1 hour.

title: jewish coffee cake
directions: Beat cake mix, pudding mix, eggs, sour cream and vegetable oil together. Set aside.
In separate bowl, mix together sugar, cinnamon, cocoa and nuts.
Put half of batter in tube pan; sprinkle with half of topping mixture, then rest of batter and remaining topping.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: chili beans
directions: Brown hamburger in one pan.
Cook onions and peppers in another pan for 5 to 6 minutes.
Add all ingredients together, except beans.
Bring to boil.
Let simmer 1 hour and 45 minutes. Add beans and simmer 15 minutes more.

title: banana surprise
directions: Puree bananas in electric mixer, adding banana pudding mixture.
Place bananas in large saucepan, adding cookie crumbs, sugar, milk, cornstarch (mixed in milk) and pistachio pudding mixture.
Cook until mixture is thick enough to form small balls. Roll in graham cracker crumbs.
Makes two to three dozen balls.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Saute onion in margarine;
mix with liquid, soups and cheese to make sauce.
Cook broccoli by package directions.
Mix broccoli and rice/macaroni with sauce.
Bake in a greased casserole for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: funnel cakes
directions: Beat eggs with milk in medium bowl.
Stir in flour and sugar. Mix until smooth.
Let stand for 15 minutes.
Place about 1/2 cup of oil in a small frying pan and heat.
Cover the bottom of a funnel with your finger, then fill with 1/2 cup of the batter. Remove finger and let batter drop into oil in a spiral pattern. Fry to a golden brown.
Turn with slotted spoon and fry second side.
Drain on paper towels and sprinkle with powdered sugar. Yields 8 funnel cakes.

title: ham loaf
directions: Bake in moderate oven about 1 1/2 hours.

title: italian sweet pie
directions: Combine margarine, sugar, eggs and vanilla.
Add Ricotta; mix well.
Add whiskey to your own taste and mix.
Pour in pan.
Cook for 1 hour at 350°.
Let it set in oven for 1/2 hour more.
For best results, refrigerate overnight.

title: pineapple cheese ball
directions: Blend all ingredients except nuts together well (can use electric mixer).
Form into a ball and roll ball into chopped nuts.
Serve with crackers.

title: sauerkraut and sausage(crock-pot)
directions: Fry bacon bits until crisp; set aside.

title: pineapple cheese ball
directions: Soften cream cheese.
Gradually stir in pineapple, green pepper, onion, 1 cup of pecans and seasoned salt.
Form mixture into ball or log and roll into 1 cup of finely chopped pecans. Chill in refrigerator.
Serve with favorite crackers.

title: quick buttermilk biscuits
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Sift flour in bowl.
Add in Crisco, add milk and stir.
Roll out on floured board and cut.
Place in greased pan and bake 10 to 12 minutes.

title: caramel pie
directions: Combine beaten egg yolks, milk and salt and stir.
Place in a double boiler and add butter; melt and add combined flour and 3/4 cup of sugar.
Stir thoroughly and gradually add to heated mixture.
Allow this to reach a consistency where a spoon will leave an indention in the mixture when removed.
Remove from heat. In an aluminum skillet, caramelize 1 cup of sugar on high, stirring constantly.
Sugar is caramelized when all the granules have dissolved and turns color of old penny.
Do not burn. Quickly pour caramel mixture into thickened eggs.
Beat with mixer.
Add vanilla.
Pour into cooked pie crust.
Top with meringue.

title: heavenly vegetable casserole
directions: Mix the soups, vegetables, salt and pepper in a 13 x 9 baking dish. Sprinkle with bread crumbs and Parmesan cheese. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until the vegetables are tender. (I would boil the fresh veggies until desired tenderness first.) The top should be slightly browned.

title: broccoli supreme
directions: Prepare frozen broccoli as package directs, but cook only 5 minutes or cook fresh broccoli in boiling water until tender. Drain and put into greased 2-quart casserole.
Sprinkle grated cheese over broccoli.
Pour over top a mixture of milk and mushroom soup.
Bake 25 minutes uncovered.
Remove from oven and add onion rings.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes more or until golden brown. Makes 6 servings

title: peach pie
directions: Put peaches in raw pie crust.
Melt oleo, sugar and flour. Beat egg and mix with sugar mixture.
Pour in pie crust and bake at 375° until brown.

title: d j's fruit dip
directions: Combine the first 3 ingredients.
Microwave 1 1/2 to 2 minutes on 70% power or until it bubbles.
Stir and cook an additional 30 seconds on same power.
Add orange and vanilla extracts.
Cool to lukewarm.
Mix in topping and refrigerate.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Grease and flour 2 bread pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: fruit dip
directions: Soften cream cheese.
Mix Marshmallow Creme and Cool Whip. Add small amounts at a time.
Serve with fresh fruit.

title: sweet meatballs
directions: Mix together and set aside.

title: sour cream dressing for cole slaw
directions: Chill cabbage thoroughly; shred fine.
Add about 1/4 cup onion and 9 1/2 cups celery, chopped.
Mix all together lightly.

title: rum or bourbon balls
directions: Crush vanilla wafers with a rolling pin. Mix all ingredients together.
Shape into small balls about one-inch in diameter. Roll in confectioners sugar.
Makes about 4 dozen.

title: potato souffle
directions: Prepare potatoes, using package directions.
Add next 3 ingredients and beaten egg yolks.
Mix well.
Beat egg whites until stiff peaks form.
Fold into egg yolk mixture.
Turn into a 2-quart casserole.
Bake at 375° for 35 minutes.
Makes 6 servings.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients well.
Add shrimp and refrigerate 15 minutes.
Serve with crackers.

title: no cook fudge
directions: Line an 8 or 9-inch pan with foil.
Melt chocolate chips, 2 tablespoons butter, vanilla and milk.
Stir in salt.
Remove from heat.
Add nuts.
Spread in pan.
Melt marshmallows with 2 tablespoons butter.
Spoon over fudge.
Swirl with knife. Refrigerate 2 hours.
Store at room temperature.

title: ma sheffler's pigs in the blanket
directions: 1. Boil cabbage. As leafs become cooked remove from head and cut out main vein. The more leafs removed makes
more pigs. 2. In a large bowl mix rice, beef or turkey, garlic powder pepper, salt, and onion. Set aside. Slightly salt
inside of cabbage leaf. Place spoonful of rice mixture
in leaf. Fold leaf's left and right ears in and roll
top to bottom.
3. In roaster make bed of 1 can sauerkraut. Lay pigs on
bed. Layer 2nd can of sauerkraut on top of pigs. Spread

title: old fashion sweet coleslaw
directions: Combine cabbage and carrots in a large bowl.
Sprinkle with sugar, salt and pepper; toss gently.
Set in refrigerator for an hour, then add mayonnaise.
Cover and chill good before serving. Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: gelatin wigglers(servings:  12)
directions: Dissolve gelatine and Kool-Aid in hot apple juice and honey. Pour into molds or glass casserole dish.
Chill until set.

title: death by chocolate!
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Put pecans, chocolate chips and caramel topping into pie shell.
Beat until smooth the cream cheese, sour cream, sugar and vanilla.
Add 3 eggs and beat on low until just mixed.
Pour this mixture into pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until center is set.
Cool.
Dust with cocoa powder, if desired.

title: kid pleasing iced tea
directions: Place ice cubes in a 2-quart pitcher.
Add water to almost fill the pitcher.
Add lemon, cut into quarters, but not peeled. Add artificial sweetener and stir.
Refrigerate overnight; remove lemons and enjoy!
(Or leave lemons in and reuse them for the next pitcher!)

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix flour, sugar and margarine. Beat eggs and salt together and add to mixture. Add syrup; add pecans last. Bake at 350° for 55 minutes to 1 hour.

title: butter pecan cake
directions: Bake cake as per directions on box.
When cake is removed from oven, poke holes with the end of a spoon.
Drizzle the sweetened condensed milk on top of cake.
Sprinkle pecans (amount at your discretion) on the cake after all milk has been poured on cake. Top cake with Cool Whip; sprinkle with pecans and Heath bar pieces. Refrigerate.

title: frozen strawberry salad
directions: Mix the cream cheese and Cool Whip with mixer, then stir in the strawberries, bananas and pineapple.
Line 2 bread pans with wax paper and freeze.
Remove from freezer at least 15 minutes before serving.
Will keep 6 months in freezer.
Serves 16.

title: orange dry jello salad
directions: Drain oranges and pineapple well.
In mixing bowl, mix the oranges and pineapple.
Sprinkle the dry jello over fruit.
Stir well.
Fold in cottage cheese.
Last, fold in Cool Whip.
Let chill until very cool.
Do not use crushed pineapple.

title: pizza-style seafood dip
directions: Spread cream cheese evenly on a dinner plate.
Spread cocktail sauce over the cream cheese.
Top with small shrimp or crab. Serve with party crackers.

title: hornet's nest cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Cook pudding with 2 cups milk and cool slightly; stir in well with the yellow cake mix. Add in the butterscotch chips and nuts. Pour into 9 x 13-inch greased pan and bake for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: eclair cake
directions: Butter a 9 x 11-inch pan.
Line with whole graham crackers. Mix pudding and milk; beat 2 minutes at medium speed.
Blend in Cool Whip.
Pour 1/2 mixture over the crackers.
Put another layer of crackers.
Pour remaining pudding mix and finish with another layer of crackers.
Refrigerate 2 hours or overnight.
Frost. Refrigerate another 24 hours.

title: tuna spread
directions: Let cream cheese soften to room temperature.
Mash tuna into tiny pieces and add to cream cheese.
Chop onion into tiny pieces and add to mixture according to individual taste.
Add Texas Pete to taste.
Mix well and serve on crackers.

title: double peanut cookie
directions: Thoroughly cream together first five ingredients.
Beat in peanut butter.
Sift together flour and soda.
Blend into creamed mixture.
Stir in peanuts.
Shape dough into balls and place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Flatten with glass dipped in granulated sugar.
Bake in a 350° oven about 10 minutes.
Makes 5 dozen.

title: old fashioned cream pie
directions: Mix together first 3 ingredients. Pour in an unbaked pie shell.
Dot with butter and nutmeg.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: 7 layer bars
directions: Place ingredients in 9 x 13-inch pan in order listed, spreading same over pan.
Bake 1/2 hour, until light brown.

title: southern spoon bread
directions: Place these ingredients in a saucepan and bring to a boil. Boil until mixture is clear and thick, then add one 3 ounce package of strawberry jello to the hot mixture and pour over the strawberries in pie shell.
When cool, top with Cool Whip before serving.

title: cole slaw
directions: Grate cabbage and carrots in food processor.
Add salt, pepper and sugar.
Mix altogether and let set 15 minutes before adding mayonnaise.

title: creamy broccoli casserole
directions: In a bowl, beat eggs; add soup, mayonnaise, pecans and onion. Stir in broccoli; pour into a greased 2 qt. baking dish. Sprinkle with cheese, combine butter and bread crumbs; sprinkle over cheese.
Bake uncovered, at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: chicken "watchamacallit"
directions: Arrange everything in a large baking pan with tight cover or cover with foil, but let no steam escape.

Add just a little bit of water to cover the bottom of the pan. Season all ingredients and add soy sauce. Bake at 375° for about 1 3/4 hours. The steam seals in the various flavors and therefore it is very important to cover tightly.

title: double apple butter(sugar-free)
directions: Soften gelatin in cold lemon juice in blender container for 4 minutes; add boiling apple juice and blend on high speed until all gelatin granules are dissolved.
Add salt, undrained apples, cinnamon
and
vanilla
and
blend	until
smooth
and fluffy. Fill
jars,
cover and chill.
Store in refrigerator. Yields about 3
cups.
Contains
about
calories per 1 tablespoon. Exchanges:	1 tablespoon equals 1/5 fruit.

title: italian beef casserole(microwave)
directions: Place beef in a 3-quart casserole.
Break with fork.
Use "Cook" cycle and cook 6 to 8 minutes in microwave until meat changes color.
Break up any remaining large pieces.
Add remaining ingredients except cheese.
Mix well and cover.
Use "Cook" cycle for 10 minutes.
Stir and cover.
Cook for 14 minutes.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Cover and let stand 10 minutes before serving.

title: spanish pisto
directions: Saute ham, onions, garlic and green pepper in oil in large skillet until onions are tender, but not browned.
Add beans, artichokes, tomatoes and salt.
Cover and simmer until vegetables are tender, about 15 minutes.
Serve hot or cold.
Makes 4 servings.

title: chicken and dressing casserole
directions: Prepare stuffing according to box, then mix remaining ingredients all together.
Bake 30 minutes for 350° or until golden brown on top.

title: joyce's bread topping
directions: Mix the first 4 ingredients in a small bowl.
Cut the bread in half longways.
Butter the bread.
Spread the topping mixture evenly onto the buttered bread.
Put bread on a cookie sheet and place under a hot broiler until brown and bubbly (approximately 1 minute).
Watch it carefully as it burns easily.
Slice into pieces and serve immediately.

title: stuffed green peppers
directions: Wash green peppers; cut a thin slice from stem ends and remove seeds.
Cover with boiling salted water and simmer 5 minutes. Drain.

title: christmas cookies
directions: Put two cups of self-rising flour in one bowl.
In another bowl place 3/4 cup solid shortening and 1 cup of sugar.
Mix together, using hands.
Add 1 egg, 2 teaspoons of vanilla and milk.
Add flour, using hands.
Roll out with pin.
Bake at 325° until lightly browned.

title: chocolate chip cheese ball
directions: Add soft butter. Add rest of ingredients. Spray Pam on plastic wrap. Roll in a ball. Put in refrigerator and chill for about 1 to 2 hours, then roll in nuts or chocolate chips (mini).

title: vegetable quiche
directions: Put broccoli or spinach into unbaked pie crust.
Mix egg substitute, milk and seasonings and pour over broccoli in crust. Cook at 375° for 50 to 55 minutes or until knife inserted comes out clean.
Let stand 10 minutes.

title: sweetbread bread-pudding
directions: Combine butter, milk and sugar in saucepan.
Heat until butter melts; cool.
Add eggs and vanilla.
In a 9 x 13-inch or 9 x 9-inch greased pan, break bread into large chunks.
Sprinkle raisins in bread.
Pour egg mixture over bread.
Spread with pie filling.
Sprinkle with cinnamon.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes (for 9 x 13-inch pan) or 40 to 45 minutes (for 9 x 9-inch pan).

title: zucchini soup
directions: Combine zucchini, seasonings, chicken broth and water.
Bring to boil.
Cover and cook over moderate heat until tender, about 10 minutes.
Blend zucchini slices and broth, 1/3 at a time, in a blender until smooth. Combine with half and half and stir over moderate heat until heated through.
If refrigerated, reheat slowly and do not boil.
Garnish with a sprinkling of chives. Makes 8 servings.
May be frozen.

title: easy beef tips
directions: Brown meat in margarine at medium heat.
Add remaining ingredients and simmer for 2 hours.
Stir occasionally.
Add more water, 1/2 cup at a time, if too much liquid boils away.
Serve over potatoes, rice or noodles.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: earthquake cake
directions: Grease 9 x 13-inch pan.
Layer nuts on bottom of pan, then layer coconut.
Pour prepared cake batter over nuts and coconut. Mix cream cheese, margarine and powdered sugar together until smooth.
Dab on top of cake all over.
Bake at 350° until done.

title: rosy spaghetti
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Cook spaghetti according to package directions; drain in a colander.
Combine spaghetti, cheese, butter, salt, Worcestershire sauce and pepper.
Toss until cheese and butter are melted.
Stir in tomato juice and parsley.
Turn into a 1-quart baking dish.
Cover; bake for 30 minutes.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: chicken roll-ups
directions: Cook chicken breasts; reserve broth.
Debone chicken and half each one.
Place cheese and chicken on crescent roll and wrap. Heat soup and add 1 cup chicken broth.
Add garlic salt and pepper to taste.
Lay onion and pepper in oblong baking dish.
Pour soup mixture over this.
Lay chicken rolls on top of mixture.
Bake 30 minutes at 350° or until rolls begin to brown.

title: buckeye chicken
directions: Combine cheese, flour and seasonings.
Dip chicken in combined egg and milk and coat with cheese mixture.
Place on cookie sheet or baking dish and pour melted margarine over it.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: dip
directions: Mix cheese, chopped onions, olives and beef together.
Chill. Spread on crackers.

title: pimento and cheese
directions: Mix all ingredients and chill.

title: stinger
directions: Over cracked ice in cocktail shaker, pour brandy and creme de menthe.
Shake well.
Strain mixture into chilled cocktail glass.

title: fruit salsa with cinnamon chips
directions: Chop fruit until extremely small; food chopper or hand held chopper works best.
Keep all juices made when chopping fruit.
Add juice of orange.
Melt apple jelly in the microwave about 10 seconds and blend all ingredients well.
Refrigerate.

title: mixed vegetable casserole
directions: Cook vegetables according to package directions.
Combine all ingredients (except cracker crumbs and margarine) and pour into large casserole dish.
Melt margarine in skillet and stir in crushed cracker crumbs.
Stir to coat all crumbs. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: lois' meat loaf
directions: Mix together the ground chuck and egg.
Place the bouillon cube in the hot water until it is dissolved then add the stuffing mix.
Add remaining ingredients to the ground chuck mixture. Shape into loaf pan and bake 350 degrees for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.

title: opelousa's baked chicken
directions: Season chicken generously with seasoning or salt and pepper. Rub well on each side.
Place halves in open baking pan and cover with mixture of oil and water.
Place pan in preheated 275° oven and cook until hot.
Sprinkle generously with paprika and chili powder.
Baste continuously about every 1/2 hour until dark, dark brown.
Takes 3 to 5 hours.

title: german chocolate cake
directions: Grease and flour 9 x 13-inch pan.
Add nuts and coconut to bottom.
Prepare cake mix as directed on box.
Pour over nuts and coconut.
Now, mix the cream cheese, sugar and butter; pour on top of cake before baking.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.
It may be jelly like, but after it cools, it will set up.

title: shipwreck
directions: In a 9 x 13-inch casserole, layer first 9 ingredients.
Mix soup with water and pour over other ingredients.
Cover and bake at 350° for 2 hours.

title: ham roll-ups
directions: You will also need one package of toothpicks.
Lay ham slices out flat and spread with cream cheese.
Place pickle spear at one end of ham slice and roll pickle tightly in ham slice.
Cut in fours and insert toothpicks to keep ham together.
Serve cold.

title: chicken wings
directions: Simmer all ingredients, except chicken wings, for 10 to 15 minutes.
Put chicken wings in broiler pan.
Pour sauce on the wings.
Bake at 325°, turning every 1/2 hour.

title: easy stroganoff
directions: Cook meat and onion until brown and tender.
Stir in flour, salt, garlic, pepper and mushrooms.
Cook 5 minutes, stirring constantly.
Stir in soup; heat to boiling, stirring.
Simmer, uncovered, 10 minutes.
Add sour cream, mix well and heat through. Serve over cooked noodles.

title: rocky road fudge
directions: Melt milk, chips
and butter.
Pour over the marshmallows. Add nuts and pour into 13 x 9-inch pan.
Refrigerate.

title: tutti frutti ice cream
directions: Combine first 7 ingredients;
blend well.
Add milk and water. Pour
mixture
into freezer can of one gallon electric freezer. Freeze.
Allow
ice
cream to ripen at least 1 hour. Makes 2 quarts.
Very good.

title: italian shrimp
directions: Melt margarine, Italian dressing and lemon juice in skillet. Stir in shrimp. Saut for 10 to 15 minutes, turning occasionally. Serve over rice.

title: christmas rice
directions: Mix all together and pour into 9 x 13-inch pan or 2-quart casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until rice is tender.
Do not cook until dry.
If needed, add more water.
Keep stirring while cooking.

title: pork chop and potato scallop
directions: Combine soup, sour cream, water and parsley.
In a 2-quart shallow casserole dish, alternate layers of sliced potatoes, onions, green pepper and cheese soup mixture.
Sprinkle each layer of potatoes lightly with salt and pepper.
Place uncovered in a preheated oven (about 375°).
Bake 30 minutes.
Trim excess fat from pork chops.
Roll in flour to coat thoroughly.
Heat oil in a large skillet over medium heat (about 375°).
Brown pork chops in oil evenly on both sides.
Sprinkle pork chops with salt and pepper.
Place on top of potatoes.
Cover and return to oven for one hour and 20 minutes.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: blueberry muffins
directions: Combine the first 5 ingredients.
Fold in blueberries.
Pour in paper-lined muffin tins.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes.
Makes 12.

title: cheese chips
directions: Let cheese and margarine soften together, then mix in remaining ingredients.
Roll into 2-inch rolls; put in aluminum foil (about 3 rolls).
Chill overnight or longer.
Slice thin and bake on lightly greased cookie sheet in 325° oven for 20 minutes.

title: chocolate fudge pie
directions: Blend cocoa into melted butter.
Add remaining ingredients; mix well.
Pour into pie shell.
Bake 25 minutes at 350°.
Cool and serve with ice cream or whipped cream.

title: fluffy egg dumplings
directions: Sift flour with baking powder and salt into bowl.
In a small bowl, combine egg, shortening and milk until well combined.
Pour all at once into flour mixture, mixing until dry ingredients are moistened.
Drop batter by rounded tablespoonfuls into boiling stew.
Cook uncovered for 10 minutes.
Lower heat.
Then cover tightly for 10 minutes more.

title: scalloped oysters
directions: Melt butter; stir
in crumbs.
Place half of crumbs in bottom of greased oblong baking dish.
Spread with oysters.
Season with salt and pepper.
Top with
remaining crumbs.
Add cream and seasoning.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Do
not have more than two layers of oysters.
If you do, the top layer will be overdone and the bottom ones are undone.

title: vegetarian chili
directions: Soak beans overnight and then cook until tender.
Add remaining ingredients.
Mix ingredients and simmer a few hours until thick.
Good with corn bread.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Broil chicken breast.
Pull chicken off bone.
Tear into small bits and pieces; mix chicken, mushroom soup, cream of chicken soup, sour cream and 1 pack of crackers.
Mix all ingredients together.
Put into a 2-quart casserole dish.
Take the other pack of crackers and crumble on top.
Dot cracker crumbs with butter. Put in oven at 450° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: rice broccoli casserole
directions: Pour boiling water over chopped broccoli.
Cook 5 minutes (until tender).
Add soup and Cheez Whiz to broccoli.
Add cooked rice and sauteed veggies.
Place in a casserole dish and bake at 375° for 20 minutes.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Melt margarine, soup, Cheez Whiz and salt. Add rice.
Put in casserole dish and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: spicy spinach dip
directions: If using fresh spinach, cook on medium-high until spinach wilts, about 5 minutes.
While cooking, add the garlic clove (minced) and sprinkle with salt and a little oil or butter.
Add milk to spinach and puree.

title: hummus
directions: Drain can of garbanzo beans; reserve 2 to 4 tablespoons of liquid.
Mash beans with 2 tablespoons liquid.
Beat in yogurt, lemon juice, sesame paste or peanut butter, garlic, salt and pepper.

title: south florida steamed shrimp
directions: Blend 1 cup of water , olive oil and onion powder in a stew pot.
Bring to boil and lower temperature.
Using steam tray, steam shrimp
1 layer at a time.
When they turn pink, take out and put in bowl with ice.

title: kathy's salsa
directions: Combine all
of the above and blend well.
Cover and chill for several hours or over night. A food processor works very well for all of the chopping.
Wear plastic gloves for the jalapenos and don't touch your eyes.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: coolrise white bread
directions: Spoon flour into measuring cup.
Pour onto wax paper.
Combine 4 cups of flour, dry yeast, sugar and salt in large bowl.
Stir to blend.
Add butter to milk and water; heat until lukewarm.
Add warm liquids to dry ingredients.
Beat with electric mixer at medium speed for 2 minutes.
Scrape bowl occasionally.
Add 2 more cups of flour; beat at high speed until thick and elastic. Gradually add remaining flour, stirring with wooden spoon.

title: pork chops italiano
directions: About 2 hours before serving, trim pork chops of excess fat. Sprinkle with seasoned salt and pepper.
In large skillet, saute chops until well browned.
Drain and place in large roasting pan or casserole dish.
Arrange mushrooms around chops.
Heat oven to 375°.

title: bacon-cheese-potato slices(microwave)
directions: Scrub potatoes; trim ends.
Cut into 3/8-inch slices.
Evenly arrange on microwave dish (12-inch plate).
Put smaller slices in center.
Sprinkle with green onion.
Cover with plastic wrap; cook on High 7 to 10 minutes.
Turn plate half turn after 4 minutes. Sprinkle with bacon bits, olives and cheese.
