Cook, uncovered, for 1 to 1 1/2 minutes, just until cheese starts to melt.

title: baked pork chops with rice
directions: Season chops with salt and pepper.
Brown chops in frying pan.
Place in baking dish.
Cover with rice.
Mix soup and milk; pour over chops and rice, being careful to cover with liquid.
Cover tightly.
Bake in 350° oven for 1 1/4 hours. Soup will be absorbed into rice.

title: pudding delight
directions: Mix flour and butter together. Place in bottom of cake pan, 13 x 9-inches. Bake at 400° for 10 minutes. Let cool.
Mix cream cheese, powdered sugar and Cool Whip together.
Spread on dough mixture after it has cooled. Mix pudding and milk together, then pour on top. (I think butterscotch is the best.) Top with some more Cool Whip.

title: homestyle boursin cheese
directions: Blend all ingredients together.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
(This may be placed in a mold first and then refrigerated.)
Serve with crackers.

title: flakey pie crust(makes 2 crusts)
directions: Beat together or shake in a jar, then add to flour.
It may seem kinda sticky, but avoid working in too much flour.
Pie crusts freeze real well.

title: meat loaf (crock-pot)
directions: Mix egg, milk, salt and bread.
Allow to soften.
Thoroughly combine with meat and chopped vegetables.
Shape into loaf and place in crock-pot.
Top with catsup and green pepper rings. Place potatoes beside loaf.
Cover and set on high for 1 hour, then on low for 8 to 9 hours.

title: almond chicken casserole
directions: Cook noodles in salted water until tender.
Meanwhile, melt butter.
Add celery; cover and cook slowly for 10 minutes.
Blend in flour, mustard, salt and pepper.
Add milk and Worcestershire sauce.
Cook and stir until thick.
Add cheese, chicken, pimiento, green pepper, drained noodles and half of almonds.
Put into shallow baking dish; sprinkle with crumbs and remaining almonds. Decorate with additional almonds, if desired.
Bake in hot oven for 15 to 20 minutes until heated through.

title: sausage-rice casserole
directions: Brown sausage with onions and peppers.
Add broth envelope in package of Uncle Ben's long grain and wild rice.
Add 2 cups of water.
(Do not drain grease from sausage before adding rice package.)
Add rice.
Cook at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: ham barbecue sauce
directions: Saute onions in butter until soft.
Add all remaining ingredients and cook on medium fire for 10 minutes.
Let cool and add 1 pound cold ham, sliced thin.
Serve on hamburger buns.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix first five ingredients (after cheese is soft) to form into a ball; roll in parsley flakes.

title: grandma taylor's no bake cookies
directions: Melt over low heat, sugar, milk and margarine.
Remove from heat and add oatmeal, cocoa and nuts.
Blend well.
Drop on wax paper by tablespoonful and let harden.
Watch them "disappear" ... they are so good!

title: grover's pickled peppers(no fat)
directions: Boil 2 parts water to 1 part vinegar.
Cut peppers in quarters and remove seeds.
Place peppers and garlic (to taste) in sterilized jars and cover with liquid mixture.
Seal jars and get ready for a tasty treat.

title: old fashioned flapjacks(makes eight 4-inch flapjacks)
directions: In a large bowl of electric mixer at high speed, beat eggs until light and fluffy, about 2 minutes.
Into eggs, sift flour with baking powder, salt and sugar.
Add brown sugar; beat until smooth.
Stir in buttermilk and butter, just until combined; do not overbeat.

title: scott's spaghetti salad
directions: Mix ingredients
in chilled Dutch oven.
Place in creek for 3 to 6 hours to chill.
Stir to blend every hour.
Careful not to get any water inside Dutch oven.

title: reese's balls
directions: Melt margarine with peanut butter; remove from heat.
Add sugar.
Knead together and form into bite size balls.
Chill.
Dip balls into melted chocolate and paraffin mixture.
Place on waxed paper to dry.

title: champagne punch
directions: Make a syrup of the strawberry and lemonade Kool-Aid.
Makes 1 gallon, then add the pineapple juice and ginger ale and champagne.

title: soft shell tacos
directions: Mix and drop on hot griddle.
Spread thin and cook until dry on top.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Cream sugar and shortening in bowl of electric mixer.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Beat well.
Add vanilla.
Combine soda and buttermilk.
Add flour and buttermilk alternately to creamed mixture.
Fold in bananas and nuts.

title: amazing coconut pie
directions: In blender, combine all ingredients except coconut for 3 minutes.
Pour in 9-inch greased pie pan.
Let stand 5 minutes. Sprinkle coconut over filling.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes. Makes its own crust.
Amazing.

title: chicken bake
directions: Combine the rice, evaporated milk, and 1/2 package of onion soup mix and mushrooms and place in pan.
Put chicken on top.
Put 1 can of cream of celery soup on top.
Sprinkle with other 1/2 package of onion soup mix.
Cover with foil and bake at 350 for about 1 hour.
Uncover and bake for 15 minutes more.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: In a skillet, put 3 tablespoons oil.
Add vegetables, 1 teaspoon salt and 1/4 teaspoon black pepper.
Cook together until tender, about 10 minutes.

title: zucchini dessert squares
directions: In large bowl, cream butter, oil and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Blend in vanilla and buttermilk.
In another bowl, combine flour, soda, baking powder, salt, cocoa and cinnamon.
Add dry ingredients slowly to creamed mixture.
Stir in zucchini. Spread on greased jellyroll pan.
Sprinkle chocolate bits and walnuts over top and bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Cool. Cut into 2-inch squares.
Makes 40 squares.

title: quick spring dessert
directions: Wash the strawberries.
Hull them and place in individual serving dishes.
In a smaller dish, place 1/4 to 1/2 cup powdered sugar.
Dip the strawberries in the sugar and eat.

title: chris' lemon jello pound cake
directions: Do not follow instructions on cake box, instead add the ingredients listed.
Beat this real good.
Pour into a greased and floured Bundt pan and bake 35 to 40 minutes or until done in a 350° oven.

title: carne guisada tacos
directions: Season
meat
with
salt and pepper.
Braise in skillet with bacon
drippings
or
oil.
When browned, stir in onion, garlic and
bell pepper, comino and flour.
Brown flour well, then add tomato
sauce
and 2 to 3 cups water.
Stir well and cover. Simmer
for
minutes, adding water, if needed, for gravy. Serve with hot flour tortillas and hot sauce.

title: corn casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together except butter.
Pour into greased casserole dish and dot with butter.
Bake at 325° until golden brown, about 45 minutes.

title: peanut butter fudge 2
directions: Melt butter over medium heat. Add sugar, Karo syrup and milk. Heat over medium heat, stirring constantly until mixture comes to a boil. Reduce heat to medium, cook and stir for 5 minutes. Remove from heat. Add peanut butter, marshmallow cream and vanilla. Stir until all ingredients are well combined and fudge loses its gloss. Pour
into greased 9x13
pan. Let set until completely cool. Cut into squares. Makes approximately 5 pounds of fudge.

title: sweet potato souffle
directions: Mix together ingredients and pour into greased (buttered) baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: easy ham and potatoes
directions: First, mix
soup
and
water
together; heat until well mixed. Then place potatoes and ham into baking dish.
Add all other ingredients.
Salt
and pepper to taste.
Pour soup over potatoes and ham.
Bake in oven at 350° until done.
Don't dry out.
Serves 3 to 4 people.

title: baked beans crockpot style
directions: Combine all ingredients in crockpot. Set on low at bedtime for the next evening.

title: grandma graham's sugar cookies
directions: Add sugar gradually to shortening and cream until light and fluffy.
Beat in eggs and vanilla.
Sift flour, baking powder and salt together.
Add to sugar mixture, blending well.
Chill for several hours.
Roll 1/8-inch thick floured board and cut into desired shape.
Sprinkle with additional sugar.
Bake at 400° for 6 to 8 minutes.

title: cream cheese and crab sauce
directions: In a small bowl, beat cream cheese.
Add crab juice, onions, lemon juice, salt and hot sauce.
Stir in crab meat.
Put in greased shallow baking dish.
Bake, uncovered, in preheated 350° oven for 20 to 30 minutes, or until bubbly.
Serve hot on cocktail bread or crackers.

title: fresh lemonade
directions: Combine lemon juice, water and sugar in a large pitcher; stir to dissolve sugar.
Add lemon slices.
Chill. Serve over ice. Garnish with orange slices, strawberries and a sprig of fresh mint.

title: pizza dough
directions: Mix all together.
Can even turn out on countertop and knead all together.
When mixed, press out with hands onto pizza pan or 9 x 13-inch cookie sheet.
Top with your favorite pizza sauce and toppings.

title: ice cream(one gallon)
directions: Heat the milk.
Soak the plain gelatin in a bit of cold water. Mix 1 cup sugar, Clear Jell and egg yolks.
Add to milk; cook until thick.
Add soaked gelatin and 1 more cup sugar.
Cool.
Add the cream, beaten egg whites and milk to fill.
You can add any kind flavor instant pudding, if you wish.

title: hot milk cake
directions: Add sugar to beaten eggs, then add flour which has been sifted with baking powder and salt.
Beat all these together.
Put the butter (1/4 pound) in saucepan along with the milk.
Bring just to a boil and add to and beat the first mixture.
Add the flavoring. This cake may be baked in a tube pan, greased and floured well, at 325°.
Cooking will require from 45 minutes to 1 hour.
It may also be used for all kinds of cupcakes or layer cakes and baked 20 minutes at 375°.

title: apple cake
directions: Beat eggs well, then add sugar, oil and vanilla.
Beat well. Add apples.
Sift flour 3 times, then sift with soda.
Add nuts. Combine apple batter with flour and nuts.
Bake in 2 layers, starting in cold oven.
Set at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: meat loaf
directions: Combine all but the ham and cheese and mix together well. Spread the meat mixture out on a large piece of foil and roll/pat to form a 10 x 12 inch rectangle. Arrange the ham on top leaving a small margin around the edges. Sprinkle cheese over the ham. Starting from the short end, roll up loaf using the foil to lift (jelly-roll style). Place roll seam side down in a 9 x 13 inch pan. Bake at 350° for 1 hour 10 minutes. Put extra cheese on top the last 5 minutes.

title: blueberry cobbler
directions: Mix 1/2 cup sugar and the cornstarch in saucepan.
Stir in berries and water.
Heat to boiling; boil and stir 1 minute.
Pour into ungreased casserole.
Mix remaining ingredients until soft dough forms.
Drop dough by 6 tablespoons onto hot blueberry mixture.
Bake until golden brown, about 15 minutes in 425° oven.

title: fresh citrus punch
directions: Combine 6 cups fruit juice and sugar, stirring until sugar is dissolved.
Add ginger ale.
Serve over ice, if desired.
Garnish punch with fresh strawberries and pineapple chunks.

title: carrie's cheese ball
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients together.
Form into one large ball or 2 small balls.
Roll in chopped pecans.
Wrap in plastic wrap. Store in refrigerator.

title: mulled apple cider
directions: Combine all ingredients in large pan and bring to a boil. Cover and reduce heat; simmer for 30 minutes to blend flavors. Strain and serve hot.

title: homemakers' holiday casserole
directions: Cook macaroni; drain.
Combine soup and milk; add to macaroni. Simmer.
Add onion, pepper and meat.
Put in casserole pan and bake at 325° for 30 minutes.

title: veggie squares appetizer
directions: Mix together first 3 ingredients.
Roll out 2 packages crescent rolls in about a 10 x 12-inch square.
Pinch ends together and press flat.
Place on cookie sheet and bake 10 minutes at 350° until golden.
Cool.
Spread cream cheese mixture on cooled bread. Sprinkle vegetables on top.
Cut in squares and serve.

title: rice krispie cookies
directions: Mix together the brown sugar, sugar and margarine. Add the vanilla, flour, baking soda and cream of tartar. Mix all together. Add and mix with wooden spoon the Rice Krispies. Drop by spoonful on cookie sheet. Bake at 350° for 5 to 6 minutes.

title: mixed vegetable casserole
directions: Cook vegetables until tender.
Pour in a greased casserole dish.
Mix onions, cheese and mayonnaise.
Spread over vegetables. Melt margarine and mix with crackers.
Spread on top and bake for 30 minutes at 350° in oven.

title: zucchini sausage pie
directions: Cook squash in salt water until tender; drain.
Saute sausage and drain.
Combine sausage and squash with remaining ingredients. Save 2 tablespoons of cheese to sprinkle on top.
Spoon into sprayed (Pam) 9-inch pie plate.
Bake 45 minutes in 350° oven. Serves 4 to 6.

title: tuna noodle casserole
directions: Cook noodles in boiling water until tender; drain.
Drain water from tuna.
Place all ingredients in a casserole.
Salt and pepper to taste and mix well.
Top with buttered 1/2-inch squares of bread.
Bake in 350° oven for 45 minutes.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Mix and drop from spoon.
Bake in moderately hot oven.

title: so easy casserole
directions: Lightly butter glass casserole dish.
Put in uncooked chicken. Place 2 slices of cheese on top of each chicken piece.
Cover cheese with generous amount of stuffing, making small mounds and being sure to cover cheese.
Blend can of chicken soup with white wine.
Pour evenly over casserole.
Bake uncovered at 325° for 50 to 60 minutes.
Test into center making sure chicken is white and done.
Can be made in advance, pouring soup and wine over just before baking.
(Refrigerate until ready to bake.)

title: raisin icebox cookies
directions: Mix all and roll into 3 or 4 rolls.
Cover each roll in waxed paper and leave in refrigerator overnight or longer.
Slice and bake at 325° until light brown.

title: party cheese ball
directions: Place cheeses in small bowl and let stand at room temperature until softened.
Add onion and Worcestershire sauce, blending on low speed.
Beat on medium speed until fluffy, scraping side and bottom of bowl.
Cover; chill for 8 hours.
Shape mixture into one large ball.
Roll in parsley and place on serving plate.
Cover and chill 2 hours or until firm.
Serves 12.

title: easy herbed oyster crackers
directions: Mix all
ingredients,
except crackers, in saucepan and heat. Pour over
crackers,
which
you have placed in a brown paper bag; shake.
The
oil will be absorbed by the bag so you may want to use double thickness or else change bags after the 1st shaking.

title: cream cheese squares
directions: Mix cake mix, butter, 1 egg and nuts by hand.
Pat in greased pan.
Mix powdered sugar, cream cheese, 2 eggs and vanilla well. Pour over first mixture.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: easiest pie
directions: Melt Hershey bar in a plastic bowl in microwave at 50% power for 3 minutes.
Blend Cool Whip into melted Hershey bar and pour into pie shell.
Cool for 1 hour in fridge.
Enjoy!

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Combine peanut butter with confectioners sugar and softened cream cheese.
Fold in whipped topping.
Spoon mixture into crust. Place in freezer for several hours before serving.	After cutting pie, place on dessert plates and drizzle chocolate syrup lightly over each piece.
Store leftovers in refrigerator.

title: tavern cheesecake
directions: You will need a 10-inch spring-form pan and a cookie sheet or other pan underneath to catch drippings.

title: vidalia onion muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Spray muffin pans with cooking spray. Beat milk, oil and egg and stir in flour, oatmeal and sugar just until moistened.
Fold in Vidalia onions, cheese and pecans.

title: barbecued meatballs
directions: Moisten bread with small amount of water or milk.
Mix with beef.
Form into small meatballs; brown.
Brown chopped onion in fat.
Add other ingredients.
Pour over meatballs and simmer 30 minutes or until meatballs are done.

title: crab dip
directions: Combine cream cheese, onion and Worcestershire sauce in a small bowl.
Place in Pyrex pie plate.
Cover mixture with chili sauce; sprinkle crab meat over sauce and add parsley flakes.

title: cranberry nut loaf
directions: Sift flour and measure.
Resift with baking powder, salt and soda.
Combine beaten egg with orange juice, water, cooking oil and Sweet 10.
Stir into dry ingredients just enough to moisten. Fold in cranberries and nuts.
Turn into well-greased 9 x 5 x 3-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: chicken enchiladas
directions: Mix thoroughly sour cream, soup, chicken broth, chilies and onions.
Set aside.
Grease 9 x 13-inch dish.
Layer with 1/3 tortillas (torn in bite size pieces).
Top with 1 cup cooked chicken (cubed).
Layer with 1/3 sour cream mixture.
Sprinkle with 1/3 Cheddar cheese (shredded).
Layer 2 more times, ending with cheese.

title: sour cream banana cake
directions: In mixing bowl, cream together butter and sugar until light and fluffy.
Add eggs and butter, blending thoroughly.
Sift together flour, baking powder, soda and salt.
Add alternately with sour cream to creamed mixture, beginning and ending with dry ingredients.
Add bananas and nuts just until blended.
Pour into greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake for 40 to 45 minutes at 350°.
Cool on wire rack.

title: baked beans with sausage(serves 6)
directions: Mix all ingredients, except sausages and place in a bean pot. Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Top with hot sausages and serve.

title: homestead stew
directions: Brown ground beef with green pepper, onion and chili powder in heavy saucepan, stirring until ground beef is crumbly.
Drain. Add soup, undrained tomatoes, undrained beans and water.
Mix well.
Simmer for 15 minutes or longer.
May omit water and/or tomato juice and serve in taco shells if preferred.
Yields 4 servings.

title: summer squash soup
directions: * Or 4 of either, if one is not available.

title: working mom's delight
directions: Brown ground beef with onion in a large pan.
Drain grease and return to pan.
Add stewed tomatoes, sauce, water, corn and seasonings to the ground beef.
Simmer 10 minutes.
Add egg noodles and cook at fast simmer 12 to 15 minutes or until noodles are tender.
If too soupy, simmer until liquid cooks down.
Great served with a green salad and French bread.

title: pumpkin or sweet potato pie
directions: Blend smooth all but pumpkin or sweet potato with 1/2 cup of the water.
When smooth, add remaining liquid and as much of the pumpkin or sweet potato as the blender can whiz.
Pour contents in with remaining squash.
Stir well.
Cook over medium heat in a saucepan, stirring constantly, for about 10 minutes.
Pour into baked pie crust.
Chill.
To serve, sprinkle coconut on top or soy whipped cream.

title: tortillas paraguaya
directions: Mix together slowly the egg, flour and salt, then add liquids. Add veggies last.
Heat oil in a pan until it's really hot.
Deep fry tortillas with 2 tablespoons of batter per tortilla.
Turn once, spooning hot oil on top until tortilla is golden brown.

title: cherry cake
directions: Spread both cans of pie filling in bottom of 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Crumble and sprinkle dry cake mix all over top of pie filling.
Pour melted oleo over top of cake mix and then top the entire dish with the chopped pecans.

title: ben's yummy cake
directions: Cook cake mix according to directions in rectangular cake pan. While warm, poke holes in cake with straw or wooden spoon every couple of inches apart.
Pour milk over cake so that it seeps into holes.
Sprinkle with coconut and then cover with caramel.

title: onion pie
directions: Bake pie shell.
Remove and turn heat to 300°.
Saute bacon until crisp and crumble.
In 3 tablespoons of oil, saute onions. Beat eggs slightly.
Stir in sour cream, pepper, chives, onions and bacon.
Pour into pie shell and sprinkle with seeds.
Bake 30 minutes.

title: lo-fat turkey meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients together and form into loaf.
Bake 1 hour and 20 minutes at 350°.
Use meat thermometer to be sure of doneness.
Don't overcook.

title: skillet chicken parmesan
directions: Combine bread crumbs and 4 tablespoons Parmesan.
Dip chicken in egg, then coat with crumb mixture.
Heat oil in skillet.
Cook chicken 5 minutes per side or until done.
Add desired amount of sauce and heat until hot.
Remove to serving dish.
Sprinkle with remaining Parmesan.

title: sixty minute rolls
directions: In a large bowl, mix first 4 ingredients, plus one cup of the flour.
Add margarine and hot water and stir until margarine is mostly melted.
Add rest of flour and mix well.
Cover and let rise 15 minutes.
Turn out on floured board and knead until no longer sticky.
Shape your rolls.
Place on buttered pans.
Cover and let rest for 15 minutes.
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes or until golden brown.

title: dump cake
directions: Dump undrained pineapple in a lightly greased 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Swirl it around to fill all corners.
Cover pineapple with cherry pie filling.
Sprinkle dry cake mix over pie filling. Pour melted butter over cake mix.
Sprinkle nuts on top, if desired.
Bake at 350°
for 50 to 55 minutes until lightly browned.

title: hot spiced tea
directions: Simmer water, tea bags and cloves for 10 minutes.
After 10 minutes, remove tea bags and cloves.
Add juice, sugar and lemon juice.
Keep warm and serve.

title: peaches and cream pie
directions: Mix together salt, oleo, egg, milk, and pudding and beat for 2 minutes.
Pour into well greased 9 inch pie pan and press around evenly.
Place sliced peaches (drain and keep juice) in pan.
Beat together
cream cheese, 3 Tbsp. peach juice and 1/2 cup sugar. Beat until creamy.
Spread over peaches to within 1 inch of edge of pan.
Mix 1 Tbsp. sugar and 1/2 tsp. cinnamon together. Sprinkle on top.
Bake 30 - 35 minutes at 350 degrees.

title: filled won ton cookies
directions: Mix together nuts, coconut and brown sugar.
Fold won ton squares into triangles and round off corners with scissors.
Unfold and place 2 teaspoons of the filling in center.
Moisten edges with water and refold.
Cook in hot oil until golden, turning once. Drain on paper towel and sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: sauce vinaigrette
directions: Beat the vinegar, salt and mustard in a bowl until dissolved, then beat in the oil.
Season with the pepper and herbs.
Or, place all ingredients in a screw-top jar and shake vigorously for 30 seconds to blend thoroughly.
Taste carefully for seasoning.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Great in crock-pot.
Will need to increase baking time.

title: party beef dip
directions: Brown beef and drain.
Saute onion and add garlic. Add ground beef; stir in tomato sauce, ketchup, oregano and sugar.
Cover and simmer 10 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Add cheeses; stir until cream cheese is melted.
Serve warm with tortilla chips and vegetables.

title: cucumbers in sour cream
directions: Mix all ingredients, adding cucumbers last.
Cover and chill several hours.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Thoroughly
wash
and
dry strawberries; cut in halves. Place strawberries
in
baked pie shell.	Mix water with sugar and cornstarch.
Cook
to 5 minutes; add strawberry Jell-O. Stir until dissolved.
Pour over strawberries in crust and top with whipped cream.
Serves 8.

title: coconut chews
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Mix powdered sugar, margarine and flour. Press into ungreased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Bake 12 to 15 minutes. Mix remaining ingredients and spread over baked layer. Bake 20 minutes and cool.
Frost with orange, lemon or chocolate frosting. Cut into bars. Yields 3 dozen.

title: lemon pie
directions: Beat 1 whole egg and yolks of 2.
Add sugar and cornstarch. Mix well.
Add hot water and stir, then add juice of 2 lemons and grated rind of 1.
Cook over double boiler until thick (at least 15 minutes).

title: italian potatoes
directions: Line large baking dish with aluminum foil.
Put in sliced potatoes and Italian dressing.
Dot with margarine.
Pour in water.
Bring the foil over potatoes to seal.
Bake 45 minutes to 1 hour at 350°.

title: french fried onion rings
directions: Slice onions 1/4-inch thick and separate into rings. Combine eggs, milk, salt and flour. Dip rings in batter and immediately fry in about 2 cups of hot oil.
Drain well. Sprinkle lightly with salt. Serve immediately.

title: country brunch skillet
directions: In a large skillet over medium heat, cook bacon until crisp. Remove bacon; crumble and set aside. Drain, reserving 2 tablespoons of drippings. Add potatoes, green pepper, onion, salt and pepper to drippings. Cook and stir for 2 minutes. Cover and cook, stirring occasionally, until potatoes are browned and tender, about 15 minutes. Make six wells in the potato mixture. Break one egg into each well. Cover and cook on low heat for 8 to 10 minutes or until eggs are completely set. Sprinkle with cheese and bacon. Yield: 6 servings.

title: spanish noodles
directions: Cut bacon into pieces.
Fry until crisp.
Add onion, green pepper and ground beef; saute until brown.
Add undrained tomatoes and salt.
Boil.
Stir in uncooked noodles.
Cook, uncovered, over low heat, stirring occasionally until noodles are tender.
Pepper to taste.
Put into casserole dish and bake for 20 to 30 minutes. Makes 5 servings.

title: granny's fudge
directions: Cook the first 4 ingredients to soft boil stage, then remove from heat and add vanilla, butter and nuts.
Stir.
Pour out on buttered plate.
Let set up and then cut into pieces.

title: lumpia
directions: Saute pork, beef and onion and drain.
Add shrimp and cook 1 minute.
Remove from heat and add eggs, carrot, green onion, cabbage, garlic, sprouts and soy sauce.
Salt and pepper to taste. Let mixture cool.
Put heaping tablespoon of filling on each lumpia wrapper.
Roll up, making small cylinder.
Tuck ends in and seal with milk.
Deep fry until brown.
Serve with sweet and sour sauce for dipping.

title: pickle burgers
directions: Mix all ingredients together except dill pickle.
Cut pickle into 4 lengthwise pieces.
Shape hamburger mixture around pickle quarter.
Broil 6 minutes on each side.
Serve on a hot dog roll.

title: lime pear salad
directions: Heat 1 cup pear juice to boiling.
Add jello and sugar and dissolve.
Add cream cheese and mix well.
Add one cup mashed pears.
Let stand until slightly thick, but not firm.
Use beater through jello to whip it up.
Add whipped cream.
Mix chopped cherries and nuts if desired.
This can be molded or set in plain bowl.

title: oven-fried potatoes
directions: Cut potatoes in 1/8-inch wedges.
Place in single layer in baking dish. Combine remaining ingredients in a cup/bowl.
Brush half of the mixture on the potatoes.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes, basting occasionally with oil mixture.

title: kentucky pie
directions: Mix sugar and flour.
Beat eggs and mix well with sugar and flour.
Stir in cooled margarine.
Stir in remaining ingredients. Pour in prepared pie shell.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: bran muffins
directions: Combine buttermilk, eggs, sugar and oil; blend.
Stir flour and baking soda together.
Combine with fruit mixture.
Add bran and raisins.
Mix lightly; divide into muffin pan and bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Makes 24 medium muffins.

title: parmesan potatoes
directions: Prepare potatoes; soak in cold water.
Mix flour, cheese and seasonings in plastic bag.
Melt butter in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Dredge potatoes in flour mixture.
Bake in 375° oven for 30 minutes.
Turn potatoes and bake 30 minutes more.

title: chicken supreme
directions: Boil chicken and break into pieces.
Boil rice and drain.
In 9 x 13-inch pan, cover bottom of pan with rice.
In bowl, mix sour cream and soups.
Then layer chicken over rice and next put soup mixture.
Top with crushed crackers and melted butter.
Bake at 350°, uncovered, until hot and bubbling.

title: super slaw
directions: Mix pepper, onion, cabbage and sugar (except 2 tablespoons). In a pot, mix vinegar, oil, dry mustard, salt, 2 tablespoons (reserved) sugar and celery seed.
Put mixture together and boil. Pour over cabbage mixture and let set at least 4 hours.

title: czechoslovakian pastry bars
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
In large bowl, cream together butter and sugar until light and fluffy.
Beat in eggs and vanilla until combined.
In medium bowl, mix salt with 3 1/2 cups flour. Gradually add to butter mixture to form thick batter.

title: chicken teriyaki
directions: Mix together all ingredients, except chicken, in an 11 3/4 x 1 3/4-inch dish.
Add chicken and coat with sauce.
Marinate for at least 30 minutes or overnight in the refrigerator.
Drain off most of the sauce.
Cover with foil.
Cook in hot oven until tender. Turn the chicken over and brush with drippings halfway through cooking.
Allow to stand 5 minutes before serving.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: caramel layer chocolate squares
directions: Melt caramels in milk; let cool.
By hand, stir until dough holds together.
Press 1/2 of dough into bottom of 13 x 9-inch pan.
Sprinkle chips and nuts over top of mixture.
Spread caramel mixture over chips.
Add the other 1/2 of dough on top. Bake 15 to 18 minutes at 350°.
Cool.
Cut into bars.

title: hot tamales
directions: Cook cut-up roast on top of stove, about 2 to 3 hours, totally immersed in water.
Set aside and let cool.
Separate husks and soak in warm water (they should be trimmed to about 6 1/2 x 5 1/2-inches).
After soaking, lay out on towels and blot dry.

title: chicken imperial
directions: Saute onions and celery in butter or margarine until soft. Mix chicken and mushrooms in saucepan. Add cheese and melt over low heat.
Add garlic powder, salt, pepper, onions and celery; mix well.

title: lima bean casserole
directions: Brown hamburger and onions. Combine limas, tomato soup, Worcestershire sauce and 1/2 cup bean juice. Mix and bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: chili
directions: Combine ingredients in crock-pot.
Cook 8 to 12 hours.

title: tuscan veal and tomato stew
directions: Tips:
Boneless skinless chicken or turkey breasts can be substituted for the veal.
White wine can be substituted for vermouth.

title: white fudge
directions: Combine sugar, sour cream, milk, butter, syrup and salt in saucepan.
Stir over moderate heat until sugar is dissolved and mixture reaches a boil.
Boil 9 to 10 minutes to 238° (soft ball stage).
Remove from heat and cool to lukewarm, about 1 hour.
Add vanilla and beat until it begins to lose its gloss and holds its shape.
Quickly stir in nuts and cherries and pour into a greased pan.
Let stand until firm.

title: lemon dressing
directions: Process all ingredients for 5 minutes in a food processor or blender.
Store in a jar in the refrigerator.
Recipe may be doubled.
Great for green salad, noodle recipes, etc.

title: glaze for brownies
directions: Cook sugar, butter and milk in a heavy saucepan until reaches full boil.
Then add semi-sweet chocolate and blend quickly to milk and spread at once over the brownies.

title: layered lettuce salad
directions: Break lettuce into small pieces and place 1/2 of it in a bowl. Combine eggs, green peppers, bacon, celery, peas and onion and pour 1/2 over lettuce layer.
Repeat lettuce and top with rest of the bacon-egg-veggie mixture.
Combine Miracle Whip with sugar and spread over top of salad like icing.
Top with shredded cheese.

title: egg roll wrappers
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Roll out and cut into 3-inch squares. Yield 10 - 12 pieces.

title: sauce for smokies
directions: Over low heat, melt jelly in heavy saucepan. Stir in chili sauce. Simmer over smokies for at least 30 minutes.

title: cheese dainties
directions: Cream butter and cheese together and add flour, a little at a time.
Mix well and add Rice Krispies, salt and pepper.
Roll into balls.
Mash with a fork and bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: wild rice soup
directions: Melt the margarine in a saucepan. Saute onion until tender. Blend in flour. Gradually add broth. Cook, stirring constantly, until mixture comes to a boil. Boil 1 minute.
Stir in rice, ham, carrots, almonds and salt.
Simmer 5 minutes. Blend in half and half. Garnish with minced parsley.

title: fruit cake cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar; add eggs, one at a time, beating after each egg and add flour slowly.
Flour fruit and nuts with remaining 1/2 cup of flour.
Combine all ingredients.
Drop by teaspoonful on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 250° to 300° for about 35 minutes.

title: mexican fruitcake
directions: Mix ingredients with a wooden spoon.
Bake in a 9 x 13-inch pan at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: congealed spring salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water; add cold water, salt and vinegar.
Chill and when it begins to thicken, add other ingredients; chill until firm.
Unmold on salad greens.
Slice and serve with mayonnaise or salad dressing.

title: sugarless cake
directions: Boil raisins in water until almost dry.
Add the rest of the ingredients.
Mix and bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: chess pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together with mixer.
Pour into pie shells and cook at 375° for 40 to 50 minutes or until firm.

title: meatball stew
directions: Place potatoes, carrots, onions, celery and meatballs in a 5 qt. slow cooker. Combine
the remaining ingredients in a bowl and pour over meatball
mixture. Cover and cook on low for 9 to 10 hours or until vegetables are crisp tender. Makes 6 servings.

title: chicken to the macs
directions: Prepare elbow macaroni according to package directions, adding broccoli the four minutes of cooking time; drain.
In a large skillet, heat margarine; add red pepper, onion and mushrooms and cook until onion is tender.
Add soup, milk, salt and pepper.
Cook and stir for five minutes.
Stir in 1 cup cheese and chicken. Combine macaroni and broccoli with soup mixture.
Pour into a 2 1/2-quart baking dish; top with remaining cheese.
Cover; microwave on Medium-high (rotating halfway through cooking time) for 5 to 6 minutes.

title: noodle candy
directions: Melt butterscotch morsels in double boiler until soft.
Add noodles a little at a time until well covered.
Add peanuts and stir until all covered.
Drop on waxed paper with iced tea spoon. Allow to cool.

title: steak and spinach salad
directions: Toss together all ingredients and enjoy! Breadsticks are optional.

title: carrot casserole
directions: Mix the first 5 ingredients together in a 9 x 11-inch pan or medium casserole dish.
Mix the butter with the stuffing together and put over the carrot mixture. Bake for 20 minutes at 350°.

title: blueberry cream cheese pie
directions: Mix cream cheese, both envelopes of Dream Whip and milk, 10x sugar and vanilla extract.
Pour into pie shells, pour pie filling over pies.
Refrigerate.

title: peanut butter cake
directions: Mix brown sugar, peanut butter, margarine and hot water all together.
Add
sour
milk.
Add
flour, soda and vanilla. Bake 45 minutes in a 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: cold cucumber and dill soup
directions: Put broth in blender. Add cucumber (cut into chunks), onion, salt, dill and garlic powder. Blend lightly. Stir in yogurt and sour cream until smooth.
Chill before serving.
Add green onion, cucumber slices and sliced egg. Sprinkle with pepper and paprika.

title: graham cracker bars
directions: Line 9 x 13-inch pan with whole graham crackers.
Mix crushed graham crackers, nuts and coconut.
In pan combine and boil for 1 minute the sugar, butter, milk and beaten egg.
Mix the dry ingredients and pour over graham cracker crust, then put on top layer of graham crackers.
Ice with powdered sugar frosting. Refrigerate to set up before cutting into squares.

title: freezer coleslaw
directions: Mix cabbage and salt, let stand 1 hour.
Heat sugar, vinegar, water and celery seed to boil in 1-quart saucepan.
Boil 1 minute.
Cool to lukewarm.
Drain cabbage, stir in celery, green pepper, carrot and onion.
Stir vinegar mixture into cabbage mixture.
Put in container and freeze.

title: pineapple cake
directions: Mix all ingredients by hand.
Pour into 10 x 14-inch cake pan (ungreased).
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Top with cream cheese icing.
Refrigerate and keep cold.

title: no cook fluffy icing
directions: Beat egg white until it forms a peak, adding sugar gradually. Add strawberries. This also works with other fruit or peanut butter.

title: nordic tossed salad
directions: Combine greens, zucchini, mushrooms and olives in salad bowl; toss lightly.
Top with tomatoes; serve with dressing.

title: spinach florentine
directions: Cook spinach according to directions and drain in colander. Mix sour cream and soup together and pour into spinach. Mix together. Top with enough cheese to generously cover the top and bake at 350° for 20 minutes or until cheese is melted and casserole is hot and bubbly.

title: christmas cookies
directions: Cream butter, sugar and vanilla.
Add flour and nuts.
Mix well.
Roll into small balls.
Bake at 300° for 10 to 12 minutes. Roll in confectioners sugar while still warm.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Use a large heavy pan.
Mix milk and sugar in a pan, heat to boiling, add peanut butter.
Cook on low heat to soft ball stage- 236 to 238 degrees.
Remove from heat, stir with wooden spoon until thick.
Pour onto a greased pan.
Cool, cut into one inch squares.

title: cranberry-percolator punch
directions: Pour cranberry juice, lemonade and apple cider in a 30-cup percolator; place spices into percolator basket.
Perk through complete cycle of electric percolator.
Remove basket with spices from percolator and stir in rum.
Yields about 20 cups.
Good for a crowd.

title: strawberry salad dessert
directions: Mix jello, water, strawberries and pineapple with juice. Chill.
Combine Cool Whip, cream cheese and sugar with mixer. Spread over top of jello once it is firm.
Chill 1 hour.

title: spinach stuffed shells
directions: Cook shells according to package.
Rinse and drain.
Brown ground beef; drain.
Add spaghetti sauce, salt and pepper.
In mixing bowl, combine cheeses and creamed spinach.
Stuff shells with cheese and spinach mixture; put in large casserole dish.
Top with beef mixture.
Cover with foil.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: peanut butter and cereal candy
directions: Mix cereal and nuts.
Set aside.
Mix sugar and syrup; heat until a good boil.
Add peanut butter and mix good.
Add cereal and peanuts.
Put in a greased bread pan.

title: onion and tomato soup
directions: Combine in a large saucepan.
Bring to a boil and simmer for about 30 minutes or until onions are soft.

title: juicy fruit salad
directions: Mix together and refrigerate.
Keeps well.
Bananas do not turn dark for several days.
One can cherry pie filling can be substituted for peach, or if recipe is doubled, use 1 of each.

title: banana-nut cake
directions: Cream shortening; gradually add sugar, beating well.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Add bananas and mix until smooth.
Combine flour, baking powder, soda and salt; add to creamed mixture, stirring until just moistened.
Stir in chopped pecans.
Pour batter into a greased and floured 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.
Cool in pan 10 minutes.
Remove cake to wire rack to complete cooling.
Yield: one 9-inch loaf.

title: raisin puff cookies
directions: Cook raisins in saucepan in the water until water is absorbed. Set aside. Cream the oleo and sugar until fluffy. Add dry ingredients and vanilla. Fold in raisins.
Shape into a ball. Roll in sugar and bake on ungreased cookie sheet at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: pineapple bars
directions: Combine 2 cups flour and powdered sugar in a medium bowl; cut butter in with a pastry blender until mixture is crumbly.
Press mixture into an ungreased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 18 minutes or until lightly browned.
Remove from oven and cool.

title: lemon-lime jello salad
directions: Add 1 cup boiling water to jello.
Chill until partially congealed.
Whip with mixer until fluffy.
Add cottage cheese; continue beating until smooth.
Add salad dressing, horseradish, lemon juice and evaporated milk.
Continue beating; add pineapple and mix well.
Pour into mold and chill until firm.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Boil sweet potatoes until fork goes all the way through easily.
Skin them; mash in butter.
Beat well.
Add in 2 eggs at a time while beating, about 5 minutes.
Pour into Ready-Crusts. Cook at 350° for about an hour (until silver fork comes out smooth).

title: red velvet cake
directions: Prepare cake mix according to directions on box but in place of water, add food coloring.
Then use remaining amount of water according to directions.

title: old-fashioned sweet-sour coleslaw(12 servings!)
directions: Place cabbage in large bowl.
Cover and refrigerate until well chilled.
Mix sugar, vinegar and salt in small bowl.
Add to cabbage and toss well.
Add cream and toss again.
Cover and refrigerate 30 minutes.
Season with salt and pepper and serve.

title: chinese chicken casserole
directions: Combine chicken, vegetables and soup.
Place in greased casserole dish.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes.
Sprinkle with onions and return to oven for another 5 minutes. Serve over rice.
